Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.57,0:01:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.62,0:01:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.21,0:01:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我们开始前 你要宣读一份声明\N{\r原文字幕}As we begin, I believe you have a statement to read into the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.63,0:01:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 法官大人\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.00,0:01:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不是法官 博士  -对\N{\r原文字幕}We're not judges, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.17,0:01:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然不是\N{\r原文字幕}No. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.81,0:01:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位安全委员会成员\N{\r原文字幕}Members of the security board.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.73,0:01:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们对我做出所谓的诋毁性指控\N{\r原文字幕}The so-called and derogatory information in your indictment of me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无法受到公正评断\N{\r原文字幕}cannot be fairly understood,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.19,0:01:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非真正理解我的生活和工作\N{\r原文字幕}except in the context of my life and my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.36,0:01:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他作证了多久？\N{\r原文字幕}How long did he testify?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.95,0:01:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说 我忘了\N{\r原文字幕}Honestly, I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.20,0:02:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整场听证会耗时一个月\N{\r原文字幕}The whole hearing took a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.24,0:02:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是一场折磨\N{\r原文字幕}An ordeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.62,0:02:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只看过庭审记录\N{\r原文字幕}I've only read the transcripts, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.33,0:02:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁会想为自己的一生辩护？\N{\r原文字幕}Who'd want to justify their whole life?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.96,0:02:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不在场？\N{\r原文字幕}You weren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.92,0:02:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身为主席 我不被允许出席\N{\r原文字幕}-As chairman, I wasn't allowed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.38,0:02:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们真的会问那件事？\N{\r原文字幕}Are they really going to ask about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.01,0:02:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是好几年前的事  -四年前…\N{\r原文字幕}It was years ago. Four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.97,0:02:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五年前\N{\r原文字幕}-Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.89,0:02:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默仍然分裂着美国\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer still divides America.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.64,0:02:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,委员会想知道你的立场\N{\r原文字幕}The committee is gonna want to know where you stood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.27,0:02:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑟蒙参议员不希望你觉得是你在受审\N{\r原文字幕}Senator Thurmond asked me to say not to feel that you're on trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你刚刚说了我才这么觉得\N{\r原文字幕}Aw.Funny, I didn't till you just said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.61,0:02:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯先生…  -是少将\N{\r原文字幕}Really, Mr.Strauss-- It's Admiral.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.28,0:02:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯少将 这只是走程序\N{\r原文字幕}Admiral Strauss.This is a formality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.61,0:02:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾森豪总统请你加入他的内阁\N{\r原文字幕}President Eisenhower has asked you to be in his cabinet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.82,0:02:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参议院别无选择只能确认\N{\r原文字幕}Senate really has no choice but to confirm you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.74,0:02:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他们提起奥本海默？\N{\r原文字幕}And if they bring up Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.12,0:02:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若是如此 你就据实回答\N{\r原文字幕}When they bring up Oppenheimer, you answer honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.49,0:02:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参议员无法否认你尽了职责\N{\r原文字幕}No senator can deny you did your duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.87,0:02:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那会很难堪\N{\r原文字幕}It'll be uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁会想为自己的一生辩护？\N{\r原文字幕}Who'd want to justify their whole life?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.26,0:02:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何离开美国？\N{\r原文字幕}Why did you leave the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.80,0:03:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想学习新物理学\N{\r原文字幕}I, uh--I wanted to study the new physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.39,0:03:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能在美国学习？\N{\r原文字幕}Was there nowhere here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.52,0:03:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伯克利有首屈一指的理论物理学系\N{\r原文字幕}I thought Berkeley had the leading theoretical physics department.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.40,0:03:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我成立了以后就有\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.Once I had built it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.61,0:03:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我得先去欧洲\N{\r原文字幕}But first I had to go to Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.11,0:03:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在剑桥大学的导师是帕特里克·布莱克特\N{\r原文字幕}I went to Cambridge to study under Patrick Blackett.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.53,0:03:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在那里比在美国更快乐？\N{\r原文字幕}Were you happier there than in America?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.53,0:03:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更快乐？  -对\N{\r原文字幕}Happier?  -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.37,0:03:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并没有 我…\N{\r原文字幕}No. No, I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.13,0:03:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很想家\N{\r原文字幕}I was homesick, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.88,0:03:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感情不成熟\N{\r原文字幕}emotionally immature,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.17,0:03:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,受到一个隐藏宇宙的幻象困扰\N{\r原文字幕}troubled by visions of a hidden universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在实验室一无是处\N{\r原文字幕}Useless in the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.99,0:04:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊 奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}Christ, Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有没有睡觉？\N{\r原文字幕}Have you had any sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再来一次\N{\r原文字幕}Start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.87,0:04:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得去听课 先生\N{\r原文字幕}I need to go to the lecture, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.87,0:04:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讲师是尼尔斯·波耳\N{\r原文字幕}It's Niels Bohr.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.09,0:04:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我完全忘了\N{\r原文字幕}I'd completely forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 我们去吧\N{\r原文字幕}All right.Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.55,0:04:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能去 奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, no, not you, Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要涂覆那些平板\N{\r原文字幕}You finish coating those plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,量子物理学不是向前迈进的科学\N{\r原文字幕}Quantum physics is not a step forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.89,0:05:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是一种理解现实的全新方法\N{\r原文字幕}It is a new way to understand reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.90,0:05:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱因斯坦打开一扇门 我们通过它窥探\N{\r原文字幕}Einstein's opened the door. Now we are peering through,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.32,0:05:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到一个全新的世界\N{\r原文字幕}seeing a world inside our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.98,0:05:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,充满能量与悖论 不是每个人都能接受\N{\r原文字幕}A world of energy and paradox that not everyone can accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.95,0:06:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝对是如此\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.33,0:06:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没事吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼尔斯 这是 J·罗伯特·奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}Niels, meet J.Robert Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.83,0:06:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“ J”是什么的缩写？\N{\r原文字幕}What's the J stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.62,0:06:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么都不是\N{\r原文字幕}Nothing, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听了我的讲课 只有你问了好问题\N{\r原文字幕}You were at my lecture.You asked the only good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.59,0:06:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的确独具见解\N{\r原文字幕}No one's denying his insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.21,0:06:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但在实验室的表现有点差强人意\N{\r原文字幕}It's his laboratory work that leaves a little to be desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.84,0:06:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听过同样的讲课…  -在哈佛\N{\r原文字幕}I heard you give the same lectu--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.51,0:06:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你问了同样的问题\N{\r原文字幕}At Harvard, yes, and you asked the same question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.51,0:06:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么再问一次？\N{\r原文字幕}Why ask again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.72,0:06:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不喜欢你的回答\N{\r原文字幕}Hadn't liked your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,昨天的回答有好一些吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you like it better yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.31,0:06:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好很多\N{\r原文字幕}-A lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.39,0:06:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你抬起石头却没想到会出现一条毒蛇\N{\r原文字幕}You can lift the stone without being ready for the snake that's revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在看来你准备好了\N{\r原文字幕}Now it seems you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.23,0:06:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你不喜欢进实验室？\N{\r原文字幕}But you don't enjoy the lab?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就离开剑桥大学的实验室\N{\r原文字幕}So get out of Cambridge with its beakers and potions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.41,0:06:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去能让你思考的地方\N{\r原文字幕}Go somewhere they'll let you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去哪里？\N{\r原文字幕}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.79,0:06:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哥廷根大学\N{\r原文字幕}Göttingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.83,0:06:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玻恩？  -玻恩\N{\r原文字幕}Born.  -Born.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.83,0:07:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前往德国师从马克斯·玻恩\N{\r原文字幕}Get to Germany.Study under Max Born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.75,0:07:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,学习理论方法\N{\r原文字幕}Learn the ways of theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.21,0:07:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会捎个口信\N{\r原文字幕}I'll send word.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有虫子\N{\r原文字幕}Wormhole.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.55,0:07:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的数学好不好？\N{\r原文字幕}How's your mathematics?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对他想当的物理学家还不够好\N{\r原文字幕}Not good enough for the physicist he wants to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.09,0:07:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,代数就像乐谱\N{\r原文字幕}Algebra's like sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重点不是你会不会读音乐？\N{\r原文字幕}The important thing isn't "can you read music?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.81,0:07:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是能不能听到？你能听到音乐吗？\N{\r原文字幕}It's "can you hear it?" Can you hear the music, Robert?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.90,0:07:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能听到\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.24,0:09:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来自怀俄明州的参议员\N{\r原文字幕}The senator from Wyoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.83,0:09:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯少将…\N{\r原文字幕}Admiral Strauss,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道你和罗伯特·奥本海默的关系\N{\r原文字幕}I'm interested in your relationship with Dr.J.Robert Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在1947年认识他？\N{\r原文字幕}You met him in 1947?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.96,0:09:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当时是原子能委员会主席？\N{\r原文字幕}You were commissioner of the Atomic Energy Commission?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.17,0:09:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 但我认识罗伯特的时候是…\N{\r原文字幕}I was, but I actually met Robert in my capacity as board member
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普林斯顿高等研究院理事会成员\N{\r原文字幕}of the Institute for Advanced Study at Princeton,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.72,0:09:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在战后是举世闻名的物理界巨擘\N{\r原文字幕}because after the war he was world renowned as the great man of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我决心要请他担任院长\N{\r原文字幕}and I was determined to get him to run the Institute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.95,0:09:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士 幸会了\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.An honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.79,0:09:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯先生\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.04,0:09:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,应该念成 “史劳斯”\N{\r原文字幕}It's pronounced "straws."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.37,0:09:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欧本海默 奥本海默…\N{\r原文字幕}Oh-ppenheimer, Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎么念都是犹太人\N{\r原文字幕}Whatever way you say it, they know I'm Jewish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.92,0:09:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是曼哈顿以马内利会堂的主席\N{\r原文字幕}I'm president of Temple Emanu-El in Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.01,0:09:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“史劳斯” 只是南方的发音\N{\r原文字幕}"Straws" is just the Southern pronunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.63,0:09:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎来到研究院 你在这里会很开心\N{\r原文字幕}Anyway, welcome to the Institute. I think you could be very happy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.60,0:10:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且通勤很方便\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, well, you'll love the commute.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那栋房子是给你和尊夫人住的…\N{\r原文字幕}The position comes with that house for you and your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.22,0:10:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有两个小孩？\N{\r原文字幕}and your--Is it two children?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.31,0:10:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 两个\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.60,0:10:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我非常崇拜你的研究成果\N{\r原文字幕}I'm a great admirer of your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.23,0:10:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是物理学家吗 史劳斯先生？\N{\r原文字幕}And you're a physicist by training, Mr.Strauss?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 休息室下午四点有茶点\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry, common room, four o'clock tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.74,0:10:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我没念过什么书 完全是白手起家\N{\r原文字幕}No, I'm not trained in physics or anything else. I'm a self-made man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能理解  -真的吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Ah.I can relate to that.Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.28,0:10:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 我父亲也一样\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, my father was one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.41,0:10:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这会是你的办公室\N{\r原文字幕}And this would be your office.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.47,0:10:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说他下午多半都会在那里\N{\r原文字幕}I'm told he's there most afternoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很好奇你为何没让他参与曼哈顿计划\N{\r原文字幕}You know, I've always wondered why you didn't involve him in the Manhattan Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.89,0:10:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们这个时代最伟大的科学家\N{\r原文字幕}Greatest scientific mind of our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.23,0:10:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他那个时代\N{\r原文字幕}Of his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.31,0:10:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱因斯坦在40年多前发表相对论\N{\r原文字幕}Einstein published his Theory of Relativity more than 40 years ago now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.28,0:10:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却从未接受它揭露的量子世界\N{\r原文字幕}But never embraced the quantum world it revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“上帝不会掷骰子”\N{\r原文字幕}"God doesn't play dice."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.95,0:11:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一点也没错\N{\r原文字幕}Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没想过要正式学习物理学？\N{\r原文字幕}You never thought of studying physics formally, Mr.Strauss?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.16,0:11:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有过机会 但我选择卖鞋子\N{\r原文字幕}I had offers, but I chose to sell shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.29,0:11:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,路易斯·史劳斯曾是低微的鞋类销售员\N{\r原文字幕}Lewis Strauss was once a lowly shoe salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.00,0:11:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 就只是鞋类销售员\N{\r原文字幕}No, just a shoe salesman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以介绍你们认识  -没必要\N{\r原文字幕}I'd love to introduce you. No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.22,0:11:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认识他很多年了\N{\r原文字幕}I have known him for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.53,0:11:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么回事？你跟他说了什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What was that? What did you say to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.46,0:11:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他没事啦\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, he's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.72,0:12:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的过去有些事你应该知道\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Strauss, there are things in my past you ought to be aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.39,0:12:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身为原子能委员会主席\N{\r原文字幕}Well, as chairman of the AEC,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.18,0:12:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看过你的安全档案\N{\r原文字幕}I have access to your security file. I've read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不担心？  -不担心\N{\r原文字幕}You're not worried? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.48,0:12:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为国家贡献良多 我为什么要担心？\N{\r原文字幕}Why would I be worried after everything you've done for your country?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.31,0:12:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时代改变了 史特劳斯先生\N{\r原文字幕}Well, times change, Mr.Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.98,0:12:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这所研究院的目的…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, the purpose of this institute
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是为独立思想家提供避风港\N{\r原文字幕}is to provide a haven for independent minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.19,0:12:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是这份工作的最佳人选\N{\r原文字幕}That's you. You are the man for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.82,0:12:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会考虑看看\N{\r原文字幕}Well, then I'll consider it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天在原子能委员会会议上见\N{\r原文字幕}I'll see you at the AEC meeting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.87,0:12:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是全国威望最高的职位\N{\r原文字幕}This is one of the most prestigious appointments in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 而且通勤很方便\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, with a great commute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.17,0:12:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我会考虑看看\N{\r原文字幕}That's why I'm considering it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在任命奥本海默博士之前他就提到…\N{\r原文字幕}So, Dr.Oppenheimer brought your attention to his past associations
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.84,0:12:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他过去的左翼倾向？\N{\r原文字幕}before you appointed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.93,0:12:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不感到担忧？\N{\r原文字幕}-And they didn't concern you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.35,0:12:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我当时只担心他跟爱因斯坦\N{\r原文字幕}Just then I was entirely consumed with what he must have said to Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.35,0:12:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说的话会让他讨厌我\N{\r原文字幕}to sour him on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.32,0:12:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是后来呢？\N{\r原文字幕}But later?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.40,0:13:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道后来发生什么事\N{\r原文字幕}Well, we all know what happened later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.82,0:13:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,博士 你在欧洲…\N{\r原文字幕}Doctor, your time in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.86,0:13:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,见过许多其他国家的物理学家\N{\r原文字幕}you seemed to meet with a wide range of other countries' physicists.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 没错\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有俄国人吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Any Russians?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.24,0:13:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一时想不到\N{\r原文字幕}None that spring to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.58,0:13:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请让我继续宣读声明…\N{\r原文字幕}If you'll just allow me to continue with my statement--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.08,0:13:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗博先生 你会有充分机会交叉诘问\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Robb, you'll have ample opportunity to cross-examine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.46,0:13:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我离开哥廷根后前往荷兰莱登大学\N{\r原文字幕}After Göttingen, I moved on to Leiden in Holland,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.38,0:13:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一次见到伊西多拉比\N{\r原文字幕}where I first met Isidor Rabi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.14,0:13:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思\N{\r原文字幕}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.39,0:13:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国佬讲解新物理学？我非听不可\N{\r原文字幕}A Yank, lecturing on the new physics? This I have to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我也是美国人\N{\r原文字幕}I'm an American myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.02,0:13:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真没想到\N{\r原文字幕}How surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要帮你翻译英文就跟我说\N{\r原文字幕}Let me know if you need any help with the English.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:13:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等 他在说什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Wait, what's he saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.55,0:14:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不了 谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.64,0:14:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到苏黎世还要很久\N{\r原文字幕}It's a long way to Zurich.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.52,0:14:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你再瘦一点就会陷入坐垫中间\N{\r原文字幕}You get any skinnier, we're gonna lose you between the seat cushions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是拉比\N{\r原文字幕}I'm Rabi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.19,0:14:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.44,0:14:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听了你关于分子的讲课 只听懂一点\N{\r原文字幕}I caught your lecture on molecules. Caught some of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.65,0:14:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是纽约犹太人 你怎么会荷兰语？\N{\r原文字幕}We're a couple of New York Jews.How do you know Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要来一个学期 最好学会荷兰语\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I thought I'd better learn it when I got here this semester.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你六周内就学会用荷兰语教量子力学？\N{\r原文字幕}You learned enough Dutch in six weeks to give a lecture on quantum mechanics?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.53,0:14:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想挑战自己\N{\r原文字幕}Wanted to challenge myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.91,0:14:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,量子物理学的挑战性还不够\N{\r原文字幕}Quantum physics wasn't challenging enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史威泽  -“史威泽”？\N{\r原文字幕}Schvitzer.Schvitzer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱现鬼\N{\r原文字幕}Show-off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,六周学会荷兰语却没学过意第绪语？\N{\r原文字幕}Dutch in six weeks, but you never learned Yiddish?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.71,0:14:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我住的高级住宅区不太会用到\N{\r原文字幕}They don't speak it so much my side of the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.75,0:14:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去你的\N{\r原文字幕}Screw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.47,0:14:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想家吗？\N{\r原文字幕}You homesick?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.55,0:14:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了\N{\r原文字幕}-Oh, you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们这种人在这里好像不太受欢迎\N{\r原文字幕}Ever get the feeling our kind isn't entirely welcome here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.97,0:14:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,物理学家？\N{\r原文字幕}Physicists?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很搞笑  -在系上不会\N{\r原文字幕}That's funny. Not in the department.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.60,0:14:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们也都是犹太人\N{\r原文字幕}They're all Jewish too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.44,0:15:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吃吧\N{\r原文字幕}Eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.82,0:15:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得去找一个德国人\N{\r原文字幕}There's a German you have to seek out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.07,0:15:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海森堡  -没错\N{\r原文字幕}Heisenberg.Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.66,0:15:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们可能会假设量子世界的背后…\N{\r原文字幕}One might be led to the presumption that behind the quantum world,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.67,0:15:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仍有一个因果关系成立的真实世界\N{\r原文字幕}there still hides a real world in which causality holds,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这种假设对我们来说…\N{\r原文字幕}but such speculations seem to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.88,0:15:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说毫无用处 谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}to say it explicitly, fruitless. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.89,0:15:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝大家愉快\N{\r原文字幕}Have a great day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.31,0:15:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太精彩了  -谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Werner.Wonderful.Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.85,0:15:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.31,0:15:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默 我喜欢你关于分子的论文\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer, yes.I liked your paper on molecules.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.11,0:15:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是受到你的启发\N{\r原文字幕}Probably because you inspired it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.44,0:15:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我若还有什么启发 我们可以共同发表\N{\r原文字幕}If I inspire anything else, let me know. We could publish together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.32,0:15:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须赶回美国\N{\r原文字幕}I have to get back to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.03,0:15:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？那里没人认真看待量子力学\N{\r原文字幕}Why? There's no one there taking quantum mechanics seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.03,0:15:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是原因\N{\r原文字幕}That's exactly why.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.79,0:16:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很想念曼哈顿的峡谷\N{\r原文字幕}He's pining for the canyons of Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新墨西哥州的峡谷\N{\r原文字幕}Canyons of New Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.58,0:16:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来自新墨西哥州？\N{\r原文字幕}You're from New Mexico?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.67,0:16:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纽约 但我和弟弟在圣塔菲郊外有座牧场\N{\r原文字幕}No.New York, but my brother and I have a ranch outside Santa Fe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.13,0:16:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那才是我想念的美国\N{\r原文字幕}That's the America I miss right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.88,0:16:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们最好赶快回家 牛仔们\N{\r原文字幕}Then it's best you get home, cowboys.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.26,0:16:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有他 我和马匹合不来\N{\r原文字幕}That's him. No, me and horses? I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.52,0:16:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴认识你\N{\r原文字幕}Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.56,0:16:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有没有再见到海森堡？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you ever encounter Heisenberg again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.81,0:16:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没再见到本人 但…\N{\r原文字幕}Not in person, no, but, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.02,0:16:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在工作上交过手\N{\r原文字幕}you might say our paths crossed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.74,0:16:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一回到美国就接受\N{\r原文字幕}On returning to America,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.07,0:16:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加州理工学院和伯克利的教职\N{\r原文字幕}I accepted positions at both Caltech and up at Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.52,0:17:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我猜你就是劳伦斯博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Lawrence, I presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.44,0:17:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一定是奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}You must be Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.77,0:17:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说你想成立量子理论系所\N{\r原文字幕}I hear you want to start a school of quantum theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.36,0:17:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经在隔壁成立了\N{\r原文字幕}I am starting it.Next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被安排在那里？\N{\r原文字幕}They put you in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我要求的 我想接近你这种实验学者\N{\r原文字幕}I asked for it. Wanted to be close to you experimentalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.57,0:17:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理论是有局限的\N{\r原文字幕}Theory will get you only so far, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.53,0:17:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在建造一台粒子加速器\N{\r原文字幕}We're building a machine to accelerate electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.66,0:17:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\N{\r原文字幕}Magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.99,0:17:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想帮忙吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Would you like to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.12,0:17:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帮忙建造？不了\N{\r原文字幕}Build it? Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.29,0:17:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我想用它来测试我研究的理论\N{\r原文字幕}No, no. But I am working on theories I'd like to test with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.79,0:17:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你几时开始教课？\N{\r原文字幕}When do you start teaching?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一堂课是一小时后\N{\r原文字幕}I've got my first in an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.50,0:17:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小组讨论？\N{\r原文字幕}Seminar?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.67,0:17:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一名学生\N{\r原文字幕}-Pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一名学生？就这样？\N{\r原文字幕}One student? That's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.09,0:17:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要教没人梦想过的理论\N{\r原文字幕}I'm teaching something no one here has dreamt of.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但只要知道它能用来做什么…\N{\r原文字幕}But once people start hearing what you can do with it--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.64,0:17:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就无法回头\N{\r原文字幕}There's no going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.39,0:17:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一定是走错…\N{\r原文字幕}Oh.I must have missed the--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨先生？\N{\r原文字幕}-Mr.Lomanitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对啊\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.73,0:17:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是这里 请进\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, this is it.Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.82,0:17:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下来\N{\r原文字幕}Take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.95,0:18:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对量子力学了解多少？\N{\r原文字幕}What do you know about quantum mechanics?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.66,0:18:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有一些基本的了解\N{\r原文字幕}I have a grasp on the basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就完全误解了\N{\r原文字幕}Then you're doing it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.71,0:18:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,光是由粒子或波动构成？\N{\r原文字幕}Is light made up of particles or waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.29,0:18:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,量子力学说两者都是 怎么可能？\N{\r原文字幕}Quantum mechanics says it's both.How could it be both?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.04,0:18:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能  -不可能\N{\r原文字幕}It can't.  -It can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.05,0:18:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它是 这是悖论 但却成立\N{\r原文字幕}But it is. It's paradoxical, and yet, it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.77,0:18:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在\N{\r原文字幕}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.40,0:18:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨先生 你不会被当掉\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Lomanitz. You're gonna be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.77,0:18:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史奈德先生\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Snyder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们想像一颗恒星\N{\r原文字幕}Now let's consider a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.74,0:18:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个在外太空燃烧的巨大熔炉\N{\r原文字幕}A star. A vast furnace burning in outer space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.95,0:18:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火焰违反自身重力向外扩散\N{\r原文字幕}fire pushing outwards against its own gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,达到平衡\N{\r原文字幕}Balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.12,0:18:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当星体冷却 重力起作用 它就会收缩\N{\r原文字幕}But if that furnace cools and gravity starts winning, it contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.67,0:18:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,密度会增加\N{\r原文字幕}Density increases.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.34,0:18:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.34,0:18:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重力增加\N{\r原文字幕}Increasing gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,密度增加\N{\r原文字幕}Increasing density.  -And?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.05,0:18:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢？  -这是恶性循环 直到…\N{\r原文字幕}It's a vicious cycle until...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.09,0:18:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,极限是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What's the limit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.01,0:19:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.01,0:19:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看数学带我们去哪里\N{\r原文字幕}See where the math takes us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我保证是没有人去过的地方\N{\r原文字幕}I guarantee it's somewhere no one's been before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.31,0:19:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你问我？\N{\r原文字幕}Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.14,0:19:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 你的数学比我好\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, you.Your math is better than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.94,0:19:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默的档案详记他在伯克利的活动\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer's file contained details of his activities in Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.48,0:19:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们为何在战前就建立他的档案？\N{\r原文字幕}Why would they have started a file on Dr.Oppenheimer before the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.90,0:19:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这你就得去问胡佛先生\N{\r原文字幕}Well, you'd have to ask Mr.Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在问你 史特劳斯少将\N{\r原文字幕}I'm asking you, Admiral Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.08,0:19:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的假设是这跟他的…\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, my assumption is that it was connected to his,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.54,0:19:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,左翼政治活动有关\N{\r原文字幕}uh, left-wing political activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.54,0:19:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不该让学生在课堂上讨论政治 奥比\N{\r原文字幕}You shouldn't let them bring up politics in the classroom, Oppie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.05,0:19:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我写的\N{\r原文字幕}I wrote that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.38,0:19:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯 你支持物理学革命\N{\r原文字幕}Lawrence, you embrace the revolution in physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道看不出处处都有革命？\N{\r原文字幕}Can't you see it everywhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.18,0:19:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毕卡索 史特拉汶斯基\N{\r原文字幕}Picasso, Stravinsky,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.47,0:19:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佛洛伊德 马克思\N{\r原文字幕}Freud, Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里是美国 奥比\N{\r原文字幕}Well, this is America, Oppie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.77,0:19:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有过革命了\N{\r原文字幕}We had our revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.31,0:19:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说真的 别带进实验室\N{\r原文字幕}Seriously, keep it out of the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.19,0:19:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在实验室外 我房东今晚有场讨论会\N{\r原文字幕}Well, out of the lab, my landlady is having a discussion group tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.86,0:19:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有兴趣吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.94,0:20:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我参加过伯克利的政治活动\N{\r原文字幕}I have sampled the Berkeley political scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.95,0:20:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哲学系研究生和共产党员高谈种族共融\N{\r原文字幕}It's all just philosophy postgrads and communists talking integration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.37,0:20:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不关心种族共融\N{\r原文字幕}You don't care about integration?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.12,0:20:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想投票支持 不是高谈阔论\N{\r原文字幕}I want to vote for it, not talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.95,0:20:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是在周五 去吃饭吧\N{\r原文字幕}Especially on a Friday. Come on.Let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.62,0:20:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去见我弟弟\N{\r原文字幕}I'm meeting my brother there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.71,0:20:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,联邦调查局怎么会注意到这些活动？\N{\r原文字幕}And how would these activities have come to the attention of the FBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.46,0:20:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我没记错\N{\r原文字幕}Well, if I remember correctly,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.51,0:20:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,联邦探员在共产党集会外面抄车牌时\N{\r原文字幕}the FBI was taking license plates outside suspected communist gatherings,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.72,0:20:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到他的名字\N{\r原文字幕}and his name popped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.40,0:20:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吓到你了  -老天爷\N{\r原文字幕}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.94,0:20:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 哥  -弗兰克\N{\r原文字幕}Sorry. Frank.Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.23,0:20:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该记得贾姬\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, you remember Jackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\r原文字幕}Evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.57,0:20:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.03,0:20:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 我要你见见薛瓦利埃\N{\r原文字幕}Robert. I want you to meet Chevalier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.50,0:20:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈肯薛瓦利埃博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Haakon Chevalier,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特·奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Robert Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸会  -幸会 这是我弟弟弗兰克\N{\r原文字幕}Pleasure.Pleasure. This is my little brother, Frank.Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.33,0:20:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位是…\N{\r原文字幕}And this is--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.46,0:20:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是贾姬\N{\r原文字幕}-Still Jackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.46,0:20:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 还是贾姬\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Still Jackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.59,0:21:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薛瓦利埃 你在语言学系？\N{\r原文字幕}Chevalier, you're in languages?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.63,0:21:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我早就听说过你了\N{\r原文字幕}And your reputation precedes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.38,0:21:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听说过我什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What have you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在教一门全新的物理学\N{\r原文字幕}That you're teaching a radical new approach to physics
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.76,0:21:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我完全不懂 但我没听说你是党员\N{\r原文字幕}I have no chance of understanding, but I hadn't heard you're a Party member.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是  -还不是\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not.  -Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.77,0:21:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和弗兰克正在考虑加入\N{\r原文字幕}Frank and I are thinking of joining.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.39,0:21:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我前几天…  -我支持各种行动\N{\r原文字幕}Just the other day, I was-- I support a range of causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.65,0:21:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西班牙内战？\N{\r原文字幕}The Spanish Civil War?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.36,0:21:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁不支持法西斯暴徒推翻民主共和国\N{\r原文字幕}A democratic republic being overthrown by fascist thugs, who wouldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.23,0:21:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国政府\N{\r原文字幕}Our government.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们认为社会主义比法西斯主义更危险\N{\r原文字幕}They think that socialism is a bigger threat than fascism.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.07,0:21:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快就不会 看看纳粹怎么迫害犹太人\N{\r原文字幕}Not for long.Look at what the Nazis are doing to the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.87,0:21:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我寄钱给德国的同事让他们移民\N{\r原文字幕}I send funds to colleagues in Germany to emigrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.49,0:21:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须有点实际行动\N{\r原文字幕}I have to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.04,0:21:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的研究太抽象了\N{\r原文字幕}My own work is so abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.00,0:21:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在研究什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What are you working on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.08,0:21:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恒星死亡后会发生什么事\N{\r原文字幕}What happens to stars when they die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.54,0:21:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恒星会死亡？\N{\r原文字幕}Do stars die?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.00,0:21:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们死亡后\N{\r原文字幕}Well, if they do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.63,0:21:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会先冷却然后坍缩\N{\r原文字幕}they cool, then collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.47,0:21:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恒星越大 过程会越猛烈\N{\r原文字幕}In fact, the bigger the star, the more violent its demise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.68,0:21:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重力塌缩的强大力量会吞噬一切\N{\r原文字幕}Their gravity gets so concentrated, it swallows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.77,0:21:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切 包括光\N{\r原文字幕}Everything, even light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.35,0:21:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那真的有可能发生？\N{\r原文字幕}Can that really happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.69,0:21:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数学说有可能\N{\r原文字幕}The math says it can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若能发表论文 也许天文学家就会发现\N{\r原文字幕}If we can get published, then perhaps one day an astronomer finds one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但目前只是理论 不会影响日常生活\N{\r原文字幕}But right now, all I have is theory, which can't impact people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.36,0:22:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想寄钱去西班牙最好通过共产党\N{\r原文字幕}Well, if you're going to send money to Spain, do it through the Communist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们能把钱带到前线\N{\r原文字幕}They can get it to the front lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.49,0:22:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛丽寄给我这些\N{\r原文字幕}-Mary sent me with these.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是琼\N{\r原文字幕}I'm Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.41,0:22:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.41,0:22:17.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是哈肯薛瓦利埃\N{\r原文字幕}Haakon Chevalier.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.62,0:22:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上个月在瑟伯尔家的工会会议？\N{\r原文字幕}The union meeting at Serber's last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.54,0:22:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 没错\N{\r原文字幕}Right, right, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.00,0:22:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.67,0:22:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特说他不是共产主义者\N{\r原文字幕}Robert here says he's not a communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.76,0:22:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他就不够了解\N{\r原文字幕}Well, then he doesn't know enough about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.97,0:22:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我读完三卷《资本论》 这算不算？\N{\r原文字幕}I've read Das Kapital, all three volumes. Does that count?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.68,0:22:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你比大多数的党员读得更多\N{\r原文字幕}-It would make you better read than most party members.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.97,0:22:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太枯燥了 有些想法…\N{\r原文字幕}It's turgid stuff. There's some thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.27,0:22:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“所有权就是窃盗”\N{\r原文字幕}"Ownership is theft."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.60,0:22:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“财产”\N{\r原文字幕}"Property."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.73,0:22:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“财产”？  -“财产” 不是“所有权”\N{\r原文字幕}"Property"? "Property," not "ownership."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.48,0:22:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 我读的是德文原版\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry, I read it in the original German.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.73,0:22:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,失陪了\N{\r原文字幕}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.94,0:22:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,书不是重点\N{\r原文字幕}It's not about the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.32,0:22:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重点是想法 你似乎不太相信\N{\r原文字幕}It's about the ideas. And you sound uncommitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.53,0:22:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信应该自由思考如何改善世界\N{\r原文字幕}I'm committed to thinking freely about how to improve our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.54,0:22:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何要局限于一种教条？\N{\r原文字幕}Why limit yourself to one dogma?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.75,0:22:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是物理学家 你该挑选规则？\N{\r原文字幕}You're a physicist.You pick and choose rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.75,0:23:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是该将你的精力投注于社会进步？\N{\r原文字幕}Or do you use the discipline to channel your energies into progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.05,0:23:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢有点转圜空间\N{\r原文字幕}I like a little wiggle room.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.84,0:23:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你总是坚守党的路线吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you always toe the party line?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.47,0:23:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也喜欢有转圜空间\N{\r原文字幕}I like my wiggle room too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.94,0:23:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了？\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.02,0:23:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等\N{\r原文字幕}Wait, wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.03,0:23:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真没想到\N{\r原文字幕}Unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.74,0:23:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么？\N{\r原文字幕}-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.07,0:23:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看很多书嘛\N{\r原文字幕}For a physicist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.16,0:23:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的书架上只有佛洛伊德？\N{\r原文字幕}You only have a shelf full of Freud?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.70,0:23:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实我比较倾向…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, actually, my background's more--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.37,0:23:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,荣格？\N{\r原文字幕}Jungian?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.38,0:23:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道分析心理学？\N{\r原文字幕}You know analysis?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.84,0:23:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在剑桥大学念研究所时出了点事\N{\r原文字幕}When I was a postgrad at Cambridge, I had a little trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.09,0:23:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我洗耳恭听\N{\r原文字幕}I'll bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.09,0:23:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我试图毒死我的老师\N{\r原文字幕}I tried to poison my tutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.01,0:23:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你恨他吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you hate him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.01,0:23:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很喜欢他\N{\r原文字幕}I liked him very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.76,0:23:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只是需要找人上床\N{\r原文字幕}You just needed to get laid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.47,0:23:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的心理师花了两年都没说到这重点\N{\r原文字幕}Took my analyst two years, and I don't think they ever put it that succinctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.23,0:24:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你让每个人都以为你这人很复杂\N{\r原文字幕}You have everyone convinced you're more complicated than you actually are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.15,0:24:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个人的本质都很单纯\N{\r原文字幕}We're all simple souls, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.48,0:24:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就不是\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.24,0:24:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.24,0:24:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,梵文\N{\r原文字幕}Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.90,0:24:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能读梵文？\N{\r原文字幕}You can read this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.28,0:24:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在学\N{\r原文字幕}I'm learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.00,0:24:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,读这一段\N{\r原文字幕}Read this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.58,0:24:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毗湿奴在这里显现他多臂的本相…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, in this part, Vishnu reveals his multi-armed self--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.34,0:24:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.46,0:24:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,读出这一段话\N{\r原文字幕}Read the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.01,0:24:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“我现在成了死神”\N{\r原文字幕}"And now I am become Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.27,0:24:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“世界的毁灭者”\N{\r原文字幕}"The destroyer of worlds."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.47,0:25:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里就行\N{\r原文字幕}This'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.35,0:25:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暴风雨在日出前就会停息\N{\r原文字幕}It'll break before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.14,0:25:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚上会降温 日出前就会停息\N{\r原文字幕}Air cools overnight.Just before dawn, it breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.69,0:25:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\r原文字幕}Come on.Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.99,0:25:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要结婚了\N{\r原文字幕}I'm getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.70,0:25:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克 恭喜了  -谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Frank.Congratulations.  -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.12,0:25:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是贾姬吗？\N{\r原文字幕}To Jackie?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.25,0:25:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对啊 是贾姬\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, to Jackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.71,0:25:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个女服务生\N{\r原文字幕}The waitress.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.79,0:25:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比 你说对了 暴风雨停息了\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie, you're right.It's lettin' up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.84,0:25:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去看有没有星星\N{\r原文字幕}I'm gonna go see if there's any stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.13,0:25:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你老是说要支持平民百姓\N{\r原文字幕}All your talk about the common man,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.22,0:25:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却觉得贾姬不够好？\N{\r原文字幕}but Jackie's not good enough for you, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.80,0:25:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们加入共产党\N{\r原文字幕}We join the Party,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.89,0:26:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你却无法掩饰你的不满\N{\r原文字幕}and you can't hide your disapproval, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.39,0:26:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为你本来要加入吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is that because that's supposed to be your thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.22,0:26:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有加入共产党\N{\r原文字幕}I haven't joined the Party, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.85,0:26:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为她不该说服你加入\N{\r原文字幕}And I don't think she should have convinced you to either.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一半的教职员都是党员\N{\r原文字幕}Half of the faculty is communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.10,0:26:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们系上不是\N{\r原文字幕}Not that half.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.61,0:26:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是你哥 我要你小心点\N{\r原文字幕}I'm your brother, Frank, and I want you to be cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.53,0:26:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想扭断你脖子\N{\r原文字幕}And I want to wring your neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.16,0:26:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想过担心犯错的生活\N{\r原文字幕}I won't live my life afraid to make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.20,0:26:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你很幸福 我替你高兴\N{\r原文字幕}You're happy, I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.66,0:26:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很高兴你为我感到高兴\N{\r原文字幕}So then I'm happy you're happy that I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.30,0:26:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我好像能看到你在研究的暗星\N{\r原文字幕}I feel like I could see one of those dark stars that you're working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.67,0:26:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能 那就是重点\N{\r原文字幕}You can't.That's the whole point.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.80,0:26:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的重力吞噬了光\N{\r原文字幕}Their gravity swallows light.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.72,0:26:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像太空中的一个洞\N{\r原文字幕}It's like a kind of hole in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.85,0:26:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克没事吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Is Frank okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.14,0:26:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事 他只是有个烂哥哥\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.He just has a shitty brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.77,0:26:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里很特别\N{\r原文字幕}It is special here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.78,0:26:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我小时候…\N{\r原文字幕}When I was a kid,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.28,0:26:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以为只要想办法…\N{\r原文字幕}I thought if I could find a way
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.41,0:27:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结合物理学和新墨西哥州\N{\r原文字幕}to combine physics and New Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.70,0:27:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的人生就会圆满\N{\r原文字幕}my life would be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.41,0:27:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里太偏僻了\N{\r原文字幕}Little remote for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.62,0:27:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.88,0:27:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,睡觉吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.54,0:27:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天看到的那片台地是我最喜欢的地方\N{\r原文字幕}That mesa we saw today, one of my favorite places in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.22,0:27:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天要爬上去\N{\r原文字幕}Tomorrow we'll climb it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.76,0:27:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那地方叫什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What's it called?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.14,0:27:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.43,0:27:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没想到今天会见到你\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't expect to see you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.69,0:27:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得先跟你预约吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do I have to make an appointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.32,0:27:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿！给我回来！\N{\r原文字幕}Hey! Hey, get back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.28,0:27:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔瓦雷茨？\N{\r原文字幕}-Alvarez?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.57,0:27:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比！奥比！\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie! Oppie!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.20,0:27:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干嘛？怎么了？\N{\r原文字幕}What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.29,0:27:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们做到了 德国的哈恩和施特拉斯曼\N{\r原文字幕}They've done it.They've done it. Hahn and Strassmann in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.17,0:27:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们分裂了铀核\N{\r原文字幕}They split the uranium nucleus.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.54,0:27:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么做到的？\N{\r原文字幕}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.88,0:27:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用中子撞击它\N{\r原文字幕}Bombarded it with neutrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.80,0:28:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是核分裂\N{\r原文字幕}It's a nuclear fission.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.17,0:28:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们造成原子核分裂\N{\r原文字幕}They did it, they split the atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.88,0:28:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是不可能的\N{\r原文字幕}It's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.35,0:28:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也要试着这么做\N{\r原文字幕}I'm gonna try to reproduce it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.73,0:28:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瞧？不可能做到\N{\r原文字幕}See? Can't be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.86,0:28:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常优雅 也很简单\N{\r原文字幕}Very elegant. Quite clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.20,0:28:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有一个问题\N{\r原文字幕}There's just one problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.45,0:28:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在哪里？\N{\r原文字幕}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.99,0:28:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,隔壁\N{\r原文字幕}Next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.70,0:28:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔瓦雷茨做到了\N{\r原文字幕}Alvarez did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.12,0:28:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看 这些核脉冲 非常巨大\N{\r原文字幕}But then look, these fission pulses, they're massive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.17,0:28:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在10分钟内看到30次\N{\r原文字幕}I've seen 30 of these in the past ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.09,0:28:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理论是有局限的\N{\r原文字幕}Theory will take you only so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.93,0:28:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这过程中…\N{\r原文字幕}During the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.01,0:28:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,释放出的中子能用来分裂其它铀原子核\N{\r原文字幕}extra neutrons boil off, which could be used to split other uranium atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.98,0:28:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,造成连锁反应\N{\r原文字幕}Chain reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.81,0:28:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也在想同样的事\N{\r原文字幕}You're thinkin' what I'm thinkin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.15,0:28:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你我和全世界的物理学家都看到新闻\N{\r原文字幕}You, me and every other physicist around the world who's seen the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.03,0:29:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都在想什么事？\N{\r原文字幕}What? What are we all thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.82,0:29:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一颗炸弹 阿尔瓦雷茨\N{\r原文字幕}A bomb, Alvarez.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.78,0:29:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一颗炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}A bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.37,0:29:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说过 别再送我花了\N{\r原文字幕}I told you, Robert, no more fucking flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.62,0:29:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要我做什么？\N{\r原文字幕}I don't understand what you want from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.00,0:29:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我什么都不要你做\N{\r原文字幕}I don't want anything from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.88,0:29:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你又打给我\N{\r原文字幕}Well, you say that and then you call.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.84,0:29:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就不要回应\N{\r原文字幕}Well, don't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.84,0:29:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一定会回应\N{\r原文字幕}I'll always answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.51,0:29:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.89,0:29:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但别再送花\N{\r原文字幕}Just no more flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.31,0:29:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不来吗？\N{\r原文字幕}You're not coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.48,0:29:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要知道自己被拒绝 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}You have to know when you're beaten, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.07,0:29:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没那么简单 哈肯\N{\r原文字幕}It's not that simple, Hoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.94,0:29:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薛瓦利埃 很高兴见到你 芭芭拉…\N{\r原文字幕}Chevalier, good to see you.Barbara, good to see you,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.24,0:29:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有著名的奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}and the illustrious Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.82,0:29:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是艾尔坦顿\N{\r原文字幕}I'm Eltenton.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.12,0:29:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸会了  -请吧\N{\r原文字幕}Pleasure. Please, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.49,0:29:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能谈谈校园的组织化劳工吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Might you say a word about organized labor on campuses, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.50,0:29:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,借过！\N{\r原文字幕}Coming through! Coming through.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.08,0:29:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在壳牌石油工作\N{\r原文字幕}I work at Shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.50,0:30:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,化学家和工程师都加入\N{\r原文字幕}We've signed up chemists, we signed up engineers,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.71,0:30:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,学术界的科学家为何不能？\N{\r原文字幕}so why not scientists in academia?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.67,0:30:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比…奥比…\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie! Oppie! Oppie! Oppie! Oppie! Oppie!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.64,0:30:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,教师有工会 教授为何不能有？\N{\r原文字幕}Teachers are unionized. Why not professors?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.52,0:30:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没别的事吗？\N{\r原文字幕}-Don't you have somewhere to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.02,0:30:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯 学者也有权利\N{\r原文字幕}Lawrence, academics have rights too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.36,0:30:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是那样 我有个讨论小组\N{\r原文字幕}Look, it's not that.I've got a group coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.65,0:30:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我要旁听\N{\r原文字幕}Oh.I'll sit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.24,0:30:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次不行\N{\r原文字幕}Not this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.87,0:30:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查德 布希博士\N{\r原文字幕}Richard.Dr.Bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.67,0:30:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们怎么会来北加州？\N{\r原文字幕}What brings you two up north?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.18,0:30:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查德 跟露丝说我周四会去帕萨迪纳\N{\r原文字幕}Richard, you tell Ruth I'll be down to Pasadena Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.65,0:31:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的黑洞论文发表了！\N{\r原文字幕}Your paper on black holes is in!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.65,0:31:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈特兰呢？把哈特兰找来\N{\r原文字幕}Where's Hartland? Get Hartland.Get Hartland.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.53,0:31:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1939年9月1日 世人会记得这一天\N{\r原文字幕}September 1st, 1939.The world's gonna remember this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.83,0:31:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈特兰 我们的论文已经付梓了\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, Hartland.Our paper, it's in print.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.79,0:31:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被抢了风头\N{\r原文字幕}We've been upstaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.38,0:31:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在不列颠战役中 我越来越不同情…\N{\r原文字幕}During the Battle of Britain, I found myself increasingly out of sympathy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.92,0:31:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共产党提倡的中立政策\N{\r原文字幕}with the policy of neutrality that communists advocated.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.97,0:31:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希特勒入侵俄国后我们成为盟友\N{\r原文字幕}But after Hitler invaded Russia and we became allies,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.26,0:31:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你又开始同情共产党吗？\N{\r原文字幕}these communist sympathies, did they return?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.68,0:31:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.89,0:31:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须明确表示 我对俄国改变看法\N{\r原文字幕}I need to make clear that my changing views on Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.52,0:31:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不代表我和意见相左的人士决裂\N{\r原文字幕}did not mean a sharp break from those who held different views.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.07,0:31:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在上一段婚姻有一两年…\N{\r原文字幕}For a year or two, and during a previous marriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.49,0:31:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我太太琪蒂曾经是共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}my wife Kitty had been a Communist Party member.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.70,0:31:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里 我把好酒都放在这儿\N{\r原文字幕}This way.This is where I keep the good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.91,0:31:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为这是托尔曼家的房子\N{\r原文字幕}I thought this was the Tolmans' house.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.83,0:32:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在加州理工学院时住过这里\N{\r原文字幕}I live with them while I'm at Caltech.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.96,0:32:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们需要什么吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you two need anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.67,0:32:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了 露丝\N{\r原文字幕}-We're good, Ruthie.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.96,0:32:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 你是生物学家\N{\r原文字幕}So, you're a biologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.34,0:32:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在却变成家庭主妇\N{\r原文字幕}Well, somehow I have graduated to housewife.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.59,0:32:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能解释量子力学吗？真的很难懂\N{\r原文字幕}Can you explain quantum mechanics to me? Seems baffling.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.68,0:32:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.18,0:32:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个杯子\N{\r原文字幕}Well, this glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.73,0:32:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这杯酒\N{\r原文字幕}this drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.81,0:32:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个台面\N{\r原文字幕}this countertop,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.19,0:32:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的身体\N{\r原文字幕}uh, our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.19,0:32:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有的一切\N{\r原文字幕}all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.40,0:32:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎都是虚体\N{\r原文字幕}It's mostly empty space.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.49,0:32:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多微小能量波结合而成\N{\r原文字幕}Groupings of tiny energy waves bound together.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.62,0:32:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被什么结合？\N{\r原文字幕}By what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.20,0:32:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强大的吸引力说服我们…\N{\r原文字幕}Forces of attraction strong enough to convince us
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.71,0:32:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,物质是固体\N{\r原文字幕}that matter is solid,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.00,0:32:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阻止我的身体穿过你的\N{\r原文字幕}stop my body passing through yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.72,0:33:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你嫁给哈里逊医师\N{\r原文字幕}You're married to Dr.Harrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.93,0:33:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很疏离\N{\r原文字幕}Not very.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.98,0:33:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢上一个女人…\N{\r原文字幕}There is someone that I feel--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.82,0:33:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她有同感吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Does she feel the same way?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.53,0:33:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候有 但是不够\N{\r原文字幕}Sometimes. Not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.36,0:33:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去新墨西哥州\N{\r原文字幕}You know, I'm going to New Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.32,0:33:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带朋友去我的牧场\N{\r原文字幕}To my ranch, with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.20,0:33:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该一起来\N{\r原文字幕}You should come.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.33,0:33:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说带着你先生\N{\r原文字幕}I meant with your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.37,0:33:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才怪\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.62,0:33:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你根本就不在乎他去不去\N{\r原文字幕}'Cause you know it won't make a bit of difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.55,0:33:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么嫁给他？\N{\r原文字幕}Why did you marry him?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.13,0:33:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我当时很迷惘 他人很好\N{\r原文字幕}I was lost and he was kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.85,0:33:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迷惘？\N{\r原文字幕}Lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.18,0:33:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的前夫死了 而且…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, my previous husband had died,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.35,0:33:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才28岁 不想当个寡妇\N{\r原文字幕}and at 28 I wasn't really ready to be a widow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.90,0:33:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你第一任丈夫是谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who was your first husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.90,0:33:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁都不是 但我第二任丈夫是乔戴勒\N{\r原文字幕}Nobody.But my second husband was Joe Dallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.36,0:33:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他跟我一样出身富裕家庭 但…\N{\r原文字幕}He was, um, from money, like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.32,0:33:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在俄亥俄州扬斯敦组织工会 我很爱他\N{\r原文字幕}but he was a union organizer in Youngstown, Ohio. Fell hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.07,0:33:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多爱他？\N{\r原文字幕}How hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.07,0:34:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接下来四年只吃豆子和煎饼\N{\r原文字幕}Hard enough to spend the next four years living off beans and pancakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.74,0:34:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在工厂大门散发《工人日报》\N{\r原文字幕}handing out the Daily Worker at factory gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.29,0:34:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了36岁我跟乔说我再也受不了\N{\r原文字幕}By 36, I just told Joe I couldn't take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.67,0:34:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但退党后一年又想要他回来\N{\r原文字幕}Quit the Party.A year later, I wanted him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.25,0:34:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他 不是《工人日报》…\N{\r原文字幕}Him, not the Daily Worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.96,0:34:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说 “太好了 我们在西班牙见”\N{\r原文字幕}He said, "Swell, I'll meet you on my way to Spain."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.05,0:34:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他去为忠诚派打仗？\N{\r原文字幕}He went to fight for the Loyalists?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.34,0:34:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他加入国际旅 我只好耐心等\N{\r原文字幕}And then he went to the brigades and I waited,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.59,0:34:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后…\N{\r原文字幕}and...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.26,0:34:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乔一从战壕探出头来就被射死\N{\r原文字幕}Joe got himself killed first time he popped his head outta the trench.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.94,0:34:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,意识形态害乔白白牺牲\N{\r原文字幕}Ideology got Joe killed.For nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.40,0:34:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是为西班牙共和国牺牲\N{\r原文字幕}Spanish Republic isn't nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.81,0:34:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我丈夫付出我们的未来\N{\r原文字幕}My husband offered both our futures to stop one fascist bullet
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.48,0:34:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却只阻止了一颗法西斯子弹\N{\r原文字幕}from embedding itself in a mudbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.99,0:34:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那绝对是白白牺牲\N{\r原文字幕}That's the definition of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.41,0:34:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那未免太消极了\N{\r原文字幕}Seems a little reductive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.66,0:34:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是务实\N{\r原文字幕}Pragmatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.37,0:34:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来到这里\N{\r原文字幕}Now here I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.33,0:34:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道这算什么\N{\r原文字幕}Wherever the hell this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.26,0:34:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不希望你从别人口中得知\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't want you to hear it from anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.51,0:35:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少你这次没送我花\N{\r原文字幕}Least you didn't bring me flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.02,0:35:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道我不是你要的\N{\r原文字幕}We both know I'm not what you want, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.65,0:35:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 但我们不会再见面了\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, but it's a door closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.44,0:35:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.49,0:35:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说不是这样\N{\r原文字幕}Not as far as I'm concerned, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.99,0:35:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把她的肚子搞大 有够快\N{\r原文字幕}You knocked her up.Fast work.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.41,0:35:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是个厉害角色\N{\r原文字幕}Can't keep a good man down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.12,0:35:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她才是\N{\r原文字幕}I meant her.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.25,0:35:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她很清楚自己要什么\N{\r原文字幕}She knew what she wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.00,0:35:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她丈夫呢？\N{\r原文字幕}What about the husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.46,0:35:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们谈过了…\N{\r原文字幕}We talked.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.96,0:35:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会离婚\N{\r原文字幕}They're getting a divorce
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.92,0:35:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以趁她肚子隆起前结婚\N{\r原文字幕}so we can get married before she starts showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.55,0:35:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想得真周到\N{\r原文字幕}How civilized.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.01,0:35:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这个傻瓜\N{\r原文字幕}You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.31,0:35:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是你的圈子\N{\r原文字幕}This is your community.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.77,0:35:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为你这金童不必守规矩？\N{\r原文字幕}You think the rules don't apply to the golden boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.06,0:35:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有非凡成就就够了\N{\r原文字幕}Brilliance makes up for a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.40,0:35:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别得罪这世上唯一了解你研究的人\N{\r原文字幕}Don't alienate the only people in the world that understand what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.74,0:36:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一天你会需要他们\N{\r原文字幕}One day you might need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.03,0:36:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,建筑师、工程师、化学家、技工联盟\N{\r原文字幕}The Federation of Architects, Engineers, Chemists and Technicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.17,0:36:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨 你的月薪多少？\N{\r原文字幕}Lomanitz, what do you get paid a month?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.42,0:36:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是重点 劳伦斯\N{\r原文字幕}-That's not the point, Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.59,0:36:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们跟农工和码头工人有何共通点？\N{\r原文字幕}What do any of you have in common with farm laborers and dock workers?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.51,0:36:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多共通点\N{\r原文字幕}Plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.97,0:36:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都出去 马上！\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody out.Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.52,0:36:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你留下来\N{\r原文字幕}Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.82,0:36:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在做什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.57,0:36:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是个工会\N{\r原文字幕}It's a trade union.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.20,0:36:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全都是共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}Filled with communists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.61,0:36:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又没入党\N{\r原文字幕}So? I haven't joined the Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.41,0:36:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会因为这种事不让你加入计划\N{\r原文字幕}They won't let me bring you onto the project because of this shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.16,0:36:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么计划都不会告诉你\N{\r原文字幕}They won't even let me tell you what the project is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.00,0:36:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道这是什么计划\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, I know what the project is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.37,0:36:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.38,0:36:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱因斯坦和西拉德寄信给罗斯福\N{\r原文字幕}We've all heard about Einstein and Szilard's letter to Roosevelt
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.04,0:36:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警告他德国人能制造原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}warning him the Germans could make a bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.63,0:37:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道纳粹有一颗原子弹代表什么\N{\r原文字幕}and I know what it means for the Nazis to have a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.13,0:37:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就不知道？\N{\r原文字幕}And I don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.47,0:37:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们送进集中营的不是你的同胞\N{\r原文字幕}It's not your people they're herding into camps.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.72,0:37:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我的同胞\N{\r原文字幕}It's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.60,0:37:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为我跟他们说你的政治立场\N{\r原文字幕}You think that I tell them about your politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.02,0:37:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下次你开完会回家\N{\r原文字幕}The next time you're coming home from a meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.81,0:37:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何不看看你的照后镜？\N{\r原文字幕}why don't you take a look in the rearview mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.02,0:37:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听听电话线的声音 别这么天真\N{\r原文字幕}Listen to the sounds on your phone line and stop being so goddamn naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.40,0:37:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们为何在乎我做什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Why would they care what I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.78,0:37:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是自以为很重要 是真的很重要\N{\r原文字幕}Because you're not just self-important, you're actually important.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.29,0:37:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.37,0:37:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好 我懂了\N{\r原文字幕}I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.87,0:37:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你可以再…\N{\r原文字幕}If you could just be a little more--
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.71,0:37:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,务实一点\N{\r原文字幕}Pragmatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.92,0:37:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会跟洛马尼茨和其他人说…\N{\r原文字幕}I'll talk to Lomanitz, I'll talk to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.63,0:37:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不必担心 不会有事\N{\r原文字幕}You don't have to worry.It's done,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.80,0:37:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯\N{\r原文字幕}Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.85,0:37:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就欢迎加入战争\N{\r原文字幕}Then welcome to the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.93,0:37:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我填完安全调查问卷后被告知\N{\r原文字幕}I filled out my first security questionnaire
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.39,0:37:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和左翼团体的关系不会是…\N{\r原文字幕}and was informed that my involvement with left-wing groups
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.61,0:38:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参与原子能计划的障碍\N{\r原文字幕}would not prove a bar to my working on the atomic program.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.61,0:38:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他亲共的立场\N{\r原文字幕}Why were his communist associations
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.28,0:38:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在战时为何不构成国安风险？\N{\r原文字幕}not seen as a security risk during the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.32,0:38:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参议员 我不可能知道…\N{\r原文字幕}Senator, I can't possibly answer for security clearance
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.12,0:38:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们认识前他为何获得安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}granted years before I ever met the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.45,0:38:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 之后呢？\N{\r原文字幕}Fine.What about after?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.54,0:38:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士在战后\N{\r原文字幕}After the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.71,0:38:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为全世界最受尊敬的科学家\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer was the most respected scientific voice in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.38,0:38:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才会请他担任院长\N{\r原文字幕}That's why I asked him to run the Institute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.46,0:38:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且担任原子能委员会的顾问\N{\r原文字幕}That's why he advised the Atomic Energy Commission.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.51,0:38:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就这么简单\N{\r原文字幕}Simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.09,0:38:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在指控我什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What are they accusing me of?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.26,0:38:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1947年到1954年发生了什么事\N{\r原文字幕}I think they just wanna know what happened between 1947 and 1954
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.85,0:38:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,改变你对于给予他安全许可的看法\N{\r原文字幕}to change your mind on Oppenheimer's security clearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.64,0:38:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并没有 我当时是原子能委员会主席\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't. I was chair of the AEC,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.44,0:38:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我没对罗伯特提出指控\N{\r原文字幕}but it wasn't me that brought the charges against Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.98,0:38:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是谁提出的？\N{\r原文字幕}Who did?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.36,0:38:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国会联席委员会的前任职员\N{\r原文字幕}Some former staff member of the Joint Congressional Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.28,0:38:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个叫波登的狂热反共分子\N{\r原文字幕}He was a rabid anti-communist named Borden.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.45,0:38:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他写信要求联邦调查局采取行动\N{\r原文字幕}He wrote to the FBI demanding they take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.74,0:38:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,何不直接找原子能委员会？\N{\r原文字幕}The FBI? Why not go to the AEC direct?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.33,0:38:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想要借刀杀人\N{\r原文字幕}Why get caught holding the knife yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.08,0:38:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波登跟奥本海默有什么仇？\N{\r原文字幕}What did Borden have against Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.37,0:38:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是麦卡锡时代\N{\r原文字幕}This was the McCarthy Era.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.42,0:39:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要跟共产党沾上边就会丢掉饭碗\N{\r原文字幕}People hounded out of jobs for any hint of red.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.30,0:39:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他又看过奥本海默的安全档案\N{\r原文字幕}And then, reading Oppenheimer's security file,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.92,0:39:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道他弟弟、弟媳、未婚妻\N{\r原文字幕}his communist brother, sister-in-law, fiancée,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.18,0:39:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好友和妻子都是共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}best friend, wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.34,0:39:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那还是在薛瓦利埃事件之前\N{\r原文字幕}That's before we even get to the Chevalier incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.85,0:39:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波登怎么会有奥本海默的安全档案？\N{\r原文字幕}But how would Borden have access to Oppenheimer's security file?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.27,0:39:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为有人交给他\N{\r原文字幕}Because somebody gave it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.27,0:39:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人想让罗伯特噤声\N{\r原文字幕}Somebody who wanted Robert silenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.15,0:39:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁？  -谁知道？\N{\r原文字幕}Who? Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.82,0:39:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特得罪了很多华府权贵\N{\r原文字幕}Robert didn't take care not to upset the power brokers in Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.49,0:39:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他对原子能的意见成为主流\N{\r原文字幕}His opinions on the atom became definitive
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.41,0:39:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我们这些凡夫俗子也没有耐心\N{\r原文字幕}and he wasn't always patient with us mere mortals.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.66,0:39:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我接任后受到严厉的批评\N{\r原文字幕}I came in for plenty of harsh treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.08,0:39:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一次原子能委员会投票表决\N{\r原文字幕}There was an AEC vote
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.38,0:39:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否该向挪威出口同位素\N{\r原文字幕}on the export of isotopes to Norway,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.75,0:39:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们把罗伯特找来让我出糗\N{\r原文字幕}and they drafted in Robert to make me look like a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.63,0:39:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士 史特劳斯少将表示…\N{\r原文字幕}But, Dr.Oppenheimer, we've already heard from Admiral Strauss
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.14,0:39:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些同位素可能用来帮助敌人制造核武\N{\r原文字幕}that these isotopes could be useful to our enemies in the production of atomic weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.47,0:40:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位 铁铲能用来制造核武 是真的\N{\r原文字幕}Congressmen, you could use a shovel in making atomic weapons. In fact, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.94,0:40:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一瓶啤酒都能用来制造核武 也是真的\N{\r原文字幕}You could use a bottle of beer in making atomic weapons. In fact, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.90,0:40:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同位素不像电子零件那么有用\N{\r原文字幕}I say isotopes are less useful than electronic components,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.78,0:40:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是比三明治更有用\N{\r原文字幕}but more useful than a sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.62,0:40:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天才不一定是智者\N{\r原文字幕}Genius is no guarantee of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.29,0:40:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个人曾经历许多怎会如此盲目？\N{\r原文字幕}How could this man who saw so much be so blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.59,0:40:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂？\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.76,0:40:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂？\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.31,0:40:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂…\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.73,0:40:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那项计划 我加入了\N{\r原文字幕}the project-- I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.73,0:40:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我加入了\N{\r原文字幕}I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.73,0:40:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们庆祝吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.07,0:40:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不去哄他吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Shouldn't you go to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.37,0:41:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经哄了他一整天\N{\r原文字幕}I have been going to him all fucking day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.40,0:41:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我来抱\N{\r原文字幕}Come here, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.31,0:41:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道该如何启齿\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know how to say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.40,0:41:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我惭愧到不敢说\N{\r原文字幕}I-I'm ashamed to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.28,0:41:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管说\N{\r原文字幕}Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.15,0:41:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你们照顾彼得\N{\r原文字幕}Take Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.28,0:41:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题-只是暂时的\N{\r原文字幕}-Sure. No, for a while, Hoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.91,0:41:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暂时的\N{\r原文字幕}A while.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.16,0:41:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂知道你来这里吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Does Kitty know you're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.12,0:41:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她当然知道\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, of course she knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.33,0:41:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她当然知道\N{\r原文字幕}Of course she knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.50,0:41:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很可恶 又自私又可恶\N{\r原文字幕}We're awful people.Selfish, awful people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.47,0:41:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,忘了我的要求\N{\r原文字幕}Forget I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.47,0:41:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又自私又可恶的人\N{\r原文字幕}Selfish, awful people,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.59,0:41:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会知道自己又自私又可恶\N{\r原文字幕}they don't know they're selfish and awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.64,0:42:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下来\N{\r原文字幕}Sit, sit, sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.56,0:42:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 你看到超越这世界的奥秘\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, you see beyond the world we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.23,0:42:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须为此付出代价\N{\r原文字幕}There is a price to be paid for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.90,0:42:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们当然会帮助你\N{\r原文字幕}Of course we'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.45,0:42:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切都在改变 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Everything's changing, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.87,0:42:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有了小孩一定会改变…\N{\r原文字幕}Having a child was always going to change--
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.58,0:42:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界正在改变 转向一个全新方向\N{\r原文字幕}No, the world, it's pivoting in some new direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.21,0:42:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重组新秩序\N{\r原文字幕}It's reforming.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.88,0:42:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是属于你的时刻\N{\r原文字幕}This is your moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.84,0:42:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们成立一个小组研究…\N{\r原文字幕}We're putting together a group to study feasibili--
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.55,0:42:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别找其他人 你要靠自己\N{\r原文字幕}"We" shouldn't be doing anything.You should.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.06,0:42:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯成不了大事\N{\r原文字幕}Lawrence won't get this done.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.31,0:42:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尔曼或拉比也不行 只有你行\N{\r原文字幕}Or Tolman, or Rabi.You will.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.70,0:42:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿军服的是什么人？\N{\r原文字幕}Who are the uniforms?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.16,0:43:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你知道\N{\r原文字幕}I thought you might know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.83,0:43:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.37,0:43:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是格罗夫斯上校 这是尼柯斯中校\N{\r原文字幕}I'm Colonel Groves. This is Lieutenant Colonel Nichols.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.92,0:43:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿去干洗\N{\r原文字幕}Have that dry cleaned.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.05,0:43:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是这么对待一名中校\N{\r原文字幕}Well, if that's how you treat Lieutenant Colonel,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.22,0:43:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道你会怎么对待谦卑的物理学家\N{\r原文字幕}I'd hate to see how you treat a humble physicist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.97,0:43:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没见过谦卑的物理学家\N{\r原文字幕}If I ever meet one, I'll let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.60,0:43:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好狠啊  -世界各地都有战事\N{\r原文字幕}Ouch. Theaters of combat all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.10,0:43:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我却必须留在华府  -为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}but I have to stay in Washington. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.44,0:43:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我负责建造五角大厦\N{\r原文字幕}-I built the Pentagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.73,0:43:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高层很满意 要我接管曼哈顿工程区\N{\r原文字幕}The brass likes it so much they made me take over the Manhattan Engineer District.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.82,0:43:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Which is?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.82,0:43:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别装蒜 你知道那是什么\N{\r原文字幕}Don't be a smart ass. You know damn well what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.99,0:43:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和全国一半的物理系都知道\N{\r原文字幕}You and half of every physics department across the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.53,0:43:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是第一个问题\N{\r原文字幕}That's problem number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.66,0:43:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为第一个问题是取得足够的铀矿\N{\r原文字幕}I thought problem number one would be securing enough uranium ore.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.87,0:43:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我上任那天就买了1千2百吨\N{\r原文字幕}1,200 tons bought the day I took charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.67,0:43:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,运到提炼厂了？\N{\r原文字幕}-Processing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.63,0:43:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经在田纳西州橡树岭破土动工\N{\r原文字幕}Just broke ground at Oak Ridge, Tennessee.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.88,0:43:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在找这项计划的负责人\N{\r原文字幕}Now I'm looking for a project director.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.47,0:44:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人提起我的名字？\N{\r原文字幕}And my name came up?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.01,0:44:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\r原文字幕}Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.80,0:44:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然你把量子物理学引进美国\N{\r原文字幕}Even though you brought quantum physics to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.18,0:44:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这让我很好奇\N{\r原文字幕}Which made me curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.97,0:44:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你发现了什么？\N{\r原文字幕}-What've you found out?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.48,0:44:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你吊儿郎当、风流成性\N{\r原文字幕}You're a dilettante, a womanizer,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.98,0:44:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能是共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}a suspected communist--
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.31,0:44:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是新政民主党员\N{\r原文字幕}I'm a New Deal Democrat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.69,0:44:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说可能是\N{\r原文字幕}I said "suspected."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.40,0:44:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不安于室、浮夸爱现\N{\r原文字幕}Unstable, theatrical,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.74,0:44:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狂妄自大、神经兮兮…\N{\r原文字幕}egotistical, neurotic--
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.57,0:44:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有好话？“他很杰出 但…”\N{\r原文字幕}Nothing good, no? Not even, "He's brilliant, but--"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.62,0:44:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这圈子每个人都很杰出 没好话\N{\r原文字幕}Well, brilliance is taken for granted in your circle, so no.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.04,0:44:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一说过你好话的是理查德托尔曼\N{\r原文字幕}No, the only person who had anything good to say was Richard Tolman.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.75,0:44:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尔曼认为你很有原则\N{\r原文字幕}Tolman thinks you have integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.67,0:44:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我看他比较了解科学却不会看人\N{\r原文字幕}but he also strikes me as a guy who knows more about science than people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.59,0:44:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不相信任何人却还是来找我\N{\r原文字幕}Yet here you are. You don't take much on trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.34,0:44:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不相信任何事情\N{\r原文字幕}I don't take anything on trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.89,0:44:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么没得到诺贝尔奖？\N{\r原文字幕}Why don't you have a Nobel prize?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.52,0:44:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么不是将军？\N{\r原文字幕}Why aren't you a general?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.60,0:44:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这件事会让我当上将军\N{\r原文字幕}-They're making me one for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.98,0:44:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我也会一样幸运\N{\r原文字幕}Perhaps I'll have the same luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.23,0:44:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为发明原子弹得到诺贝尔奖？\N{\r原文字幕}A Nobel prize for making a bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.02,0:44:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诺贝尔发明了炸药\N{\r原文字幕}Alfred Nobel invented dynamite.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.69,0:45:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会怎么进行？\N{\r原文字幕}So how would you proceed?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.90,0:45:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说的是利用理论\N{\r原文字幕}You're talking about turning theory
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.61,0:45:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,制造一个实用的武器系统\N{\r原文字幕}into a practical weapons system
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.74,0:45:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还要抢先纳粹一步\N{\r原文字幕}faster than the Nazis.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.08,0:45:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们领先我们整整12个月\N{\r原文字幕}Who have a 12-month head start.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.79,0:45:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,18个月-你怎么可能知道？\N{\r原文字幕}Eighteen.  -How could you possibly know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.16,0:45:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的快中子研究耗时6个月\N{\r原文字幕}Our fast neutron research took six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.42,0:45:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们任命的负责人会立刻成功做到\N{\r原文字幕}The man they've undoubtedly put in charge will have made that leap instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.34,0:45:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的负责人会是谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who do you think they put in charge?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.59,0:45:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,维尔纳海森堡\N{\r原文字幕}-Werner Heisenberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.75,0:45:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他对原子结构的理解无人能及\N{\r原文字幕}He has the most intuitive understanding of atomic structure I have ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.13,0:45:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你了解他的研究？\N{\r原文字幕}You know his work?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.09,0:45:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他、瓦尔特博特、冯魏茨泽克、第伯纳\N{\r原文字幕}-I know him. Just like I know Walther Bothe, Von Weizsäcker, Diebner.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.18,0:45:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场比赛德国人赢定了\N{\r原文字幕}In a straight race, the Germans win.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.56,0:45:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只有一个希望\N{\r原文字幕}We've got one hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.60,0:45:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Which is?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.77,0:45:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反犹太主义\N{\r原文字幕}Anti-Semitism.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.73,0:45:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.73,0:45:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希特勒称量子物理学为“犹太科学”\N{\r原文字幕}Hitler called quantum physics "Jewish science."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.48,0:45:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当着爱因斯坦的面说\N{\r原文字幕}Said it right to Einstein's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.90,0:45:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一的希望是希特勒被仇恨蒙蔽\N{\r原文字幕}Our one hope is that Hitler is so, so blinded by hate
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.74,0:45:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剥夺海森堡的资源 这需要大量资源\N{\r原文字幕}that he's denied Heisenberg proper resources, because it'll take vast resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.37,0:45:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全国最优秀的科学家共同努力\N{\r原文字幕}Our nation's best scientists, working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.99,0:45:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在他们分散各地\N{\r原文字幕}Right now, they're scattered.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.33,0:45:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样才能划分权限\N{\r原文字幕}Which gives us compartmentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.21,0:45:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有人都得看到全局才能有效工作\N{\r原文字幕}All minds have to see the whole task to contribute efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.17,0:45:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安全漏洞也许会害我们输掉比赛\N{\r原文字幕}Poor security may cost us the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.46,0:46:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,效率低落绝对会输\N{\r原文字幕}Inefficiency will.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.55,0:46:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正德国人知道的比我们多\N{\r原文字幕}The Germans know more than us anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.42,0:46:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国人没有\N{\r原文字幕}The Russians don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.34,0:46:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提醒我 我们在和谁作战？\N{\r原文字幕}Remind me, who are we at war with?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.80,0:46:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你曾有左倾的立场 最好别落人口舌\N{\r原文字幕}Somebody with your past doesn't wanna be seen downplaying
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.64,0:46:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说你低估防范共产党盟友的重要性\N{\r原文字幕}the importance of security from our communist allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.15,0:46:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我了解 但不要\N{\r原文字幕}Point taken.But, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.65,0:46:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能对我说“不”\N{\r原文字幕}You don't get to say "no" to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.27,0:46:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你错了 我的职责就是对你说“不”\N{\r原文字幕}It's my job to say "no" to you when you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.07,0:46:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想要这份工作？\N{\r原文字幕}So you have the job now?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.36,0:46:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在考虑\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, I'm considering it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.45,0:46:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我终于知道你有多难搞了\N{\r原文字幕}I'm starting to see where you got your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.12,0:46:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我最喜欢的说法是\N{\r原文字幕}My favorite response?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.46,0:46:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“奥本海默连小吃摊都管不好”\N{\r原文字幕}"Oppenheimer couldn't run a hamburger stand."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.67,0:46:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是管不好\N{\r原文字幕}I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.71,0:46:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我能掌管曼哈顿计划\N{\r原文字幕}But I can run the Manhattan Project.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.05,0:46:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有办法平均分配工作\N{\r原文字幕}There's a way to balance these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.72,0:46:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯负责伯克利的放射实验室\N{\r原文字幕}Keep the Rad Lab here at Berkeley under Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.22,0:46:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西拉德负责芝加哥的冶金实验室\N{\r原文字幕}Met Lab in Chicago under Szilard.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.35,0:46:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在哪里大量提炼铀矿？田纳西州\N{\r原文字幕}Large scale refining, where did you say? Tennessee.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.85,0:46:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有汉福德  -汉福德\N{\r原文字幕}And Hanford.And Hanford.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.48,0:47:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国所有的工业实力和科学创新\N{\r原文字幕}All America's industrial might and scientific innovation,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.27,0:47:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全都通过铁路连结\N{\r原文字幕}connected by rail.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.28,0:47:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,专注于一个目标\N{\r原文字幕}Focused on one goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.74,0:47:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各地同时进行的研究汇聚在这里\N{\r原文字幕}One point in space and time.And it comes together here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.66,0:47:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一间位置偏僻的秘密实验室\N{\r原文字幕}A secret laboratory. In the middle of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.03,0:47:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既安全又自给自足…\N{\r原文字幕}secure, self-sufficient,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.28,0:47:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,设备和住宿全都有\N{\r原文字幕}equipment, housing, the works.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.87,0:47:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁都不能离开 直到完成为止\N{\r原文字幕}Keep everyone there until it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.33,0:47:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会需要学校、商店和教堂\N{\r原文字幕}I'll need the schools, stores, a church.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.25,0:47:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.29,0:47:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不让科学家携家带眷\N{\r原文字幕}If we don't let scientists bring their families,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.04,0:47:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就找不到最优秀的人才\N{\r原文字幕}we'll never get the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.25,0:47:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要保密就必须尽快建造一个城镇\N{\r原文字幕}You want security, build a town, build it fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.26,0:47:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在哪里？\N{\r原文字幕}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.26,0:47:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎来到洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}Welcome to Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.30,0:47:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须征用一所男校\N{\r原文字幕}Now, there's a boys' school we'll have to commandeer
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.60,0:47:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也是印第安人的墓地\N{\r原文字幕}and the local Indians come up here for burial rites.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.39,0:47:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除此之外 方圆64公里什么都没有\N{\r原文字幕}But, apart from that, nothing. Forty miles.Any direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.77,0:47:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以找到完美的地点\N{\r原文字幕}Enough to find the perfect spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.86,0:47:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用来做什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.07,0:47:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,缔造成功\N{\r原文字幕}-Success.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.61,0:47:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽快建造一个城镇\N{\r原文字幕}Build him a town.Fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.45,0:47:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们去招募科学家吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's go recruit some scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.79,0:47:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为什么要离开家人？\N{\r原文字幕}Why would I leave my family?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.20,0:47:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说过你能携家带眷\N{\r原文字幕}I told you, you can bring your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.04,0:48:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是士兵 奥比\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not a soldier, Oppie.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.46,0:48:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,士兵？他是少将 我不缺士兵\N{\r原文字幕}A soldier? He's a general. I've got all the soldier I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.75,0:48:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能告诉他们什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What can I tell them?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.51,0:48:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海森堡、第伯纳、博特和波耳\N{\r原文字幕}Heisenberg, Diebner, Bothe, Bohr.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.67,0:48:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们有什么共通点？\N{\r原文字幕}What do these men have in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.93,0:48:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子理论最伟大的科学家\N{\r原文字幕}The greatest minds on atomic theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.72,0:48:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 还有呢？\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, and? Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.89,0:48:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要多少都有\N{\r原文字幕}As much as you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.47,0:48:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再啰嗦我就痛扁你\N{\r原文字幕}until you feel my boot on your balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.31,0:48:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们比任何人都更了解同位素和炸药\N{\r原文字幕}You know isotopes and you know explosives, better than anyone in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.94,0:48:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你不能说你在做什么？\N{\r原文字幕}But you can't tell us what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.69,0:48:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道  -他们为纳粹工作\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know.The Nazis have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.82,0:48:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波耳在哥本哈根  -已被纳粹占领\N{\r原文字幕}Niels Bohr's in Copenhagen.Under Nazi occupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.07,0:48:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普林斯顿没有报纸吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did they stop printing newspapers in Princeton?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.95,0:48:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要去鸟不生蛋的地方\N{\r原文字幕}Why would we go to the middle of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.45,0:48:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道要待多长的时间？\N{\r原文字幕}for who knows how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.79,0:48:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一两年 或是三年\N{\r原文字幕}A year or two.Or three.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.25,0:48:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少将 请你离开一下\N{\r原文字幕}General, could you give us a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.38,0:48:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要抢先纳粹一步释放一股巨大力量\N{\r原文字幕}It's about unleashing the strong force before the Nazis do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.72,0:48:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.05,0:48:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波耳不会为纳粹工作  -绝对不会\N{\r原文字幕}Niels won't work for the Nazis.No, never.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.39,0:49:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他在纳粹手上 所以我需要你\N{\r原文字幕}But while they have him, we don't. That's why I need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.02,0:49:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么认为我会答应？\N{\r原文字幕}Why would you think I'd do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.02,0:49:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Why? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.11,0:49:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这将是人类史上\N{\r原文字幕}How about because this is the most important fucking thing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.90,0:49:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最重要的发明\N{\r原文字幕}to ever happen in the history of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.32,0:49:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么样？\N{\r原文字幕}How about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.32,0:49:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死\N{\r原文字幕}Fuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.12,0:49:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不会让我加入计划\N{\r原文字幕}They are not gonna let me onto this project.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.25,0:49:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没通过安全查核在战后会毁了我的职涯\N{\r原文字幕}And failing a security check is not gonna be good for a career, even after the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.92,0:49:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是共产党同路人 又怎样？\N{\r原文字幕}So you're a fellow traveler.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.58,0:49:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是国家紧急状态\N{\r原文字幕}So what? This is a national emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.34,0:49:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也有秘密 但他们让我负责\N{\r原文字幕}I've got some skeletons, they put me in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.92,0:49:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们需要我们\N{\r原文字幕}They need us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.72,0:49:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到他们不需要\N{\r原文字幕}Until they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.18,0:49:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能不能把波耳弄出丹麦？\N{\r原文字幕}Is there any chance of getting Bohr out of Denmark?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.27,0:49:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能 我问过英国人\N{\r原文字幕}Nah, no dice. I checked with the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.64,0:49:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盟军展开反攻之前\N{\r原文字幕}Until we get Allied boots back onto the continent,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.73,0:49:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一点办法都没有\N{\r原文字幕}there's just no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.73,0:49:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有那么重要？\N{\r原文字幕}Is he that important?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.86,0:49:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有多少人证明过爱因斯坦是错的？\N{\r原文字幕}How many people do you know who've proved Einstein wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.36,0:49:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐飞机真的会比较快\N{\r原文字幕}You know, it really would be quicker to take a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.28,0:49:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行 太危险了\N{\r原文字幕}No, plane's too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.24,0:49:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国家需要我们\N{\r原文字幕}Country needs us.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.04,0:50:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈佛的家伙说建筑物装不下回旋加速器\N{\r原文字幕}The Harvard guys, they say the building's too small for the cyclotron.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.88,0:50:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们和建筑师开会\N{\r原文字幕}Get them together with the architects.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.97,0:50:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这地方几时开始运作？\N{\r原文字幕}When's this place supposed to open?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.85,0:50:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两个月后\N{\r原文字幕}Two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.06,0:50:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你很会临机应变 但这件事…\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, you're the great improviser, but this...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.35,0:50:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,光靠你自己的头脑做不到\N{\r原文字幕}you can't do in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.15,0:50:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四组\N{\r原文字幕}Four divisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.65,0:50:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实验、理论、冶金、军械\N{\r原文字幕}Experimental, Theoretical, Metallurgical, Ordnance.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.49,0:50:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁负责理论组？\N{\r原文字幕}Who's running Theoretical?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.53,0:50:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我\N{\r原文字幕}I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.70,0:50:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就怕会是这样\N{\r原文字幕}That's what I was afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.32,0:50:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你分身乏术\N{\r原文字幕}You're spread too thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.91,0:50:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你负责理论组\N{\r原文字幕}So you take Theoretical.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.41,0:50:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会来这里 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not coming here, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.17,0:50:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.89,0:51:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你投放的炸弹会炸死好人和坏人\N{\r原文字幕}You drop a bomb, and it falls on the just and the unjust.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.02,0:51:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不希望累积三世纪的物理学…\N{\r原文字幕}I don't wish the culmination of three centuries of physics
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.73,0:51:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为大规模毁灭性武器\N{\r原文字幕}to be a weapon of mass destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.41,0:51:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伊西\N{\r原文字幕}Izzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.49,0:51:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道人类能否被信任使用这种武器\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know if we can be trusted with such a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.42,0:51:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我知道纳粹不能使用\N{\r原文字幕}But I know the Nazis can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.34,0:51:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们别无选择\N{\r原文字幕}We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.26,0:51:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么…\N{\r原文字幕}Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.10,0:51:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要做的第二件事就是\N{\r原文字幕}the second thing you'll have to do is appoint Hans Bethe
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.52,0:51:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任命汉斯贝特负责理论组\N{\r原文字幕}to run the theoretical division.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.98,0:51:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等 第一件事是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Wait, what was the first?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.11,0:51:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,脱掉那套可笑的军服\N{\r原文字幕}Take off that ridiculous uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.48,0:51:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是科学家\N{\r原文字幕}You're a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.69,0:51:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格罗夫斯坚持要我们从军\N{\r原文字幕}Groves is insisting we join.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.65,0:51:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫格罗夫斯去吃屎吧\N{\r原文字幕}Tell Groves to go shit in his hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.86,0:52:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们需要我们 做自己吧\N{\r原文字幕}They need us for who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.62,0:52:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做更好的自己\N{\r原文字幕}So be yourself.Only better.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.78,0:52:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是唯一的钥匙\N{\r原文字幕}This is the only key.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.33,0:52:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒已经来了\N{\r原文字幕}And Teller's already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.33,0:52:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要让他进来吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Shall I just show him in?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.62,0:52:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 先等其他人\N{\r原文字幕}No, let's wait for the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.34,0:53:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们开始吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.05,0:53:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 爱德华\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Edward.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.59,0:53:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.59,0:53:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们先在这里工作 直到T组完工\N{\r原文字幕}Gentlemen, so, we will work here until the T-section at Los Alamos is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.02,0:53:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华 请你\N{\r原文字幕}Edward, can I please--
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.97,0:53:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这比较重要\N{\r原文字幕}It is more important.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.35,0:53:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在计算连锁反应时\N{\r原文字幕}When I calculated the chain reaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.44,0:53:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现一个令人不安的可能性\N{\r原文字幕}I found a rather troubling possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.48,0:53:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是吧\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.48,0:53:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不可能是对的\N{\r原文字幕}This can't be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.03,0:53:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我看你是怎么算出来的\N{\r原文字幕}Show me how you did your calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.65,0:53:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.41,0:53:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是指数函数  -不对\N{\r原文字幕}It's exponential.No.No, no, no.No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.50,0:53:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是幻想\N{\r原文字幕}This is fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.63,0:53:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒的计算不可能是对的\N{\r原文字幕}Teller's calculations can't be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.25,0:53:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你再计算一次 我要去普林斯顿\N{\r原文字幕}Do them yourself while I go to Princeton.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.59,0:53:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？  -跟爱因斯坦谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}What for? To talk to Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.63,0:53:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们俩意见完全不同\N{\r原文字幕}There's not much common ground between you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.01,0:53:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以才要征求他的意见\N{\r原文字幕}That's why I should get his view.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.48,0:53:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Albert.  -Mmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.44,0:53:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Ah, Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.44,0:53:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你见过哥德尔博士吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Well, have you met Dr.Gödel?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.90,0:54:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都在这里散步\N{\r原文字幕}We walk here most days.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.90,0:54:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,树木是最启发人心的结构\N{\r原文字幕}Trees are the most inspiring structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.28,0:54:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔伯特 能聊聊吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Albert, might I have a word?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.62,0:54:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然 失陪了 库尔特\N{\r原文字幕}Of course.Excuse me, Kurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.45,0:54:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些日子库尔特拒绝进食\N{\r原文字幕}You know, some days, Kurt refuses to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.41,0:54:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就连在普林斯顿也一样\N{\r原文字幕}Even in Princeton.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.62,0:54:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他认为纳粹能在他的食物中下毒\N{\r原文字幕}He's convinced that the Nazis can poison his food.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.35,0:54:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是谁算出来的？\N{\r原文字幕}Whose--Whose work is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.14,0:54:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒\N{\r原文字幕}Teller's.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.44,0:54:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为这代表什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What do you take it to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.90,0:54:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中子撞击原子核\N{\r原文字幕}Neutrons smash into nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.77,0:54:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,释放中子撞击其它原子核\N{\r原文字幕}releasing neutrons to smash into other nuclei.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.94,0:54:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到达临界点就会产生巨大爆炸\N{\r原文字幕}Criticality, a point of no return, massive explosive force.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.74,0:54:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这时候连锁反应不会停止\N{\r原文字幕}But this time, the chain reaction doesn't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.08,0:54:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是会点燃大气层\N{\r原文字幕}It would ignite the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.33,0:54:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我们引爆原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}When we detonate an atomic device,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.21,0:54:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能会引发连锁反应\N{\r原文字幕}we might start a chain reaction that...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.46,0:55:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毁灭全世界\N{\r原文字幕}destroys the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.88,0:55:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了这个地步？\N{\r原文字幕}So here we are, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.71,0:55:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迷失在你的量子机率世界中…\N{\r原文字幕}Lost in your quantum world of probabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.09,0:55:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要一个确定性\N{\r原文字幕}and needing certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.43,0:55:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能亲自计算吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Can you run the calculations yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.39,0:55:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你我唯一的共通点就是厌恶数学\N{\r原文字幕}About the only thing you and I have in common is a disdain for mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.85,0:55:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁在伯克利研究这个？\N{\r原文字幕}Who's working on this in Berkeley?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.19,0:55:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉斯·贝特\N{\r原文字幕}Hans Bethe.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.19,0:55:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会查出真相\N{\r原文字幕}Well, he'll get to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.03,0:55:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是毁天灭地的真相呢？\N{\r原文字幕}And if the truth is catastrophic?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.86,0:55:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就停下来\N{\r原文字幕}Then you stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.28,0:55:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你的发现和纳粹分享\N{\r原文字幕}And you share your findings with the Nazis.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.04,0:55:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确保任何一方都不会毁灭世界\N{\r原文字幕}So neither side destroys the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.33,0:55:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.79,0:55:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是你的责任 不是我的\N{\r原文字幕}This is yours, not mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.89,0:56:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒错了 他错了\N{\r原文字幕}Teller's wrong. He's wrong.Shh, shh, shh...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.41,0:56:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你了解泰勒的假设 就知道真实状况\N{\r原文字幕}When you know Teller's critical assumptions, the real picture emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.28,0:56:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Bottom line?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.33,0:56:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,核反应失控的机率几乎是零\N{\r原文字幕}The chances of an uncontrolled nuclear reaction are near zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.33,0:56:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎是零\N{\r原文字幕}Near zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.08,0:56:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比 这是好消息\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie, this is good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.75,0:56:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再算一次\N{\r原文字幕}Can you run them again?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.76,0:56:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会得到同样的答案\N{\r原文字幕}No, you'll get the same answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.80,0:56:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的引爆这玩意之前…\N{\r原文字幕}Till they actually detonate one of these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.51,0:56:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是最好的保证\N{\r原文字幕}the best assurance you're going to get is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.97,0:56:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎是零\N{\r原文字幕}Near zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.43,0:56:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理论是有局限的\N{\r原文字幕}Theory will take you only so far.Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.89,0:56:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们好\N{\r原文字幕}Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.89,0:56:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好  -嗨\N{\r原文字幕}-Hello, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.94,0:56:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们好想他\N{\r原文字幕}We missed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.27,0:56:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想领养吗？  -她在开玩笑\N{\r原文字幕}You want to adopt? She's kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.61,0:56:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们走之前想见你\N{\r原文字幕}We wanted to see you before we left.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.86,0:56:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前往未知领域\N{\r原文字幕}For parts unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.53,0:56:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道我前几天遇到谁吗？\N{\r原文字幕}You know who I ran into the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.78,0:56:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾尔坦顿\N{\r原文字幕}Eltenton.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.74,0:56:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,壳牌石油的化学家？工会的家伙？\N{\r原文字幕}The chemist from Shell? The union guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.16,0:57:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 工会的家伙\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.The FAECT guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.17,0:57:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在抱怨美国处理战争的方法\N{\r原文字幕}He was moaning about how we're handling the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.30,0:57:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么说？\N{\r原文字幕}How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.88,0:57:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,缺乏和盟友的合作\N{\r原文字幕}Lack of cooperation with our allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.84,0:57:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政府没和俄国人分享任何研究成果\N{\r原文字幕}Apparently our government's not sharing any research with the Russians.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.05,0:57:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说多数的科学家都觉得这政策很蠢\N{\r原文字幕}Well, he said, "Most scientists think the policy is stupid."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.39,0:57:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗？  -是啊\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, yeah? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.77,0:57:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他提到有人若想绕过官方管道…\N{\r原文字幕}He mentioned that if anyone had anything they wanted to pass on,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.74,0:57:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传递任何情报 他都能帮忙\N{\r原文字幕}going around official channels, that he could help.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.00,0:57:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是叛国罪\N{\r原文字幕}That would be treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.42,0:57:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.59,0:57:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想让你知道\N{\r原文字幕}I just thought you should know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.80,0:57:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小淘气睡着了\N{\r原文字幕}The brat is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.97,0:57:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁尼呢？\N{\r原文字幕}Where are the martinis?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.56,0:58:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上来\N{\r原文字幕}Coming right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.14,0:58:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只聊到那里\N{\r原文字幕}The conversation ended there.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.81,0:58:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是老朋友 我不相信\N{\r原文字幕}Nothing in our long-standing friendship would have led me to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.98,0:58:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薛瓦利埃真的在搜集情报\N{\r原文字幕}that Chevalier was actually seeking information,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.15,0:58:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也很确定他不知道我在做什么\N{\r原文字幕}and I am certain that he had no idea of the work in which I was engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.41,0:58:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很早就知道应该立刻报告这件事\N{\r原文字幕}It has long been clear to me that I should have reported this incident at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.29,0:58:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默事件凸显了科学家\N{\r原文字幕}The Oppenheimer situation highlights the tension
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.79,0:58:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和国家安全机关之间的冲突\N{\r原文字幕}between scientists and the security apparatus.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.42,0:58:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了得知候选人\N{\r原文字幕}In hopes of learning how the nominee handled such issues
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.25,0:58:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在AEC任职时如何处理这问题\N{\r原文字幕}during his time at the AEC,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.01,0:58:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将请一位科学家出席作证\N{\r原文字幕}we'll have a scientist appearing before the committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.84,0:58:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要找谁来？\N{\r原文字幕}Who are they bringing in?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.22,0:58:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们没说\N{\r原文字幕}They haven't said.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.43,0:58:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生 我被提名为商务部部长\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Chairman, if I may, I'm nominated for commerce secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.43,0:58:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何要征求科学家的意见？\N{\r原文字幕}Why seek the opinion of scientists?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.10,0:58:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是内阁职位 少将\N{\r原文字幕}This is a cabinet post, Admiral.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.94,0:58:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会征求各方意见\N{\r原文字幕}We seek a wide range of opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.78,0:58:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道出席作证的科学家是谁\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I'd like to know the name of the scientist testifying,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.15,0:58:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也想进行交叉诘问\N{\r原文字幕}I'd like the chance to cross-examine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.20,0:58:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是法庭\N{\r原文字幕}This is not a court.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.24,0:59:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是走程序？\N{\r原文字幕}Formality, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.24,0:59:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1925年后没有内阁候选人\N{\r原文字幕}No presidential Cabinet nominee
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.70,0:59:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,未能得到确认任命\N{\r原文字幕}has failed to be confirmed since 1925.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.20,0:59:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只是游戏规则\N{\r原文字幕}This is just how the game is played.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.33,0:59:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十拿九稳 路易斯\N{\r原文字幕}It's in the bag, Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.58,0:59:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好配合就行\N{\r原文字幕}So play nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.17,0:59:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们请来科学家又怎样？\N{\r原文字幕}They bring in a scientist, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.04,0:59:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不像我那么了解科学家\N{\r原文字幕}You don't know scientists like I do, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.17,0:59:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们讨厌质疑他们判断的任何人\N{\r原文字幕}They resent anyone who questions their judgment,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.38,0:59:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是局外人\N{\r原文字幕}especially if you're not one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.30,0:59:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾是原子能委员会主席\N{\r原文字幕}I was chair of the AEC.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.84,0:59:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特的事会怪在我身上\N{\r原文字幕}I'm easy to blame for what happened to Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.01,0:59:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不能让参议院觉得…\N{\r原文字幕}We can't have the Senate thinking the scientific community
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.31,0:59:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学界不支持你 先生\N{\r原文字幕}doesn't support you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.93,0:59:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许应该改变说词？\N{\r原文字幕}Or should we pivot?  -To what?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.60,0:59:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么改变？  -采取强硬立场\N{\r原文字幕}And embrace it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.40,0:59:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我杠上奥本海默 美国赢了\N{\r原文字幕}"I fought Oppenheimer and the US won."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.23,0:59:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得不该这么说\N{\r原文字幕}I-I don't think we need to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.94,0:59:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道到底发生什么事？\N{\r原文字幕}Isn't there someone we can call who knows what really happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.07,0:59:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒\N{\r原文字幕}Teller.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.07,0:59:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的份量够重\N{\r原文字幕}-He'll make an impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.24,0:59:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能查出那个科学家是谁吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Can you get the name of the scientist they've called?  -Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.99,0:59:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大概吧  -查出他在战时是在…\N{\r原文字幕}Find out if he was based in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.62,0:59:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,芝加哥或是洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}or Los Alamos during the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.20,0:59:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那有何关系？\N{\r原文字幕}Why does that matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.20,0:59:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在芝加哥就是替西拉德和费米工作\N{\r原文字幕}-If he was based in Chicago, he worked under Szilard and Fermi,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.87,0:59:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是替奥比创立的邪教工作\N{\r原文字幕}not the cult of Oppie at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.13,0:59:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特一手建造那地方\N{\r原文字幕}Robert built that damn place.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.50,0:59:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是创始者、市长、警长\N{\r原文字幕}He was founder, mayor, sheriff,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.13,0:59:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,简直就是一个神\N{\r原文字幕}all rolled into one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.06,1:00:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里只缺一间酒馆\N{\r原文字幕}All it needs is a saloon. Let's go and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.59,1:00:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有厨房\N{\r原文字幕}There's no kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.05,1:00:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗？我们会解决\N{\r原文字幕}Really? We'll fix that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.31,1:00:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,铁丝网围栏、枪械\N{\r原文字幕}Barbed wire? Guns?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.56,1:00:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.73,1:00:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在打仗 汉斯\N{\r原文字幕}We're at war, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.82,1:01:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈利法克斯 1917年\N{\r原文字幕}Halifax, 1917.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.49,1:01:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一艘满载炸药的货船在港口爆炸\N{\r原文字幕}A cargo ship carrying munitions explodes in the harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.87,1:01:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引发巨大和突然的化学反应\N{\r原文字幕}A vast and sudden chemical reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.46,1:01:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,历史上最大的人为爆炸\N{\r原文字幕}The biggest man-made explosion in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.84,1:01:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是核反应而非化学反应\N{\r原文字幕}Now let's calculate how much more destructive it would have been
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.26,1:01:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,计算破坏会有多大\N{\r原文字幕}if it were a nuclear, and not a chemical, reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.26,1:01:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以黄色炸药的吨数表示威力\N{\r原文字幕}Expressing power in terms of tons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.35,1:01:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那会是上千吨威力\N{\r原文字幕}But it will be thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.22,1:01:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就以千吨计算\N{\r原文字幕}Well, then...kilotons.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.90,1:01:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使用铀-235\N{\r原文字幕}Using U-235,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.32,1:01:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子弹会需要…\N{\r原文字幕}the bomb will need--Ah...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.90,1:01:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 小工具会需要这大小的15公斤圆球\N{\r原文字幕}Right, sorry. Gadget will need a 33-pound sphere about this size.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.49,1:01:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使用钚则需要4.5公斤圆球\N{\r原文字幕}Or using plutonium, the ten-pound sphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.66,1:01:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是橡树岭上个月提炼的铀量\N{\r原文字幕}Here's the amount of uranium Oak Ridge refined all of last month.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.71,1:02:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是汉福德工厂生产的钚\N{\r原文字幕}And the Hanford plant made this much plutonium.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.76,1:02:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果能浓缩这些 就必须设法引爆\N{\r原文字幕}Now, if we can enrich these amounts, we need a way to detonate them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.81,1:02:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华 你觉得无聊吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Are we boring you, Edward?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.02,1:02:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一点\N{\r原文字幕}A little bit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.44,1:02:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请问为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}May I ask why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.85,1:02:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道有可能制造原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}We all entered this room knowing a fission bomb was possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.82,1:02:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如用点新玩意\N{\r原文字幕}How about we leave it with something new?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.94,1:02:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}-Such as?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.28,1:02:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用氢取代铀或是钚\N{\r原文字幕}Instead of uranium or plutonium, we use hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.99,1:02:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重氢  -氢\N{\r原文字幕}Heavy hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.95,1:02:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,氘 懂吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Deuterium. You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.75,1:02:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用巨大压力把原子核…\N{\r原文字幕}We compact the atoms together under great pressure
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.04,1:02:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,压缩在一起 引发融合反应\N{\r原文字幕}to induce a fusion reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.54,1:02:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸威力不只是数千吨\N{\r原文字幕}Then we'll get not kilotons,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.34,1:02:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是数百万吨\N{\r原文字幕}but megatons.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.34,1:02:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 稍安勿躁\N{\r原文字幕}Okay, hang on, hang on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.26,1:02:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那要如何产生足够的力量融合氢原子？\N{\r原文字幕}So how do you generate enough force to fuse hydrogen atoms?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.26,1:02:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一枚小型原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}A small fission bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.47,1:02:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就对了\N{\r原文字幕}Ah...There we are!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.56,1:02:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反正需要一颗原子弹 何不继续讨论？\N{\r原文字幕}Well, since we're going to need one anyway, can we get back to the business at hand?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.27,1:03:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和奥本海默博士最大的歧见…\N{\r原文字幕}The isotopes issue wasn't your most important policy disagreement
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.82,1:03:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不是同位素的问题\N{\r原文字幕}with Dr.Oppenheimer,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.15,1:03:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是氢弹 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}it was the hydrogen bomb, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.78,1:03:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身为同事 我们有很多歧见\N{\r原文字幕}As colleagues, we agreed to disagree on a great many things, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.41,1:03:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中一个就是氢弹计划\N{\r原文字幕}and, well, one of them was the need for an H-bomb program, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.68,1:03:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多谢各位临时前来参加聚会\N{\r原文字幕}Thanks for convening on short notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.47,1:03:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不敢相信\N{\r原文字幕}I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.06,1:03:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们齐聚一堂\N{\r原文字幕}Here we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.39,1:03:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说说看 我们知道什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Catch me up.What do we know?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.44,1:03:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-29轰炸机在北太平洋上空侦测到辐射\N{\r原文字幕}One of our B-29s over the North Pacific has detected radiation.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.90,1:03:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有用滤纸侦测吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do we have the filter paper?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.28,1:03:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是毫无疑问的事实\N{\r原文字幕}There's no doubt what this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.90,1:03:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白宫表示有疑虑\N{\r原文字幕}-White House says there's a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.78,1:03:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只是一厢情愿\N{\r原文字幕}Wishful thinking, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.74,1:03:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些是远程侦测滤纸吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Are those the long-range detection filter papers?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.62,1:03:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是核弹试爆\N{\r原文字幕}It's an atomic test.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.58,1:03:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国人有核弹\N{\r原文字幕}The Russians have a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.33,1:04:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该领先好几年 但是…\N{\r原文字幕}We're supposed to be years ahead of them, but some--
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.71,1:04:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们在洛斯阿拉莫斯做什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What were you guys doing at Los Alamos?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.01,1:04:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安全措施不够严密吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Wasn't security tight?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.21,1:04:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然够严密 你当时不在…\N{\r原文字幕}Of course it was.You weren't there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.67,1:04:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恕我直言 博士…\N{\r原文字幕}-Forgive me, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.93,1:04:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我当时在那里\N{\r原文字幕}but I was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.68,1:04:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在可以开始设计实际的引爆机制\N{\r原文字幕}We can now consider the actual mechanics of detonation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.85,1:04:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有任何想法吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.23,1:04:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我称之为“射击”\N{\r原文字幕}I call this "shooting."
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.69,1:04:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把一块可分裂物质射进一个大型球体…\N{\r原文字幕}We fire a chunk of fissionable material into a larger sphere
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.40,1:04:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要有足够力量就能引爆\N{\r原文字幕}with enough force to achieve criticality.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.36,1:04:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家有什么想法？\N{\r原文字幕}What do we think? Anyone?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.90,1:04:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直在考虑内爆\N{\r原文字幕}I've been thinking about implosion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.53,1:04:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,球体周围的炸药向内爆炸…\N{\r原文字幕}Explosives around the sphere blast inwards,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.61,1:04:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,压碎可分裂物质\N{\r原文字幕}crushing the material.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.58,1:04:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想研究那个可能性\N{\r原文字幕}I'd like to investigate that idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.54,1:04:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会通知军火库 让你搞一些爆炸\N{\r原文字幕}I'll talk to Ordnance, get you blowing things up.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.96,1:04:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有进展吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Progress?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.04,1:04:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也很高兴见到你\N{\r原文字幕}-Nice to see you too.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.88,1:04:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,见过英国代表团\N{\r原文字幕}Meet the British contingent.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.75,1:04:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 我是克劳斯富赫斯\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer, Klaus Fuchs.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.63,1:04:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当英国人多久了？\N{\r原文字幕}How long have you been British?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.38,1:04:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自从希特勒说我不是德国人\N{\r原文字幕}Since Hitler told me I wasn't German.Aha.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.30,1:04:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎来到洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}Come, welcome to Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.59,1:04:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,学校开学了\N{\r原文字幕}School's up and running.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.35,1:04:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,酒吧 一直都在营业\N{\r原文字幕}Bar...always running.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.47,1:05:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我设法减少支援人力\N{\r原文字幕}And I thought of a way to reduce support staff.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.94,1:05:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是？  -瑟伯尔夫人\N{\r原文字幕}Is that-- -Mrs.Serber, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.85,1:05:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为所有妻子提供工作\N{\r原文字幕}I've offered jobs to all the wives.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.19,1:05:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行政人员、图书馆馆员、计算员\N{\r原文字幕}Admin, librarians, computation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.36,1:05:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,裁减人力 让家人一起工作\N{\r原文字幕}We cut down on staff, keep families together.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.61,1:05:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些女人合格吗？  -别傻了\N{\r原文字幕}Are these women qualified?  -Don't be absurd.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.61,1:05:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们是这里最聪明的人\N{\r原文字幕}These are some of the brightest minds in our community.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.03,1:05:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且通过安全核查\N{\r原文字幕}And they're already security cleared.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.33,1:05:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉格罗夫斯少将你每晚固定举行\N{\r原文字幕}I've informed General Groves you've been holding
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.74,1:05:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跨部门公开讨论\N{\r原文字幕}cross-divisional, open discussions on a nightly basis.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.95,1:05:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,禁止举行 权限划分是保密的关键\N{\r原文字幕}Shut them down. Compartmentalization is the key to maintaining security--
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.50,1:05:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各部主管而已\N{\r原文字幕}It's only the top men.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.50,1:05:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们一定会和下属沟通\N{\r原文字幕}Who presumably communicate with subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.50,1:05:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些人不笨 他们非常谨慎\N{\r原文字幕}These men aren't stupid.They can be discreet.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.46,1:05:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不喜欢\N{\r原文字幕}I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.51,1:05:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你什么都不喜欢就无法进行测试\N{\r原文字幕}-You don't like anything enough for that to be a fair test.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.10,1:05:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每周一次 仅限各部主管\N{\r原文字幕}Once a week.Top men only.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.81,1:05:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想把我弟弟找来\N{\r原文字幕}I'd like to bring my brother here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.10,1:05:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行\N{\r原文字幕}-No.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.98,1:05:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼柯斯…\N{\r原文字幕}Nichols.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.27,1:05:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还没听说我的安全许可获得批准\N{\r原文字幕}I still haven't heard that my security clearance has been approved.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.03,1:05:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还没有  -我们明天要去芝加哥\N{\r原文字幕}It hasn't.  -We're going to Chicago tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.03,1:05:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该再等等\N{\r原文字幕}Well, you should wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.86,1:05:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道纳粹领先我们两年吧\N{\r原文字幕}You are aware that the Nazis have a two-year head start?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.41,1:05:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士 你难以获得…\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer, the fact that your security clearance
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.28,1:06:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安全许可并不是我的错\N{\r原文字幕}is proving difficult to obtain is not my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.62,1:06:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是你的错\N{\r原文字幕}It's yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.91,1:06:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这是你的问题 因为我要去\N{\r原文字幕}May not be your fault, but it's your problem.Because I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.33,1:06:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有多少人参与这些公开讨论？\N{\r原文字幕}And how many people were in these, uh, open discussions?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.30,1:06:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太多人 权限划分应该是铁律\N{\r原文字幕}Too many.Compartmentalization was supposed to be the protocol.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.63,1:06:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时是与纳粹进行军事竞争\N{\r原文字幕}We were in a race against the Nazis.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.26,1:06:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在要和苏联进行核军备竞赛\N{\r原文字幕}And now the race is against the Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.72,1:06:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非我们挑起一罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}-Not unless we start it. Robert,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.30,1:06:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们开了第一枪\N{\r原文字幕}they just fired a starting gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.68,1:06:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们引爆了哪种炸弹？\N{\r原文字幕}What's the nature of the device they detonated?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.98,1:06:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数据显示可能是内爆式钚分裂炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}The data indicates it may have been a plutonium implosion device.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.56,1:06:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像你在洛斯阿拉莫斯制造的那种\N{\r原文字幕}Like the one you built at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.82,1:06:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国人有核弹\N{\r原文字幕}The Russians have a bomb,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.40,1:06:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜鲁门需要知道接下来会怎样\N{\r原文字幕}Truman needs to know what's next.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.78,1:06:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接下来会怎样？核武谈判\N{\r原文字幕}What's next? Arms talks.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.86,1:06:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,核武谈判？  -当然了\N{\r原文字幕}Arms talks.  -Obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.66,1:06:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,氢弹呢？杜鲁门知道吗？\N{\r原文字幕}What about the Super? Does Truman even know about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.37,1:06:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有没有向他简报？\N{\r原文字幕} Did we brief him on that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.50,1:06:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并没有\N{\r原文字幕}Not specifically.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.66,1:06:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不确定氢弹在技术上是否可行\N{\r原文字幕}We still don't know if a hydrogen bomb's technically feasible.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.71,1:06:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据我所知这是泰勒提出来的？\N{\r原文字幕}My understanding is that Teller proposed it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.79,1:06:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对  -在洛斯阿拉莫斯？\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.At Los Alamos?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.04,1:06:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒的设计一向都不切实际\N{\r原文字幕}Teller's designs have always been wildly impractical.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.34,1:06:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得用牛车拖去 不是用飞机投放\N{\r原文字幕}You'd have to deliver by ox cart. Not airplane.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.97,1:06:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比  -抱歉 劳伦斯博士 你想…\N{\r原文字幕}-Oppie. I'm sorry, Dr.Lawrence.Do you want to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.30,1:07:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发言？\N{\r原文字幕}comment?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.68,1:07:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不想\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.93,1:07:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果氢弹能让我们再度领先\N{\r原文字幕}Because if it can put us ahead again,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.19,1:07:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国总统\N{\r原文字幕}the President of the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.27,1:07:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就必须知道\N{\r原文字幕}needs to know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.78,1:07:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛斯阿拉莫斯的间谍若已泄密给俄国…\N{\r原文字幕}And if the Russians know about it already from a spy at Los Alamos,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.61,1:07:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我们就得加快脚步\N{\r原文字幕}then we've gotta get going.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.82,1:07:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你无法证明洛斯阿拉莫斯有间谍\N{\r原文字幕}There's no proof there was a spy at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.83,1:07:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.00,1:07:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把它放在美式足球场底下？\N{\r原文字幕}They put it under the football stadium?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.67,1:07:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这座球场没在使用\N{\r原文字幕}The field's not in use anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.59,1:07:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样也好\N{\r原文字幕}Just as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.63,1:07:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比  -费米博士\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie.  -Dr.Fermi.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.52,1:07:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么样？挺好吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Come stai? Va bene?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.39,1:07:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说你有一座小城镇\N{\r原文字幕}I hear you got a little town.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.68,1:07:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 去看看\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.Come and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.56,1:07:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁能在那种地方专心思考？\N{\r原文字幕}Who could think straight in a place like that? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.77,1:07:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都会发疯\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody will go crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.48,1:07:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多谢你的肯定 西拉德\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you for the vote of confidence, Szilard.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.07,1:07:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那有必要写进笔记里吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do we really--Do we really need that in the notes?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.95,1:08:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你打算几时试验？\N{\r原文字幕}When are you going to try it out?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.70,1:08:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已经试验过了\N{\r原文字幕}We did.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.28,1:08:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一次可控的核连锁反应\N{\r原文字幕}The first self-sustaining nuclear chain reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.37,1:08:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格罗夫斯没告诉你？\N{\r原文字幕}Didn't Groves tell you?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.50,1:08:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.25,1:08:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个一个来\N{\r原文字幕}One at a time, please.One at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.17,1:08:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士？\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.76,1:08:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去了人资部 他们问我会不会打字\N{\r原文字幕}I tried Personnel.They asked if I could type.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.55,1:08:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Can you?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.55,1:08:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈佛大学忘了教化学系研究生打字\N{\r原文字幕}Harvard forgot to teach that on the graduate chemistry course.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.27,1:08:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康登 让霍尼格夫人加入钚组\N{\r原文字幕}Condon, put Mrs.Hornig here on the plutonium team.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.61,1:08:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么去芝加哥？\N{\r原文字幕}What the hell were you doing in Chicago?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.61,1:08:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去看冶金实验室？\N{\r原文字幕}Visiting the Met?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.78,1:08:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？  -你不能…\N{\r原文字幕}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.66,1:08:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们有权利…\N{\r原文字幕}Because we have every right--
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.03,1:08:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我给的权利 不多也不少\N{\r原文字幕}You have just the rights that I give you.No more, no less.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.37,1:08:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是在进行计划的成年人 这太扯了\N{\r原文字幕}We are adults trying to run a project here. This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.17,1:08:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉他啊\N{\r原文字幕}Tell him.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.63,1:08:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们同意要划分权限\N{\r原文字幕}Compartmentalization is the protocol we agreed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.55,1:09:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这太扯了 没人能在这种条件下工作\N{\r原文字幕}Enough of this madhouse. Nobody can work under these conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.80,1:09:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道吗 大元帅？我不干了\N{\r原文字幕}You know what, Generalissimo? I quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.26,1:09:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是多谢了\N{\r原文字幕}Thanks for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.89,1:09:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他走了更好\N{\r原文字幕}Better off without him.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.60,1:09:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不担心他会泄漏机密吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Aren't you more concerned about his discretion out there?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.65,1:09:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会杀人灭口\N{\r原文字幕}We'll have him killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.94,1:09:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开玩笑的\N{\r原文字幕}I was just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.11,1:09:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他恨的是我 不是美国\N{\r原文字幕}No, he hates me, not America.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.41,1:09:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少将 不是每个人都跟我一样有把柄\N{\r原文字幕}You know, General, not everyone has levers to pull like mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.83,1:09:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不懂你在说什么\N{\r原文字幕}I don't think I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.49,1:09:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是无视我的左倾过去\N{\r原文字幕}You didn't hire me despite my left-wing past,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.54,1:09:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是因此雇用我\N{\r原文字幕}you hired me because of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.17,1:09:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以才能掌控我\N{\r原文字幕}So you could control me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.25,1:09:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的心机没那么重\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I'm not that subtle.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.80,1:09:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是个卑微的士兵\N{\r原文字幕}I'm just a humble soldier.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.88,1:09:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不卑微更不只是士兵\N{\r原文字幕}You're neither humble, nor just a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.55,1:09:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你念过麻省理工学院工程系\N{\r原文字幕}You studied engineering at MIT.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.26,1:09:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被你说对了\N{\r原文字幕}-Guilty as charged.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.26,1:09:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都开诚布公了 帮我弄到安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}Well, now we understand each other, perhaps you can get me my security clearance
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.35,1:09:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好让我为你创造这项奇蹟\N{\r原文字幕}so I can perform this miracle for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.44,1:10:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格罗夫斯中将 你任命奥本海默时…\N{\r原文字幕}General Groves, were you aware of Dr.Oppenheimer's
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.11,1:10:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道他的左倾思想吗？\N{\r原文字幕}left-wing associations when you appointed him?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.28,1:10:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道有人对他有疑虑\N{\r原文字幕}I was aware that there were suspicions about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.36,1:10:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也知道他的极端自由派背景\N{\r原文字幕}I was aware he had a very extreme, liberal background.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.70,1:10:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你看来 他是否会蓄意背叛国家？\N{\r原文字幕}In your opinion, would he ever consciously commit a disloyal act?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.04,1:10:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果会的话我会很惊讶\N{\r原文字幕}I would be amazed if he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.75,1:10:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你完全相信他很爱国\N{\r原文字幕}So you had complete confidence in his integrity?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.62,1:10:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在洛斯阿拉莫斯 我在那里才了解他\N{\r原文字幕}At Los Alamos, yes, which is where I really knew him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.42,1:10:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中将 你的安全官是否建议你…\N{\r原文字幕}General, did your security officers on the project
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.00,1:10:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拒绝批准奥本海默的安全许可？\N{\r原文字幕}advise you against the clearance of Dr.Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.34,1:10:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不能也不会批准 直到我坚持\N{\r原文字幕}They could not and would not clear him until I insisted.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.39,1:10:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对他的安全档案…\N{\r原文字幕}And it's safe to say that you had a pretty good knowledge
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.18,1:10:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有很充分的了解\N{\r原文字幕}of Dr.Oppenheimer's security file.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.93,1:10:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.72,1:10:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我今天只希望你回答一个问题\N{\r原文字幕}There's only really one question I need answered here today.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.39,1:10:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据目前的原子能委员会法规\N{\r原文字幕}In light of the current AEC guidelines,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.40,1:10:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会批准奥本海默的安全许可吗？\N{\r原文字幕}would you clear Dr.Oppenheimer today?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.06,1:10:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有法规吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you have the guidelines?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.20,1:10:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据目前的原子能委员会法规…\N{\r原文字幕}Under current AEC guidelines,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.70,1:10:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会批准奥本海默的安全许可吗？\N{\r原文字幕}would you clear Dr.Oppenheimer today?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.84,1:11:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,物理学和新墨西哥州？\N{\r原文字幕}Physics and New Mexico, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.89,1:11:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊 路途真遥远\N{\r原文字幕}My God. What a trek.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.97,1:11:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以你需要一个联络人\N{\r原文字幕}That's why you need a liaison.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.47,1:11:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要任命洛马尼茨\N{\r原文字幕}I'm appointing Lomanitz.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.06,1:11:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不会有事\N{\r原文字幕}You're gonna be okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.14,1:11:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里请 各位\N{\r原文字幕}This way, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.49,1:11:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.57,1:11:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莱斯利\N{\r原文字幕}-Leslie.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.91,1:11:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想提醒你我们在伯克利说的事\N{\r原文字幕}I'd like to remind you what we talked about in Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.99,1:11:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,权限划分 我完全理解\N{\r原文字幕}Compartmentalization. I understand completely.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.71,1:11:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.18,1:11:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来自伯克利的问候\N{\r原文字幕}Greetings from Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.64,1:11:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来报告我们的进展并征求各位的意见\N{\r原文字幕}I am here to update you on our progress and solicit your input.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.06,1:11:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我必须分享一些少将不准我说的事\N{\r原文字幕}To do so, I am going to have to share a few things that General Groves told me not to.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.02,1:12:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 我说我能理解 但并不苟同\N{\r原文字幕}Sorry, General, I said I understood, not that I agreed.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.06,1:12:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.52,1:12:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位 言归正传\N{\r原文字幕}Gentlemen, to business.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.65,1:12:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谣言说有间谍…  -毫无根据\N{\r原文字幕}There were rumors of espionage at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.86,1:12:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在洛斯阿拉莫斯  -未经证实\N{\r原文字幕}Unsubstantiated.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.49,1:12:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说有共产党员参与计划\N{\r原文字幕}I'm told that there were communists on the project.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.53,1:12:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不是故意的  -我只想知道…\N{\r原文字幕}We didn't knowingly employ any communists.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.33,1:12:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们有没有参与氢弹的讨论\N{\r原文字幕}Were any of them involved in discussions of the Super?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.54,1:12:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记得你要求让令弟去洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}I seem to remember you demanding your brother come to Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.04,1:12:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他那时候已经退党了\N{\r原文字幕}My brother had left the Party by then.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.88,1:12:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨呢？\N{\r原文字幕}What about Lomanitz?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.92,1:12:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他从来不是正式员工 只是联络人\N{\r原文字幕}Lomanitz was never employed at Los Alamos. He was a liaison.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.34,1:12:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼柯斯上校很清楚安检有多严密\N{\r原文字幕}Our security was tight, as former Colonel Nichols well knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.88,1:12:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安检非常严密 但仍有可疑分子…\N{\r原文字幕}Our security was as tight as it could be given the personalities involved,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.64,1:12:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做出一些尝试\N{\r原文字幕}but attempts were made.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.01,1:12:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么意思？\N{\r原文字幕}What is that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.06,1:12:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都看过他的档案\N{\r原文字幕}-We've all read his file here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.18,1:12:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是不是该谈谈琼塔特洛克？\N{\r原文字幕}Do we need to talk about Jean Tatlock?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.65,1:12:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是薛瓦利埃事件？\N{\r原文字幕}Or the Chevalier incident?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.40,1:12:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,失陪一下\N{\r原文字幕}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.07,1:12:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨在一线\N{\r原文字幕}That's Lomanitz, on line one.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.91,1:13:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 罗西\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Rossi.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.21,1:13:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了？冷静下来\N{\r原文字幕}What? Okay, just calm down.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.13,1:13:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又出了错 洛马尼茨被征召入伍\N{\r原文字幕}There's been another screw-up. Lomanitz just got drafted.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.30,1:13:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在打仗 博士\N{\r原文字幕}We are at war, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.67,1:13:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别说这种鬼话 尼柯斯 我们需要他\N{\r原文字幕}-Don't be an asshole, Nichols. We need this kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.05,1:13:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽快解决 好吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Fix it, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.30,1:13:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是出错\N{\r原文字幕}It wasn't a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.39,1:13:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨想让放射实验室工会化\N{\r原文字幕}Your friend Lomanitz has been trying to unionize the Radiation Lab.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.85,1:13:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他答应会放弃的\N{\r原文字幕}He promised to quit all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.18,1:13:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并没有\N{\r原文字幕}Well, he hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.23,1:13:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伯克利的安全官担心共产党会渗透工会\N{\r原文字幕}Security officer at Berkeley's concerned about communist infiltration through that union, the FA--
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.61,1:13:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我下周会去 我会去见他\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I'm there next week, I'll...drop in to see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.28,1:13:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的最高安全许可通过了\N{\r原文字幕}Your Q clearance came through.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.79,1:13:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你绝对不能和可疑分子继续联络\N{\r原文字幕}It's important you not maintain or renew any questionable associations.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.21,1:13:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,博士 你是否认为参与…\N{\r原文字幕}Doctor, did you think social contacts
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.22,1:13:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,秘密战争计划和共产党有交集有危险？\N{\r原文字幕}between a person engaged on secret war work and communists was dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.43,1:13:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为这种情况现在会更危险\N{\r原文字幕}My awareness of the danger would be greater today.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.39,1:14:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以你认为在战时…\N{\r原文字幕}I mean, it's fair to say that during the war years,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.23,1:14:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样的交集可能会有危险\N{\r原文字幕}you felt that such contacts were potentially dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.82,1:14:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可想而知 没错\N{\r原文字幕}Were conceivably dangerous, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.86,1:14:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说真的…\N{\r原文字幕}I mean, really?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.03,1:14:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,公开的共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}Known communists?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.33,1:14:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是这样的\N{\r原文字幕}Look...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.46,1:14:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的心中很久以来都有很多秘密\N{\r原文字幕}I've had a lot of secrets in my head for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.84,1:14:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管我跟谁往来…\N{\r原文字幕}Doesn't matter who I associate with.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.38,1:14:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我都不会谈到那些秘密\N{\r原文字幕}I don't talk about those secrets.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.64,1:14:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在声明中说…\N{\r原文字幕}You said in your statement
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.35,1:14:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在1943年必须去见琼塔特洛克\N{\r原文字幕}that you had to see Jean Tatlock in 1943.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.69,1:14:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你离开了\N{\r原文字幕}You left.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.57,1:14:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,音讯全无\N{\r原文字幕}Not a word.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.45,1:14:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得那会对我怎样？\N{\r原文字幕}What did you think that would do to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.66,1:14:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有写信\N{\r原文字幕}I wrote.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.03,1:15:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有写等于没写\N{\r原文字幕}Pages of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.62,1:15:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去了哪里？\N{\r原文字幕}Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.75,1:15:09.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能说  -为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}I can't tell you.Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.33,1:15:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你是共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}Because you're a communist.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.84,1:15:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么必须见她？\N{\r原文字幕}Why did you have to see her?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.55,1:15:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我离开前她表示她很想再见到我\N{\r原文字幕}Because she had indicated a great desire to see me before we left.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.35,1:15:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时我不能见她 但我觉得她必须见我\N{\r原文字幕}At that time, I couldn't, but I felt that she had to see me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.31,1:15:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她在接受心理治疗 她非常不快乐\N{\r原文字幕}She was undergoing psychiatric treatment. She was extremely unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.98,1:15:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道她为何必须见你吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you find out why she had to see you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.32,1:15:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为她还爱着我\N{\r原文字幕}Because she was still in love with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.83,1:15:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们共度一晚 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Spent the night together, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.42,1:15:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.89,1:16:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在我生命中来来去去…\N{\r原文字幕}You drop in and out of my life
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.06,1:16:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却不必告诉我为什么\N{\r原文字幕}and you don't have to tell me why.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.89,1:16:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是权力\N{\r原文字幕}Now, that's power.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.15,1:16:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并不喜欢\N{\r原文字幕}Not that I enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.98,1:16:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我宁愿在你需要时陪着你\N{\r原文字幕}I'd rather be here for you as you need.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.48,1:16:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你现在有更重要的事\N{\r原文字幕}But you have other priorities now.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.57,1:16:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有妻小\N{\r原文字幕}I have a wife and child.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.66,1:16:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们说的不是那件事\N{\r原文字幕}That's not what either of us is talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.87,1:16:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琼\N{\r原文字幕}Jean.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.75,1:16:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要我来\N{\r原文字幕}You asked me to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.38,1:16:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很高兴我来了\N{\r原文字幕}And I'm glad I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.92,1:16:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我不能再来见你\N{\r原文字幕}But I can't see you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.93,1:16:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但如果我需要你呢？\N{\r原文字幕}But what if I need you?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.47,1:16:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说你一定会回应\N{\r原文字幕}You said you would always answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.60,1:16:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无话可说？\N{\r原文字幕}Not a word.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.19,1:16:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为那符合安全规定？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you think that consistent with good security?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.23,1:16:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上是的\N{\r原文字幕}As a matter of fact, it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.44,1:17:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我什么也没说\N{\r原文字幕}Not a word.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.61,1:17:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你后来何时又见过她？\N{\r原文字幕}When did you see her after that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.79,1:17:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我再也没有见过她\N{\r原文字幕}I never saw her again.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.92,1:17:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能搭最后一班火车回普林斯顿\N{\r原文字幕}I can make the last train back to Princeton.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.09,1:17:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂 我什么都跟你说了\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty, I didn't say anything that I hadn't already told you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.59,1:17:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今天说的话会成为历史\N{\r原文字幕}Today you said it to history, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.60,1:17:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是秘密听证会\N{\r原文字幕}This is a closed hearing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.10,1:17:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算他们不公开记录 你也会\N{\r原文字幕}If they don't release the transcript, I'm sure you will.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.69,1:17:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我宣誓作证\N{\r原文字幕}I was under oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.73,1:17:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去见琼的时候早就宣誓和我结婚\N{\r原文字幕}Well, you were under an oath to me when you went to see Jean.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.86,1:17:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你…\N{\r原文字幕}You know, you...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.11,1:17:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只会每天坐在那里\N{\r原文字幕}you sit there, day after day,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.61,1:17:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们把我们伤得体无完肤\N{\r原文字幕}letting them pick our lives to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.49,1:17:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么不反抗？\N{\r原文字幕}Why won't you fight?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.46,1:17:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 我不会让她出席作证\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, I'm not putting her up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.84,1:18:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士 幸会了 请坐\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer, it's an honor.Please, take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.68,1:18:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了 我只想知道是不是该…\N{\r原文字幕}No need, I just wanted to check whether I should talk to Lomanitz
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.14,1:18:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,趁机和洛马尼茨谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}while I'm here, given your concerns.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.60,1:18:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是你的决定 但我会小心行事\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I'd say that's really up to you, Professor, but I'd be cautious.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.94,1:18:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,了解\N{\r原文字幕}Uh-huh.Understood.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.52,1:18:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至于工会 我想先提醒你…\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, and, um......as regards to the union,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.61,1:18:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留意一个叫艾尔坦顿的人\N{\r原文字幕}I wanted to give you a heads-up on a man named Eltenton.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.23,1:18:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先提醒我？\N{\r原文字幕}A heads-up?  -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.24,1:18:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 他可能值得你留意一下\N{\r原文字幕}Just that he might merit watching, is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.16,1:18:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道更多细节  -我…\N{\r原文字幕}I'd love to get more details.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.62,1:18:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在有约 明天一早就走\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I have an appointment now, and I leave early tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.16,1:18:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能尽快回来最好\N{\r原文字幕}Well, come back as early as you like.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.37,1:18:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既然你现在没空\N{\r原文字幕}Since you haven't time now.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.92,1:18:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你隔天早上又回去\N{\r原文字幕}You went back the next morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.59,1:18:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错 我必须回去\N{\r原文字幕}I did.I had to, really.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.67,1:18:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次有另一个人\N{\r原文字幕}This time there was another man.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.01,1:18:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说他叫帕什\N{\r原文字幕}He said his name was Pash.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.55,1:18:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕什 你见到帕什上校？\N{\r原文字幕}Pash.You met Colonel Pash?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.10,1:18:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕什上校 请你读出你的\N{\r原文字幕}Colonel Pash, could you please read from your memo
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.51,1:18:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1943年6月29日备忘录内容\N{\r原文字幕}dated June 29, 1943?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.52,1:18:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,监视对象的结果显示…\N{\r原文字幕}"Results of surveillance conducted on subject
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.65,1:19:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和更多共产党员联系\N{\r原文字幕}indicate further possible Communist Party connections.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.61,1:19:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和共产党员琼塔特洛克谈了很久\N{\r原文字幕}Subject met with, and spent considerable time with, one Jean Tatlock, communist,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.95,1:19:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,附上她的记录\N{\r原文字幕}the record of whom is attached."
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.36,1:19:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,监视对象是奥本海默博士？\N{\r原文字幕}The subject being Dr.Oppenheimer?  -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.53,1:19:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -你没见过他？\N{\r原文字幕}Whom you had not met?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.83,1:19:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时没有 后来见过面\N{\r原文字幕}Not then, but soon after.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.24,1:19:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是安全部门主管 我不该认识他？\N{\r原文字幕}He's the head of security for the project.Shouldn't I know him?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.87,1:19:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 他应该认识你\N{\r原文字幕}No, he should know you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.12,1:19:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我绝对不会让你们见面\N{\r原文字幕}I would never put you in a room with Pash.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.63,1:19:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.96,1:19:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当帕什听到洛马尼茨的事…\N{\r原文字幕}When Pash first heard about Lomanitz,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.05,1:19:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他跟联邦探员说他要绑架他 带他上船\N{\r原文字幕}he told the FBI he was gonna kidnap him, take him out on a boat
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.76,1:19:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后用老俄的方法拷问他\N{\r原文字幕}and interrogate him in the Russian manner.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.22,1:19:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格罗夫斯少将交给我一些责任\N{\r原文字幕}General Groves has placed in me a certain responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.52,1:19:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像有一个我不能见的小孩\N{\r原文字幕}and it's like having a child who I can't see.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.73,1:19:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只能远远观察他\N{\r原文字幕}By remote control.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.36,1:19:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以真的见到你…\N{\r原文字幕}So to actually meet you is...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.69,1:19:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会占用你太多时间\N{\r原文字幕}I won't take up too much of your time.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.03,1:19:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没关系 尽管用\N{\r原文字幕}-No, not at all. Whatever time you choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.53,1:19:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对你昨天和某个人的谈话很感兴趣\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Johnson told me of a conversation you had yesterday in which I'm very interested.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.20,1:19:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我担心了一整天\N{\r原文字幕}It's had me worried all day.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.41,1:19:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想未经授权就跟洛马尼茨说话\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, well, I didn't want to talk to Lomanitz without authorization.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.04,1:20:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感兴趣的不是那件事\N{\r原文字幕}That's not the particular interest that I have.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.92,1:20:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是更…\N{\r原文字幕}It's something a little bit more...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.88,1:20:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我看来是更严重的事\N{\r原文字幕}in my opinion, more serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.51,1:20:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当联邦调查局指出这种情报\N{\r原文字幕}Now, when the FBI pointed out that such information
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.51,1:20:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会被法庭采信\N{\r原文字幕}wouldn't be admissible in court,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.80,1:20:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕什就表明不会留下任何活口\N{\r原文字幕}Pash made it clear he had no intention of leaving any witness left to prosecute.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.14,1:20:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,联邦调查局劝阻了他 但他就是这种人\N{\r原文字幕}Now, the FBI talked him down, but that's the man you're dancing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.31,1:20:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道他国对放射实验室的研究感兴趣\N{\r原文字幕}I gather you've heard there are other parties interested in the work of the Radiation Lab?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.06,1:20:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个隶属苏联领事馆的人\N{\r原文字幕}A man attached to the Soviet Consul
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.48,1:20:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通过中间人表示…\N{\r原文字幕}indicated through intermediate people to people on this project
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.99,1:20:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他能够为计划中的人传递机密情报\N{\r原文字幕}that he was in a position to transmit information.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.66,1:20:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,计划中的人为什么要那么做？\N{\r原文字幕}Why would anyone on the project wanna do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.12,1:20:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说 我看得出总统可能有理由…\N{\r原文字幕}Frankly, I can see that there might be an argument
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.54,1:20:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和俄国分享情报 毕竟他们是盟友\N{\r原文字幕}for the commander-in-chief informing the Russians. They're our allies after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.92,1:20:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我不喜欢用走后门的方法\N{\r原文字幕}But I don't like the idea of it going out the back door.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.80,1:20:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以稍微留意不会有坏处\N{\r原文字幕}It might not hurt to be on the lookout for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.72,1:20:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟帕什那么说？\N{\r原文字幕}And you said that to Pash?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.10,1:20:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想表明俄国不是德国\N{\r原文字幕}I was trying to put it in the context of "Russia's not Germany."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.52,1:21:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍里斯帕什的父亲是俄罗斯正教会主教\N{\r原文字幕}Boris Pash is the son of a Russian Orthodox bishop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.06,1:21:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在美国出生 但在1918年\N{\r原文字幕}Born here, but in 1918,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.90,1:21:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回去俄国对抗布尔什维克\N{\r原文字幕}he went back to Russia to fight the Bolsheviks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.57,1:21:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他亲手杀死过共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}This is a man who has killed communists with his own hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.53,1:21:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的职责不是决定谁该拥有情报\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not the judge of who should or should not have information.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.66,1:21:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是阻止有人非法泄漏情报\N{\r原文字幕}It's my business to stop it from going through illegally.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.28,1:21:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能说得更具体吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Would you be a little more specific?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.87,1:21:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人多次跟我提起一个名字 艾尔坦顿\N{\r原文字幕}There's a man whose name was mentioned to me a couple of times. Eltenton.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.21,1:21:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是在壳牌石油工作的化学家\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, I believe he's a chemist who works at Shell.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.01,1:21:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他跟他的一位朋友谈过…\N{\r原文字幕}He talked to a friend of his
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.13,1:21:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位朋友认识计划中的某个人\N{\r原文字幕}who's an acquaintance of someone on the project.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.14,1:21:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得帕什就会满意了？\N{\r原文字幕}And you thought Pash would be satisfied with that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.14,1:21:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想招出艾尔坦顿 不希望节外生枝\N{\r原文字幕}I was attempting to give them Eltenton without opening a can of worms.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.98,1:21:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我编了牛头不对马嘴的故事\N{\r原文字幕}I told them a cock-and-bull story.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.02,1:21:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也向格罗夫斯少将说谎？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you lie to General Groves too?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.61,1:21:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有 我向他承认我对帕什说谎\N{\r原文字幕}No.I admitted to him that I'd lied to Pash.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.32,1:21:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你记得关于薛瓦利埃事件的对话吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you recall this conversation about the Chevalier incident?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.11,1:21:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看过太多版本\N{\r原文字幕}I've seen so many versions of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.66,1:22:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以为我很清楚 但现在却更糊涂\N{\r原文字幕}I wasn't confused before but I'm certainly getting there now.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.50,1:22:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的结论是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What was your conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.62,1:22:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有着典型美国小学生的天真想法\N{\r原文字幕}That he was under the influence of the typical American schoolboy attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.92,1:22:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,背叛朋友是一件坏事\N{\r原文字幕}that there's something wicked about telling on a friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.51,1:22:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原来如此\N{\r原文字幕}Well, now...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.42,1:22:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能说出中间人是谁吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Might we know through whom the contact was made?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.47,1:22:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就会牵扯到与此事无关的人\N{\r原文字幕}That would involve people who are not to be involved in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.35,1:22:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是计划的成员吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is that someone a member of the project?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.73,1:22:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是教职员 但没参与计划\N{\r原文字幕}A member of the faculty, yes, but not in the project, no.  -Ah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.81,1:22:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾尔坦顿的中间人是伯克利的教职员？\N{\r原文字幕}So Eltenton made his approach through a member of the faculty here at Berkeley?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.40,1:22:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据我所知 是的\N{\r原文字幕}As far as I know-- As far as I know, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.99,1:22:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但中间人可能不只一个\N{\r原文字幕}But......there may have been more than one person involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.54,1:22:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我看起来不愿合作 请了解\N{\r原文字幕}Gentlemen, if I--If I seem uncooperative, I think you can understand
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.46,1:22:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很坚持不让无辜的人惹上麻烦\N{\r原文字幕}it's because of my insistence in not getting innocent people into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.67,1:22:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想保护朋友 谁又能保护你？\N{\r原文字幕}You're trying to protect your friend.Who's protecting you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.72,1:22:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能保护我\N{\r原文字幕}Well, you could.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.26,1:23:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要你招出名字\N{\r原文字幕}-If you gave me the name.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.43,1:23:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你命令我 我会照办\N{\r原文字幕}If you order me to, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.47,1:23:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能这样 你必须自愿告诉我\N{\r原文字幕}That is a mistake, Robert.You need to volunteer this name.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.60,1:23:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有告诉你吗？  -有的\N{\r原文字幕}-And did he give you the name?  -He did.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.98,1:23:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当时没有 对吧？  -没有\N{\r原文字幕}But not then, did he? No.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.36,1:23:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是几个月后 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}No.In fact, it was some months later, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.15,1:23:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}It was.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.15,1:23:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为我很固执\N{\r原文字幕}You see me as persistent.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.74,1:23:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是很固执 那是你的职责\N{\r原文字幕}-Well, you are-- You are persistent, but that is your job.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.95,1:23:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的职责是保护为我工作的人\N{\r原文字幕}And-And my job is to protect the people that work for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.62,1:23:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是让我采取极端手法\N{\r原文字幕}Instead of us going on certain steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.66,1:23:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能会引起你的注意\N{\r原文字幕}which may come to your attention...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.12,1:23:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也会让你感到不安\N{\r原文字幕}and be disturbing to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.17,1:23:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想先跟你讨论一下\N{\r原文字幕}I would like to discuss those with you first.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.00,1:23:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没在制定计划 只是得了解整件事\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not formulating a plan.I'll just have to digest the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.14,1:23:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你前后诘问奥本海默博士几个月\N{\r原文字幕}In the months in between your interview with Dr.Oppenheimer
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.22,1:23:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到他最后招出薛瓦利埃的名字\N{\r原文字幕}and his eventual naming of Chevalier,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.85,1:23:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否动用更多资源查出中间人是谁？\N{\r原文字幕}did you expend resources trying to find the name of the intermediary?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.85,1:23:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我动用了大量的资源\N{\r原文字幕}Considerable resources, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.40,1:23:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有名字会让我们的工作非常困难\N{\r原文字幕}Without the name, our job was extremely difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.57,1:23:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你何时得知这个名字？\N{\r原文字幕}And when did you receive the name?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.19,1:23:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默终于招出他时我已经走了\N{\r原文字幕}I was gone by the time Oppenheimer finally offered it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.86,1:23:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走了？\N{\r原文字幕}Gone?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.82,1:24:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们觉得我应该前往欧洲…\N{\r原文字幕}-They felt my time would be better spent in Europe
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.12,1:24:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,调查纳粹原子弹计划的进展\N{\r原文字幕}determining the status of the Nazi bomb project.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.87,1:24:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who did?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.91,1:24:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格罗夫斯少将\N{\r原文字幕}General Groves.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.96,1:24:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把我调到伦敦\N{\r原文字幕}He transferred me to London.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.30,1:24:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在开圣诞派对有点早\N{\r原文字幕}It's a little early for a Christmas party.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.18,1:24:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出事了 托尔曼离开了\N{\r原文字幕}Something's up.Tolman's been away.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.26,1:24:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他去了哪？\N{\r原文字幕}Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.85,1:24:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,露丝不肯说\N{\r原文字幕}Ruth won't tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.15,1:24:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿！\N{\r原文字幕}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.23,1:24:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托 除了我你还能跟谁说？\N{\r原文字幕}Come on, Ruthie.Can't tell me, who can you tell?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.99,1:24:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,权限划分 奥比\N{\r原文字幕}Compartmentalization, Oppie.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.62,1:24:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你凭什么觉得我知道他在哪里？\N{\r原文字幕}What makes you think I know where he is anyway?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.58,1:24:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你在重要时刻一向都知道他在哪里\N{\r原文字幕}'Cause you do a pretty good job of knowing where Mr.Tolman is when it counts.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.29,1:24:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像是现在？\N{\r原文字幕}Like now?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.33,1:24:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长官驾到！\N{\r原文字幕}Attention!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.55,1:24:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提早送给大家的圣诞礼物\N{\r原文字幕}Early Christmas present for you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.81,1:25:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英国飞行员让我坐在炸弹舱\N{\r原文字幕}The British pilots put me in the bomb bay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.23,1:25:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,教我怎么用氧气罩 但我没用对\N{\r原文字幕}Showed me the-the oxygen, you know, but I messed it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.35,1:25:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,降落在苏格兰的时候我已经昏过去\N{\r原文字幕}When they opened me up in Scotland, I was unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.90,1:25:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我假装只是在打瞌睡\N{\r原文字幕}But I pretended I'd been napping.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.82,1:25:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玩得开心点\N{\r原文字幕}Please enjoy your party.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.49,1:25:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,炸弹够大吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is it big enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.86,1:25:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够终结战争？\N{\r原文字幕}To end the war?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.87,1:25:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够终结所有战争\N{\r原文字幕}To end all war.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.62,1:25:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海森堡去哥本哈根找我\N{\r原文字幕}Heisenberg sought me out in Copenhagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.75,1:25:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真可怕 我的学生竟然为纳粹工作\N{\r原文字幕}It was chilling, my old student working for the Nazis.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.05,1:25:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他为了把我引出来说了一些事\N{\r原文字幕}He told me some things to draw me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.68,1:25:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,铀的持续性核分裂反应\N{\r原文字幕}Sustained fission reactions in uranium.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.80,1:25:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那听起来像是反应炉而不是炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}That sounds more like a reactor than a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.43,1:25:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有没有提到气体扩散法？\N{\r原文字幕}Did he mention gaseous diffusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.97,1:25:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他似乎比较重视重水\N{\r原文字幕}He seemed more focused on heavy water.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.64,1:25:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作为中子减速剂？\N{\r原文字幕}As a moderator?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.89,1:25:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 不是用核石墨\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, instead of graphite.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.65,1:25:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了？\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.61,1:26:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他用错方法了\N{\r原文字幕}He took a wrong turn.We're ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.57,1:26:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们领先他们 又有你帮忙 尼尔斯\N{\r原文字幕}And with you here to help us, Niels...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.45,1:26:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 你们能不能回避一下？\N{\r原文字幕}Sorry, could you--could you give us a moment, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.67,1:26:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是来帮忙的 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}I am not here to help, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.42,1:26:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道没有我你也能做到\N{\r原文字幕}I knew you could do this without me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.38,1:26:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你为什么来？\N{\r原文字幕}Then why did you come?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.51,1:26:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讨论以后的事\N{\r原文字幕}To talk about after.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.05,1:26:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你即将制造的力量将永远改变世界\N{\r原文字幕}The power you're about to reveal will forever outlive the Nazis.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.14,1:26:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这世界却毫无准备\N{\r原文字幕}And the world is not prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.89,1:26:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你抬起石头却没想到会出现一条毒蛇\N{\r原文字幕}"You could lift the stone without being ready for the snake that's revealed."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.43,1:26:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须让政客了解这不是全新的武器\N{\r原文字幕}We have to make the politicians understand, this isn't a new weapon.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.48,1:26:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是全新的世界\N{\r原文字幕}It's a new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.32,1:26:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会尽力鼓吹这一点 但是你\N{\r原文字幕}I'll be out there doing what I can, but you...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.40,1:26:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是美国普罗米修斯\N{\r原文字幕}You are an American Prometheus.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.20,1:26:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你赋予人类自我毁灭的力量\N{\r原文字幕}The man who gave them the power to destroy themselves,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.24,1:26:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会尊重这一点\N{\r原文字幕}and they'll respect that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.08,1:26:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的工作这才真正开始\N{\r原文字幕}Then your work really begins.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.58,1:27:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 奥比 有一通电话\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry, Oppie, but there's a call.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.84,1:27:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从旧金山打来的\N{\r原文字幕}From San Francisco.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.26,1:27:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特？\N{\r原文字幕}Robert?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.98,1:27:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特？\N{\r原文字幕}Robert?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.52,1:27:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.Robert.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.19,1:27:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊 你怎么了？\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, my God.What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.82,1:27:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发生什么事？\N{\r原文字幕}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.99,1:27:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她父亲打来\N{\r原文字幕}Her father called.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.95,1:27:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们昨天在浴室发现她\N{\r原文字幕}They found her yesterday in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.12,1:27:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.49,1:27:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她吃了药…\N{\r原文字幕}She'd taken pills.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.16,1:27:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也留下遗书 没有签名\N{\r原文字幕}Left a note, not signed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.12,1:27:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她服用镇静剂 但血液中有水合氯醛\N{\r原文字幕}She took barbiturates, but there was chloral hydrate in her blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.80,1:27:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一封遗书\N{\r原文字幕}There was a note.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.46,1:27:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琼塔特洛克？\N{\r原文字幕}Jean Tatlock?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.60,1:27:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去找过她\N{\r原文字幕}We were together.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.52,1:27:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她说她需要我 而我…\N{\r原文字幕}She said she needed me.I...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.73,1:28:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟她说我不会…\N{\r原文字幕}I told her I...  -...I wouldn't--
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.69,1:28:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说我不能…\N{\r原文字幕}I told her I couldn't--
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.73,1:28:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是因为我\N{\r原文字幕}No, it was--it was me--
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.20,1:28:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能犯了罪…\N{\r原文字幕}You don't get to commit the sin
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.41,1:28:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却因为造成的后果让大家可怜你\N{\r原文字幕}and then have us all feel sorry for you that it had consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.12,1:28:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要振作起来\N{\r原文字幕}You pull yourself together.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.04,1:28:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的人全都指望你\N{\r原文字幕}You know, people here depend on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.63,1:28:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唐纳德 你想发表意见吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Donald, would you like to contribute here, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.47,1:28:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只能靠自己\N{\r原文字幕}You're on your own, pal.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.55,1:28:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会因为钚有放射性辞职\N{\r原文字幕}Bob, I'm not quitting my job because plutonium is radioactive.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.47,1:28:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不知道它对女性生殖器官有何影响\N{\r原文字幕}We just don't know what it might do to the female reproductive system--
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.73,1:28:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的生殖器官被暴露的比我的多\N{\r原文字幕}Your reproductive system is more exposed than mine, presumably.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.73,1:28:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别吵了\N{\r原文字幕}Can we please?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.94,1:28:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连内爆装置都没有\N{\r原文字幕}The implosion device is nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.15,1:28:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凡事不能急就章 拜托\N{\r原文字幕}You can't rush everything.Oppie, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.15,1:28:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有急就章和循序渐进 挑一个\N{\r原文字幕}Well, there's rushing and there's getting on with it, so, pick one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.86,1:28:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,内德迈尔在努力工作 泰勒没在帮忙\N{\r原文字幕}Wait.Neddermeyer's doing his job. Teller's not helping.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.53,1:28:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没在帮忙\N{\r原文字幕}You're not helping.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.53,1:28:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这几周都在要求爆缩透镜的计算\N{\r原文字幕}I've been asking for calculations on the implosion lenses for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.20,1:28:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让英国佬计算 富赫斯\N{\r原文字幕}The British can do it.Fuchs.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.83,1:28:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题\N{\r原文字幕}-Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.91,1:28:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是你的工作 泰勒\N{\r原文字幕}It's your job, Teller.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.41,1:29:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在进行研究\N{\r原文字幕}-I'm engaged in research.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.29,1:29:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,研究我们不会制造的氢弹\N{\r原文字幕}On a hydrogen bomb we're not even building.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.22,1:29:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会替那个人工作\N{\r原文字幕}I won't work for that man.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.10,1:29:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他走 他在耍大牌\N{\r原文字幕}Let him go.He's a prima donna.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.47,1:29:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我同意 他应该离开\N{\r原文字幕}I agree.He should leave Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.43,1:29:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.02,1:29:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基斯 你取代内德迈尔\N{\r原文字幕}Kisty, you replace Neddermeyer.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.81,1:29:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞斯 我把你调到钚组\N{\r原文字幕}Seth, I'm putting you on plutonium.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.27,1:29:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莉莉 替基斯工作 他需要你\N{\r原文字幕}Lilli, you go work for Kisty, because he needs you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.94,1:29:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,富赫斯 你取代泰勒\N{\r原文字幕}Fuchs, you take Teller's role.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.57,1:29:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要你专心研究内爆装置\N{\r原文字幕}I'm putting you exclusively on the implosion device.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.49,1:29:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人能离开洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}And no one is leaving Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.51,1:29:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不让我离开  -没错\N{\r原文字幕}They won't let me leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.84,1:29:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会让你离开\N{\r原文字幕}No.I won't let you leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.59,1:29:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别管汉斯 别管核分裂\N{\r原文字幕}Forget Hans.Forget fission.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.31,1:30:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留下来想研究什么都行\N{\r原文字幕}Stay here, research what you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.43,1:30:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,核融合、氢弹 我们会开会讨论\N{\r原文字幕}Fusion, the hydrogen bomb, whatever. We'll meet to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.19,1:30:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你根本就没空开会\N{\r原文字幕}You don't have time to meet.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.69,1:30:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你变成政客了 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}You're a politician now, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.11,1:30:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你早就把物理学抛在脑后\N{\r原文字幕}You've left physics behind many, many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.82,1:30:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每周一次\N{\r原文字幕}Once a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.53,1:30:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一小时 你和我\N{\r原文字幕}One hour, you and me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.33,1:30:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把该死的栅栏打开\N{\r原文字幕}Now raise this fucking barrier.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.84,1:30:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在洛斯阿拉莫斯时就开始研发氢弹？\N{\r原文字幕}So the Super was under development on your watch at Los Alamos?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.71,1:30:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.09,1:30:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你在战后却否认那个可行性\N{\r原文字幕}And yet, after the war, you tried to deny it was viable.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.64,1:30:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不对 我只是指出技术上的困难\N{\r原文字幕}No, no, no.I-I pointed out technical difficulties with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.72,1:30:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国进行核弹试爆后你试图终止那计划\N{\r原文字幕}Didn't you try to kill it at the AEC meeting after the Russian bomb test?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.89,1:30:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并没有  -但那是你的建议…\N{\r原文字幕}-No. But that was the recommendation of the AEC,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.60,1:30:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是吗？  -我们讨论过…\N{\r原文字幕}was it not? After hours of discussion
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.98,1:30:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是最好的回应\N{\r原文字幕}about the best response.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.90,1:30:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一枚氢弹…\N{\r原文字幕}An H-bomb
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.07,1:30:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是一颗原子弹威力的一千倍\N{\r原文字幕}is 1,000 times the power of an A-bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.41,1:30:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目标会是最大的城市\N{\r原文字幕}Its only intended target would be the largest cities.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.12,1:31:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是大规模种族灭绝武器\N{\r原文字幕}It's a weapon of mass genocide.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.74,1:31:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伊西 在地图这边画个圈…\N{\r原文字幕}Izzy, draw some circles on this side of the map
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.83,1:31:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是他们的目标\N{\r原文字幕}where they would target us.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.04,1:31:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先是纽约和华府  -没错\N{\r原文字幕}Starting with New York. That's fair.  -DC.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.46,1:31:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是无法防御的攻击武器\N{\r原文字幕}It's a weapon of attack with no defensive value.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.25,1:31:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,威慑  -“威慑”？\N{\r原文字幕}Deterrence.  -"Deterrence"?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.76,1:31:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以目前的核武数量来说\N{\r原文字幕}Do we really need more deterrence
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.42,1:31:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的需要更多威摄力量？\N{\r原文字幕}than our current arsenal of atomic bombs?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.88,1:31:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在10尺或1万尺深的水中溺死…\N{\r原文字幕}Y-You drown in ten feet of water or 10,000,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.72,1:31:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么不同？\N{\r原文字幕}what's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.14,1:31:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能溺死俄国 他们也知道\N{\r原文字幕}We can already drown Russia.They know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.18,1:31:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在他们能溺死我们  -只要威胁升级…\N{\r原文字幕}Now they can drown us.  -We're just escalating.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.53,1:31:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说过泰勒的设计和战时一样不切实际\N{\r原文字幕}As I said, Teller's designs are still as impractical as they were during the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.37,1:31:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能制造氢弹 你心知肚明\N{\r原文字幕}A hydrogen bomb can be made to work, Oppie, you know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.33,1:31:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不应该因此投入所有的资源\N{\r原文字幕}I don't believe we should commit all our resources to that chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.21,1:31:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你要杜鲁门怎么让美国人民放心？\N{\r原文字幕}Then how would you have Truman reassure the American people?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.29,1:31:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要通过国际对核能的控制\N{\r原文字幕}Simply by limiting the spread of atomic weapons
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.63,1:31:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就能限制核武的扩散\N{\r原文字幕}through international control on nuclear energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.88,1:31:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是指全世界的政府？\N{\r原文字幕}By which you mean world government.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.68,1:32:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗斯福总统心目中的联合国\N{\r原文字幕}The United Nations, as Roosevelt intended.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.47,1:32:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是问杜鲁门该怎么做 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I asked what Truman should do, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.39,1:32:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界局势改变了\N{\r原文字幕}The world's changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.47,1:32:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,威胁不是法西斯主义而是共产主义\N{\r原文字幕}It's not fascism but communism that now threatens our survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.10,1:32:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,路易斯 你要知道我们若是制造氢弹\N{\r原文字幕}Lewis, do you understand, if we build a hydrogen bomb,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.56,1:32:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国人别无选择也会制造\N{\r原文字幕}the Russians will have no choice but to build their own?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.40,1:32:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们有可能正在制造吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Could they be working on one already,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.90,1:32:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据洛斯阿拉莫斯的间谍搜集的情报\N{\r原文字幕}based on information gathered from a spy at Los Alamos?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.61,1:32:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛斯阿拉莫斯没有间谍\N{\r原文字幕}No spy at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.16,1:32:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有吗？  -别岔开话题\N{\r原文字幕}Gentlemen.Let's not get sidetracked.There wasn't?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.08,1:32:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们藉此机会逼俄国让步…\N{\r原文字幕}I say we use this moment to gain concessions from the Russians
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.87,1:32:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做出不制造氢弹的承诺\N{\r原文字幕}by committing that we will not build a hydrogen bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.91,1:32:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样一来就证实氢弹的存在\N{\r原文字幕}Thereby revealing its existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.67,1:32:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你似乎早就认为他们知道了\N{\r原文字幕}Which you seem convinced they already know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.88,1:32:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,够了\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.13,1:32:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在要请委员会成员私下开会\N{\r原文字幕}At this point, I'd like the committee members
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.72,1:32:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确认我们最后的建议\N{\r原文字幕}to meet in privacy to finalize our recommendations.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.43,1:32:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定你应该坚持己见\N{\r原文字幕}I'm just not sure you wanna go down this road.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.47,1:32:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恕我直言 我们是顾问委员会\N{\r原文字幕}Lewis, with respect, we are the advisory committee,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.81,1:32:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要给他们建议\N{\r原文字幕}we will give them our advice.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.86,1:32:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士？我是威廉波登\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer? Hi. William Borden.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.03,1:32:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子能联席委员会？\N{\r原文字幕}Joint Committee on Atomic Energy?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.32,1:32:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.74,1:33:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在战时是一名飞行员\N{\r原文字幕}During the war, I was a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.61,1:33:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一晚完成轰炸任务后\N{\r原文字幕}One night, flying back from a raid,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.20,1:33:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看见像彗星的惊人景象\N{\r原文字幕}I saw an amazing sight, like a meteor.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.83,1:33:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,射往英国的V-2火箭\N{\r原文字幕}A V-2 rocket headed to England.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.08,1:33:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我忍不住想像那枚火箭…\N{\r原文字幕}I can't help but imagine what it will be
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.13,1:33:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若是乘载核弹头会有什么后果\N{\r原文字幕}for such an enemy rocket to carry an atomic warhead.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.93,1:33:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们就必须确保不会有这种可能\N{\r原文字幕}Well, let's make sure we're not the ones to make that possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.23,1:33:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比 你最好别和史特劳斯硬碰硬\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie, I don't think you wanna go up against Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.94,1:33:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们同时发言 他们会听我的\N{\r原文字幕}If we both speak, they listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.57,1:33:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你发言 他们把你当先知\N{\r原文字幕}When you speak, they hear a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.45,1:33:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当史特劳斯发言 他们把他当自己人\N{\r原文字幕}When Strauss speaks, they hear themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.57,1:33:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会听先知的话\N{\r原文字幕}They'll listen to a prophet.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.66,1:33:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先知不会错 一次都不会\N{\r原文字幕}A prophet can't be wrong.Not once.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.79,1:33:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是指控奥本海默破坏氢弹的研发？\N{\r原文字幕}Didn't you accuse Oppenheimer of sabotaging the development of the Super?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.25,1:33:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会随便用“破坏”这种字眼\N{\r原文字幕}I was never one of those to bandy around terms like "sabotage."
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.09,1:34:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但波登先生会？\N{\r原文字幕}But Mr.Borden was?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.13,1:34:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据我所知有可能\N{\r原文字幕}As I understand it, possibly.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.42,1:34:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他怎么能写出那么详细的起诉书？\N{\r原文字幕}How was Mr.Borden able to put together such a detailed indictment?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.22,1:34:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不再是政府员工…\N{\r原文字幕}He was no longer a government employee,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.85,1:34:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但似乎能任意调阅奥本海默的安全档案\N{\r原文字幕}yet he appears to have had unlimited access to Dr.Oppenheimer's file.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.81,1:34:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有可能是出于尼柯斯的允许吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Might Mr.Nichols have given him access to the file?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.52,1:34:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是原子能委员会的其他成员？\N{\r原文字幕}Or someone else at the AEC?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.86,1:34:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是非常严重的指控 参议员\N{\r原文字幕}That's a very serious accusation, Senator.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.53,1:34:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想暗示奥本海默博士对美国不忠吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is it your intention to suggest that Dr.Oppenheimer is disloyal to the United States?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.45,1:34:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从以前到现在都认为他完全忠于美国\N{\r原文字幕}I've always assumed, and still assume, that he's loyal to the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.16,1:34:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对此坚信不移 除非有确切反证\N{\r原文字幕}I believe this.And I shall believe it until I see very conclusive proof to the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.75,1:34:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否认为奥本海默博士构成国安风险？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you, or do you not believe that Dr.Oppenheimer is a security risk?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.64,1:34:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当希特勒在地堡饮弹自尽后…\N{\r原文字幕}And if I may, when Hitler blew his brains out in that bunker,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.43,1:34:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就没必要在任何地方引爆原子弹…\N{\r原文字幕}it is my humble opinion that there is no need for that bomb to be seen
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.60,1:34:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了在试爆地点\N{\r原文字幕}anywhere except for that test site.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.19,1:34:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们必须认真思考\N{\r原文字幕}We at least have to take a moment to think about
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.31,1:35:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否应该继续研发 因为…\N{\r原文字幕}whether the means justify the ends any longer, because--
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.15,1:35:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,德国即将投降\N{\r原文字幕}Germany is about to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.45,1:35:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类最大的威胁不再是敌人\N{\r原文字幕}It's no longer the enemy who are the greatest threat to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.58,1:35:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是我们的研究成果\N{\r原文字幕}It's our work.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.12,1:35:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希特勒死了 千真万确\N{\r原文字幕}Hitler is dead, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.50,1:35:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但日本人继续作战\N{\r原文字幕}But the Japanese fight on.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.21,1:35:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们一定会战败\N{\r原文字幕}Their defeat seems assured.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.26,1:35:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对前线的士兵来说不是这样\N{\r原文字幕}Not if you're a GI preparing to invade.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.09,1:35:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能终结战争\N{\r原文字幕}We can end this war.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.26,1:35:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该怎么合理化对人类使用这个武器？\N{\r原文字幕}But how do we justify using this weapon on human beings?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.89,1:35:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是理论家 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}We're theorists, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.15,1:35:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们想像一个未来\N{\r原文字幕}We imagine a future,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.57,1:35:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个未来想像让我们胆战心惊\N{\r原文字幕}and our imaginings horrify us.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.57,1:35:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们不会感到恐惧 直到能够理解它\N{\r原文字幕}But they won't fear it until they understand it,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.82,1:35:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而人们无法理解它 直到使用它\N{\r原文字幕}and they won't understand it until they've used it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.74,1:35:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当全世界得知洛斯阿拉莫斯的可怕秘密\N{\r原文字幕}When the world learns the terrible secret of Los Alamos,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.87,1:35:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的研究成果\N{\r原文字幕}our work here
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.00,1:35:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将为人类带来前所未见的和平\N{\r原文字幕}will ensure a peace mankind has never seen.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.33,1:36:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗斯福一直设想国际合作的那种和平\N{\r原文字幕}A peace based on the kind of international cooperation that Roosevelt always envisaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.72,1:36:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有何进展？\N{\r原文字幕}Progress?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.76,1:36:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两年内花了十亿美元？\N{\r原文字幕}-Two years and a billion dollars' worth?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.55,1:36:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这很难用金钱衡量\N{\r原文字幕}Well, hard to put a price on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.22,1:36:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不难 把帐单加起来就行\N{\r原文字幕}Not really.Just add up the bills.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.93,1:36:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生小孩完全免费\N{\r原文字幕}"Rural free deliveries."
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.77,1:36:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一年生了80个婴儿\N{\r原文字幕}Eighty babies delivered the first year.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.44,1:36:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今年每个月有10个\N{\r原文字幕}This year we've had ten a month.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.98,1:36:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,节育不在我的管辖范围 少将\N{\r原文字幕}Birth control is a little out of my jurisdiction, General.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.57,1:36:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了  -少将\N{\r原文字幕}Clearly.  -General.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.66,1:36:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,低下头 大伙儿\N{\r原文字幕}Head down,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.20,1:36:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,富赫斯 低下头\N{\r原文字幕}every--Fuchs.Head down.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.21,1:36:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来不错\N{\r原文字幕}That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.63,1:36:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两次爆破测试 我需要日期\N{\r原文字幕}Two viable bombs.I need a date.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.09,1:36:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,九月\N{\r原文字幕}September.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.47,1:36:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七月\N{\r原文字幕}July.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.72,1:36:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爆破正中预定点\N{\r原文字幕}That's the sweet spot, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.18,1:36:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,八月\N{\r原文字幕}August.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.81,1:36:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七月\N{\r原文字幕}July.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.43,1:37:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七月进行试爆\N{\r原文字幕}Test in July.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.40,1:37:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我需要我弟弟\N{\r原文字幕}But I need my brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.32,1:37:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克了解沙漠 他也不再碰政治\N{\r原文字幕}Frank knows the desert, he's left politics behind,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.36,1:37:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且和劳伦斯合作两年了\N{\r原文字幕}he's been working with Lawrence for two years now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.79,1:37:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场试爆要命名什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What do we call the test?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.96,1:37:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,震撼吾心 三一之神\N{\r原文字幕}"Batter my heart, three person'd God."
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.42,1:37:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.21,1:37:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三位一体\N{\r原文字幕}Trinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.18,1:37:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,令弟是共产党员 你却坚持把他找去\N{\r原文字幕}You insisted on bringing on your brother Frank, a known communist.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.27,1:37:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前共产党员\N{\r原文字幕}Former communist.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.19,1:37:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你让前共产党员参与…\N{\r原文字幕}You brought a known former communist
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.81,1:37:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国最机密和最重要的国防计划\N{\r原文字幕}onto America's most secret and important defense project.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.03,1:37:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以完全信任他 毫无疑问\N{\r原文字幕}I knew my brother could be trusted.Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.36,1:37:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对你能信任谁的判断是正确的吗？\N{\r原文字幕}And you felt your judgment was sound on who on the team could be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.70,1:37:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,富赫斯 低下头\N{\r原文字幕}Fuchs, head down.Okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.03,1:37:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家准备好了吗？\N{\r原文字幕}everybody ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.21,1:38:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望你们得到了教训\N{\r原文字幕}I hope you learned something.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.59,1:38:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的距离必须更远\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, we learned we're gonna need to be a lot further away.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.72,1:38:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽快计算出距离\N{\r原文字幕}Well, figure it out.Fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.34,1:38:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明早要去华府 必须给出一个日期\N{\r原文字幕}We leave for Washington in the morning.We're gonna give them a date.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.61,1:38:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从芝加哥跑来 利奥\N{\r原文字幕}You're a long way from Chicago, Leo.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.40,1:38:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再不采取行动 他们会用来轰炸日本\N{\r原文字幕}If we don't act now, they're going to use this thing against Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.87,1:38:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜鲁门本来约见我们 但被人阻止了\N{\r原文字幕}We booked a meeting with Truman, but somebody killed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.95,1:38:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要去见战争部长\N{\r原文字幕}You're meeting the secretary of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.33,1:38:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在制造它 不代表能决定怎么使用\N{\r原文字幕}Just because we're building it doesn't mean we get to decide how it's used.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.67,1:38:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,历史将评断我们 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}History will judge us, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.63,1:38:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在芝加哥拟出一份请愿书\N{\r原文字幕}In Chicago, we put together a petition.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.09,1:38:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会参与那件事\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not getting into that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.30,1:39:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说出你的担忧 我会帮你转达\N{\r原文字幕}Just tell me your concerns and I'll relay them.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.01,1:39:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的担忧？\N{\r原文字幕}My concerns?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.64,1:39:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,德国战败了 日本也撑不了不久\N{\r原文字幕}Germany's defeated.Japan's not going to hold out alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.73,1:39:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么知道？这是你的主意\N{\r原文字幕}How could you know that? You got us into this.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.11,1:39:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和爱因斯坦告诉罗斯福应该制造炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}You and Einstein with your letter to Roosevelt saying we could build a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.48,1:39:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用来对付德国\N{\r原文字幕}Against Germany.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.48,1:39:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,制造武器没这么简单 西拉德\N{\r原文字幕}That's not how weapons manufacture works, Szilard.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.45,1:39:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比 你得帮忙\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie, you have to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.78,1:39:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费米在开会 劳伦斯也在开会\N{\r原文字幕}Fermi's in the meeting.Lawrence is in the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.49,1:39:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不是你\N{\r原文字幕}They're not you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.62,1:39:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是伟大的科学推销员\N{\r原文字幕}You're the great salesman of science.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.95,1:39:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以说服任何人\N{\r原文字幕}You can convince anyone of anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.33,1:39:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至你自己\N{\r原文字幕}Even yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.42,1:39:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,失陪了\N{\r原文字幕}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.46,1:39:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,东京大轰炸死了十万人\N{\r原文字幕}The firestorm in Tokyo killed 100,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.71,1:39:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大多数是平民\N{\r原文字幕}Mostly civilians.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.47,1:39:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发生这种事却没人抗议\N{\r原文字幕}I worry about an America
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.38,1:39:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为美国感到忧心\N{\r原文字幕}where we do these things and no one protests.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.93,1:39:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,珍珠港事件和三年的太平洋战争\N{\r原文字幕}Pearl Harbor and three years of brutal conflict in the Pacific
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.35,1:39:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们得到美国民众的支持\N{\r原文字幕}bought us a lot of latitude with the American public.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.14,1:39:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,足以投放原子弹？\N{\r原文字幕}Enough to unleash the atomic bomb?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.27,1:39:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子弹不会像东京大轰炸那样死伤惨重\N{\r原文字幕}The A-bomb might not cause as much damage as the Tokyo bombings.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.69,1:39:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,估计的死亡人数？\N{\r原文字幕}What are we estimating?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.11,1:39:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投放在中型城市…\N{\r原文字幕}In a medium-sized city,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.65,1:39:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2到3万人死亡\N{\r原文字幕}20,000 or 30,000 dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.95,1:39:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 但是…\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, but
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.36,1:40:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别低估原爆造成的心理冲击\N{\r原文字幕}don't underestimate the psychological impact of an atomic explosion.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.29,1:40:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一团1万尺高的火球\N{\r原文字幕}A pillar of fire 10,000 feet tall.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.16,1:40:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,方圆1英里内致命的中子辐射\N{\r原文字幕}Deadly neutron effects for a mile.In all directions.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.46,1:40:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全都来自一颗炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}From one single device.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.38,1:40:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从高空中的轰炸机上投放\N{\r原文字幕}Dropped from a barely noticed B-29,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.51,1:40:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子弹将会是…\N{\r原文字幕}the atomic bomb will be
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.01,1:40:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神圣力量的可怕启示\N{\r原文字幕}a terrible revelation of divine power.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.30,1:40:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是真的 这将是致命一击\N{\r原文字幕}If that's true, it would be definitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.01,1:40:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,二次大战将会终结\N{\r原文字幕}World War II would be over.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.22,1:40:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的弟兄也能回家\N{\r原文字幕}Our boys would come home.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.85,1:40:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,军事目标？\N{\r原文字幕}Military targets?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.44,1:40:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有够大的目标\N{\r原文字幕}Uh...There aren't any big enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.94,1:40:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重要的军工厂 附近有工人宿舍\N{\r原文字幕}Perhaps a vital war plant with workers housed nearby?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.94,1:40:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以发出警告 减少平民伤亡\N{\r原文字幕}And we could issue a warning to reduce civilian casualties.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.20,1:40:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,敌方会倾巢而出对付我们…\N{\r原文字幕}They'd send everything they have up against us,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.28,1:40:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会在轰炸机上面\N{\r原文字幕}and I'd be up in that plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.29,1:40:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但若是宣布了却没爆炸…\N{\r原文字幕}But if we announce it and it fails to go off,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.37,1:40:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就会失去日本投降的机会\N{\r原文字幕}we'd scupper any chance of a Japanese surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.29,1:40:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没办法展现原子弹威力逼日本投降吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is there no way to demonstrate a bomb to Japan to provoke surrender?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.42,1:40:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们打算以最明确的方式展现威力\N{\r原文字幕}We intend to demonstrate it in the most unambiguous terms.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.80,1:40:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两次\N{\r原文字幕}Twice.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.76,1:41:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一次展现武器的威力\N{\r原文字幕}Once, to show the weapon's power,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.93,1:41:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第二次表明他们不投降就会继续下去\N{\r原文字幕}and a second to show that we can keep doing this until they surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.56,1:41:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有12座城市可以挑选…\N{\r原文字幕}We have a list of 12 cities to choose from--
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.06,1:41:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 11座\N{\r原文字幕}Sorry, 11.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.98,1:41:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我剔除了京都 那是日本文化的象征\N{\r原文字幕}I've taken Kyoto off the list due to its cultural significance to the Japanese people.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.57,1:41:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且我和我太太去那里度蜜月\N{\r原文字幕}Also, my wife and I honeymooned there.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.49,1:41:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是很美的古都\N{\r原文字幕}It's a magnificent city.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.62,1:41:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我把事情变得更简单\N{\r原文字幕}Let me make this simple for you, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.08,1:41:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据我不能分享的情报\N{\r原文字幕}According to my intelligence, which I cannot share with you,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.62,1:41:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日本人民不会投降…\N{\r原文字幕}the Japanese people will not surrender,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.12,1:41:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管是任何情况\N{\r原文字幕}under any circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.79,1:41:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非我们完全占领日本本岛\N{\r原文字幕}short of a successful and total invasion of the home islands.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.71,1:41:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国和日本都会死伤惨重\N{\r原文字幕}Many lives will be lost, American and Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.84,1:41:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在日本城市投放原子弹会拯救人命\N{\r原文字幕}The use of the atomic bomb on Japanese cities will save lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.59,1:41:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要我们具有道德优势\N{\r原文字幕}If we retain moral advantage.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.30,1:41:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么说？\N{\r原文字幕}-How so?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.31,1:41:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不先通知盟友就使用这武器\N{\r原文字幕}Well, if we use this weapon without informing our allies,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.64,1:41:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会被视为威胁\N{\r原文字幕}they'll see it as a threat,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.68,1:41:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们就会进入军备竞赛\N{\r原文字幕}and we'll be in an arms race.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.31,1:41:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能对苏联公开多少？\N{\r原文字幕}How open can we be with the Soviets?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.52,1:41:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保密不会阻止苏联成为核武国家\N{\r原文字幕}Secrecy won't stop the Soviets from becoming part of the atomic world.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.65,1:42:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据情报他们没有铀\N{\r原文字幕}We've been told they have no uranium.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.74,1:42:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的情报错误\N{\r原文字幕}You've been misinformed.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.99,1:42:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国迟早会有核武\N{\r原文字幕}A Russian bomb is a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.78,1:42:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这项计划在战后必须继续进行\N{\r原文字幕}The program needs to continue at full pace after the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.33,1:42:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史汀生部长 容我发言\N{\r原文字幕}Secretary Stimson, if I may,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.00,1:42:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参与计划的科学家并非意见一致\N{\r原文字幕}not all scientists on the project are in agreement.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.04,1:42:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在应该考虑其他的意见\N{\r原文字幕}In fact, this might be a moment to consider other opinions.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.00,1:42:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学家…\N{\r原文字幕}If you talk--
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.71,1:42:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曼哈顿计划从一开始…\N{\r原文字幕}The Manhattan Project has been plagued from the start
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.42,1:42:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就有口风不紧和不忠贞的科学家参与\N{\r原文字幕}by certain scientists of doubtful discretion and uncertain loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.51,1:42:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中一个想和总统会面\N{\r原文字幕}One of them just tried to meet with the president.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.60,1:42:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要这些人\N{\r原文字幕}Now, we need these men, but as soon as it's practical,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.18,1:42:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但一旦可行 就该将他们踢出计划\N{\r原文字幕}we should sever any such scientists from the program.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.02,1:42:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也同意吧 博士？\N{\r原文字幕}Wouldn't you agree, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.85,1:42:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果俄国一定会有原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}If a Russian bomb is inevitable,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.44,1:42:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许应该邀请他们的顶尖科学家参与\N{\r原文字幕}perhaps we should invite their top scientists to Trinity?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.36,1:42:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜鲁门总统并不打算…\N{\r原文字幕}President Truman has no intention of raising expectations
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.03,1:42:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让史达林参与原子弹计划\N{\r原文字幕}that Stalin be included in the atomic project.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.91,1:42:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告知他我们的进展作为赢得战争的手段\N{\r原文字幕}Informing him of our breakthrough and presenting it as a means to win the war
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.41,1:42:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不必做出无法实现的承诺\N{\r原文字幕}need not make unkeepable promises.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.79,1:42:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是七月的波茨坦和平会议…\N{\r原文字幕}But the Potsdam peace conference in July
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.42,1:42:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将是杜鲁门总统进行对话的最后机会\N{\r原文字幕}will be President Truman's last chance to have that conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.79,1:43:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时候会有实用的炸弹吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Can you give us a working bomb by then?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.67,1:43:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝对会 我们会在会议前进行试爆\N{\r原文字幕}Absolutely.We will test fire before the conference.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.72,1:43:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,观测站位于原爆点9.1公里…\N{\r原文字幕}Ground Zero, observation posts at 10,000
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.85,1:43:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以北、以南及以西\N{\r原文字幕}yards north, south and west.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.15,1:43:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从哪里引爆？\N{\r原文字幕}Where do we trigger from?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.27,1:43:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9.1公里以南\N{\r原文字幕}South, 10,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.44,1:43:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,军事基地位于16公里以南\N{\r原文字幕}And Base Camp is ten miles south here.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.78,1:43:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,32.1公里外的山上还有一个观测站\N{\r原文字幕}And there's a further observation post on--on that hill 20 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.32,1:43:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么？引爆线已经埋好了\N{\r原文字幕}What's that, Frank? Trigger lines already went in.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.04,1:43:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,空军要求为B-29轰炸机提供一排指引灯\N{\r原文字幕}The Air Force requested a line of lights for their B-29.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.71,1:43:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,轰炸机？炸弹被吊在塔台上\N{\r原文字幕}What B-29? Our bomb's on the tower.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.00,1:43:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们想要藉由试爆确认安全距离\N{\r原文字幕}They wanna use the test to confirm a safe operating distance.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.13,1:43:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太危险了\N{\r原文字幕}That's risky.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.05,1:43:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在错估爆炸范围下\N{\r原文字幕}yards north, south and west.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.84,1:43:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对日本投放炸弹会更危险\N{\r原文字幕}and hoping that we were right about the blast radius.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.97,1:43:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别影响进度 我们要在15号试爆\N{\r原文字幕}Don't let them slow us down.We're firing on the 15th.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.22,1:43:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15号？那…  -15号\N{\r原文字幕}The 15th? That's not-- The 15th.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.35,1:43:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15号\N{\r原文字幕}The 15th.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.60,1:43:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会跟弗兰克和基斯在南观测站\N{\r原文字幕}So I'll be here at South Observation point with Frank and Kistiakowsky.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.15,1:44:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们会在基地、西观察站或是远距观察\N{\r原文字幕}You'll all be assigned to Base Camp, West Observation, or Far Observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.45,1:44:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小心点\N{\r原文字幕}Whoa, whoa, whoa! Careful with the knife.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.45,1:44:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小心\N{\r原文字幕}There, carefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.83,1:44:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些距离安全吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Are those safe distances?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.04,1:44:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是根据你的计算\N{\r原文字幕}-They're based on your calculations.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.92,1:44:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的该站在你的计算这一边 汉斯\N{\r原文字幕}Time to stand behind your science, Hans.Literally.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.03,1:44:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.45,1:44:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,辐射云呢？\N{\r原文字幕}What about the radiation cloud?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.33,1:45:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有强风 应该会在3到5公里处消散\N{\r原文字幕}Without high winds, it should settle within two to three miles.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.46,1:45:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,疏散措施到位\N{\r原文字幕}Evacuation measures are in place.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.71,1:45:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要好天气提供能见度 天气一定要好\N{\r原文字幕}But we need good weather for visibility, so it has to be fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.09,1:45:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都出去\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody out.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.43,1:45:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15号晚上进行试爆\N{\r原文字幕}We go on the night of the 15th.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.56,1:45:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是期限 有人有话想说就说\N{\r原文字幕}It's a hard deadline, so if anyone has anything, speak now.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.61,1:45:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 停下来\N{\r原文字幕}Little, little more.Okay, stop, stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.94,1:45:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大伙儿 床垫\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody, mattresses.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.78,1:45:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把床垫铺在底下\N{\r原文字幕}Put the mattress underneath.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.84,1:45:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,应该做最后一次内爆试验\N{\r原文字幕}Could use a final implosion test.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.38,1:45:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会有帮助\N{\r原文字幕}It couldn't hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.89,1:45:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做吧\N{\r原文字幕}-Do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.01,1:45:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有什么能阻止我们？\N{\r原文字幕}Is there anything else that might stop us?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.01,1:46:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的要发生了 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}It's happening, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.72,1:46:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会传个口信\N{\r原文字幕}I'll send a message.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.01,1:46:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果试爆成功…\N{\r原文字幕}If it's gone our way...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.93,1:46:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就来收床单\N{\r原文字幕}take in the sheets.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.15,1:46:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特？\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.32,1:46:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝好运\N{\r原文字幕}Break a leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.93,1:48:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比只估计3千吨威力\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie's taken a very modest three kilotons.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.18,1:48:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒赌4万5千吨  -2万吨\N{\r原文字幕}Teller's in with 45.  -Twenty.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.52,1:48:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2万吨黄色炸弹威力…\N{\r原文字幕}20,000 tons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.89,1:48:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人想另外赌会点燃大气层吗？\N{\r原文字幕}And does anyone want the side action on atmospheric ignition?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.90,1:48:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说必须延期？\N{\r原文字幕}Are you saying we'll have to delay?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.11,1:48:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样比较安全\N{\r原文字幕}-I'm saying it would be prudent.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.15,1:48:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暴风雨到了试爆地点？\N{\r原文字幕}This weather, has it reached the site?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.45,1:48:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贝特打来告诉你内爆试验失败\N{\r原文字幕}Bethe is calling to tell you the implosion test failed.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.50,1:48:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汉斯 他在这里\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Hans.Yes, he's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.21,1:48:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.80,1:48:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他错了吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is he wrong?  -No.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.05,1:48:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错  -没错？\N{\r原文字幕}No?  -No.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.13,1:48:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要引爆哑弹？\N{\r原文字幕}So we're about to fire a dud?  -No.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.05,1:48:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是  -请解释\N{\r原文字幕}Explain.  -Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.80,1:48:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能解释 我就是知道\N{\r原文字幕}I can't.I just--I just know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.10,1:48:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道爆缩透镜会有效\N{\r原文字幕}I know the implosion lenses will work.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.93,1:48:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们点燃引爆器 没有引发连锁反应\N{\r原文字幕}If we fire these detonators and they don't trigger a reaction,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.43,1:48:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两年份量的钚就会散落在沙漠\N{\r原文字幕}two years' worth of plutonium will be scattered across White Sands.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.02,1:48:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用月薪赌你10美元一定会成功\N{\r原文字幕}A month of my salary against ten bucks says it lights.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.90,1:48:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊\N{\r原文字幕}Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.83,1:49:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原爆点风速加快 没下雨\N{\r原文字幕}The wind's picking up at Zero, not the rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.95,1:49:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正在打雷闪电\N{\r原文字幕}Lightning circling.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.25,1:49:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是应该告诉他们…\N{\r原文字幕}You think it might be time to tell your men
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.00,1:49:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,远离吊着原子弹的铁塔吗？\N{\r原文字幕}to get away from the steel tower with the atomic bomb?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.29,1:49:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们去南观测站-叫他们离开\N{\r原文字幕}Let's get to South Observation.  -Pull 'em out.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.67,1:49:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了那里再决定\N{\r原文字幕}We can make our determination there.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.97,1:49:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家有两天没睡觉了\N{\r原文字幕}The team hasn't slept in two nights.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.22,1:49:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在喊停 确保安全 就得再等好几周\N{\r原文字幕}If we stand down, make the bomb safe, we won't be back here for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.52,1:49:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会错过波茨坦会议\N{\r原文字幕}Then we'll miss Potsdam.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.27,1:49:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我七点前得通知杜鲁门 快来不及了\N{\r原文字幕}I gotta get word to Truman by 7:00. Our window's closing.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.27,1:49:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么鬼天气？\N{\r原文字幕}What is this doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.44,1:49:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,刮风下雨和打雷闪电\N{\r原文字幕}Raining, blowing, lightning.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.82,1:49:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会持续多久？\N{\r原文字幕}For how long, damn it?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.94,1:49:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越来越糟\N{\r原文字幕}-It's holdin' strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.07,1:49:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日出前就会停息\N{\r原文字幕}It'll break before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.65,1:49:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么知道？  -我了解这片沙漠\N{\r原文字幕}How could you know that? I know this desert.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.20,1:49:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚上会降温 日出前就会停息\N{\r原文字幕}Storm cools overnight. Just before dawn, the storm breaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.45,1:49:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可能是对的 但尽量延迟时间\N{\r原文字幕}He could be right, but schedule as late as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.75,1:49:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5点30分！\N{\r原文字幕}5:30.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.16,1:49:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,签名保证 你错了我就处决你\N{\r原文字幕}Sign your forecast.If you're wrong, I'll hang you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.58,1:49:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉大家 5点30分\N{\r原文字幕}Frank, tell them all, 5:30.  -5:30.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.17,1:49:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5点30分  -5点30分\N{\r原文字幕}5:30.5:30.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.67,1:50:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3年、4千人、20亿美元\N{\r原文字幕}Three years, 4,000 people, two billion dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.63,1:50:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果没爆炸…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, if it doesn't go off,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.22,1:50:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都完蛋\N{\r原文字幕}we're both finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.27,1:50:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我打赌会是3千吨威力\N{\r原文字幕}I'm betting on three kilotons.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.10,1:50:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,低于3千吨 他们不会知道是什么\N{\r原文字幕}Anything less, they won't get what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.81,1:50:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费米说点燃大气层是什么意思？\N{\r原文字幕}What did Fermi mean by "atmospheric ignition"?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.36,1:50:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们曾经认为…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, we had a moment where it looked like
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.94,1:50:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子弹引发的连锁反应不会停下来\N{\r原文字幕}the chain reaction from an atomic device might never stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.87,1:50:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最后燃烧整个大气层\N{\r原文字幕}Setting fire to the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.58,1:50:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费米为什么还在赌这个？\N{\r原文字幕}Why is Fermi still taking side bets on it?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.62,1:50:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,算是苦中作乐吧\N{\r原文字幕}Call it gallows humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.54,1:50:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说如果我们按下那个按钮有可能…\N{\r原文字幕}Wait, are we saying there's a chance that when we push that button,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.25,1:50:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毁灭整个世界？\N{\r原文字幕}we destroy the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.63,1:50:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这三年来的研究并不能支持这个结论\N{\r原文字幕}Nothing in our research over three years supports that conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.43,1:50:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有非常小的机率\N{\r原文字幕}Except as the most remote possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.06,1:50:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多小？  -机率几乎是零\N{\r原文字幕}How remote?  -Chances are near zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.68,1:50:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎是零？\N{\r原文字幕}Near zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.89,1:50:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,光凭理论你想怎样？\N{\r原文字幕}What do you want from theory alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.07,1:51:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好就是零\N{\r原文字幕}Zero would be nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.49,1:51:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再过…\N{\r原文字幕}In exactly
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.28,1:51:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1小时58分钟…\N{\r原文字幕}one hour, 58 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.66,1:51:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们就会知道\N{\r原文字幕}we'll know.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.17,1:51:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天气变好了\N{\r原文字幕}It's letting up.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.22,1:51:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引爆小组离开原爆点 正回来这里\N{\r原文字幕}The arming party's left Zero, they're heading this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.56,1:51:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开开关\N{\r原文字幕}Throwing the switches.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.64,1:51:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发动车辆 准备进行紧急疏散\N{\r原文字幕}Turn the cars.Ready for emergency evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.12,1:51:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿片黑玻璃 各就各位\N{\r原文字幕}Take your welder's glass. Everybody, take your places.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.38,1:52:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿片黑玻璃！\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody take a welder's glass!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.96,1:52:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都拿片黑玻璃\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody take a welder's glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.10,1:52:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,20分钟\N{\r原文字幕}Twenty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.48,1:53:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,20分钟\N{\r原文字幕}Twenty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.03,1:53:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有20分钟\N{\r原文字幕}That's 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.79,1:53:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放在腿上\N{\r原文字幕}On the leg, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.33,1:53:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费曼  -不用了\N{\r原文字幕}Feynman.No.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.92,1:53:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,黑玻璃能阻隔紫外线\N{\r原文字幕}For your eyes, sir.The glass stops the UV.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.96,1:53:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么能阻隔黑玻璃？\N{\r原文字幕}And what stops the glass?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.34,1:53:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去基地 祝你好运\N{\r原文字幕}I'm gonna head to Base Camp.Best of luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.76,1:53:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.18,1:53:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽量不要毁灭世界\N{\r原文字幕}try not to blow up the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.48,1:53:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盯着仪表针\N{\r原文字幕}Watch that needle.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.86,1:53:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果引爆器无法充电\N{\r原文字幕}If the detonators don't charge,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.36,1:53:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是电压降到一伏特以下\N{\r原文字幕}or the voltage drops below one volt,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.28,1:53:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就按下按钮中止试爆\N{\r原文字幕}you hit that button, you abort.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.45,1:53:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明白吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Understood?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.58,1:53:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明白\N{\r原文字幕}Understood.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.13,1:54:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两分钟后引爆\N{\r原文字幕}Two minutes to detonation.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:07.50,1:54:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家趴下来\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody down.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.63,1:54:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到山上反射的光之前不要转身\N{\r原文字幕}Do not turn around until you see light reflected on the hills.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.68,1:54:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后只能通过黑玻璃观察爆炸\N{\r原文字幕}Then look at the explosion only through your welder's glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.68,1:54:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,90秒后引爆\N{\r原文字幕}Ninety seconds to detonation.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.93,1:54:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,90秒后引爆\N{\r原文字幕}Eighty seconds to detonation.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.10,1:54:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都擦到了吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is it rubbed in?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.11,1:54:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.74,1:54:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,60秒后引爆\N{\r原文字幕}Sixty seconds to detonation.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.46,1:54:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种事令人心情沉重\N{\r原文字幕}These things are hard on your heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.80,1:54:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,30秒\N{\r原文字幕}Thirty seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.56,1:55:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引爆器已充电\N{\r原文字幕}Detonator's charged.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.15,1:55:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\r原文字幕}17, 16,\N{\r原文字幕}17、16
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.32,1:55:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15...\N{\r原文字幕}15
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.78,1:55:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,14,\N{\r原文字幕}14
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.91,1:55:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,13,\N{\r原文字幕}13
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.53,1:55:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,12,\N{\r原文字幕}12
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.12,1:55:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,11...\N{\r原文字幕}11
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.87,1:55:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten...\N{\r原文字幕}10
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.87,1:55:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...nine,\N{\r原文字幕}9
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.29,1:55:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,eight...\N{\r原文字幕}8
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.21,1:55:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,seven...\N{\r原文字幕}7
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.84,1:55:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,six...\N{\r原文字幕}6
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.55,1:55:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,five...\N{\r原文字幕}5
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.43,1:55:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,four...\N{\r原文字幕}4
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.18,1:55:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,three...\N{\r原文字幕}3
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.47,1:55:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,two...\N{\r原文字幕}2
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.18,1:55:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1\N{\r原文字幕}one.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.82,1:57:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在成了死神\N{\r原文字幕}"And now I am become Death."
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.66,1:57:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界的毁灭者\N{\r原文字幕}"The destroyer of worlds."
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.74,1:58:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成功了\N{\r原文字幕}It worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.56,1:58:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你欠我十块钱！\N{\r原文字幕}You owe me ten dollars! Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.61,1:58:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给钱！  -我说到做到\N{\r原文字幕}Come on! I--I'm good for it, Kisty.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.36,1:58:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是真的\N{\r原文字幕}You are.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.28,1:58:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说到做到了！\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, you are!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.60,1:59:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们成功了！\N{\r原文字幕}We did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.23,1:59:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做得好\N{\r原文字幕}Well done.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:25.03,1:59:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上打去波茨坦  -是的\N{\r原文字幕}Get me Potsdam right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:38.33,1:59:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,捎个口信给琪蒂\N{\r原文字幕}Get a message to Kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.00,1:59:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们什么都不能说\N{\r原文字幕}We can't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:41.00,1:59:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫她去收床单\N{\r原文字幕}Tell her to take in the sheets.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.15,1:59:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂？\N{\r原文字幕}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:59.15,2:00:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂？  -什么？夏绿蒂…\N{\r原文字幕}-Hi.Kitty? What--What? Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.52,2:00:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏绿蒂 说吧\N{\r原文字幕}Charlotte, go ahead, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.65,2:00:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不清楚 他只叫你去收床单\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, um, well, I don't know, he just said to tell you to "bring in the sheets."
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.37,2:00:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂？\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:12.87,2:00:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂？你还在吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty? Kitty, are you still there?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.54,2:00:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果在高空引爆 爆炸威力就会减弱\N{\r原文字幕}If they detonate it too high in the air, the blast won't be as powerful.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:26.01,2:00:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士 我们会接手\N{\r原文字幕}With respect, Dr.Oppenheimer, we'll take it from here.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:40.19,2:00:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜鲁门在波茨坦向史达林做了简报吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did Truman brief Stalin at Potsdam?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:43.07,2:00:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,简报是夸大其词\N{\r原文字幕}A brief would be an overstatement.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:45.73,2:00:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只提到一种强大的新武器\N{\r原文字幕}He referred to a powerful new weapon.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:49.91,2:00:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史达林希望我们用来对付日本\N{\r原文字幕}Stalin hoped we'd use it against Japan.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.12,2:00:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就这样？\N{\r原文字幕}That's it?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:57.79,2:01:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们给了他们张王牌 出不出要看他们\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, we've given them an ace, it's for them to play the hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.34,2:01:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日标是六号？\N{\r原文字幕}You're aiming for the 6th?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:05.55,2:01:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是太平洋战争总司令的决定\N{\r原文字幕}Well, it's up to the CO in the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:09.22,2:01:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我该陪你去华府吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Should I come with you to Washington?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.68,2:01:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没这个必要\N{\r原文字幕}What for?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:16.27,2:01:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你要让我知道\N{\r原文字幕}Well, you'll keep me informed.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:19.27,2:01:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了\N{\r原文字幕}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:22.52,2:01:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会尽量\N{\r原文字幕}As best I can.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:41.79,2:01:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日本人知道我们有原子弹会投降吗\N{\r原文字幕}Would the Japanese surrender if they knew what was coming?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:45.67,2:01:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:49.63,2:01:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看了西拉德的请愿书吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Have you seen Szilard's petition?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:51.72,2:01:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,西拉德对日本人了解多少？\N{\r原文字幕}What the hell does Szilard know about the Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:54.47,2:01:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不会签署吧？\N{\r原文字幕}You're not signing it, are you?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:56.51,2:01:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多人都签署了 很多人\N{\r原文字幕}Many people have.A lot of people have.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:58.97,2:01:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华…\N{\r原文字幕}Edward,
Dialogue: 0,2:02:01.60,2:02:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然我们制造出原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}the fact that we built this bomb
Dialogue: 0,2:02:03.06,2:02:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不代表我们比其他人拥有更多权利\N{\r原文字幕}does not give us any more right or responsibility
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.27,2:02:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或责任决定如何使用它\N{\r原文字幕}to decide how it's used than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:08.57,2:02:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但只有我们知情\N{\r原文字幕}But we're the only people who know about it.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:11.07,2:02:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把我们的各种意见告诉史汀生\N{\r原文字幕}I've told Stimson the various opinions of the community.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:13.95,2:02:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你的意见是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}But what's your opinion?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:16.83,2:02:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦使用了它\N{\r原文字幕}Once it's used...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:19.41,2:02:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,核战 也许所有的战争…\N{\r原文字幕}nuclear war, perhaps all war...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.58,2:02:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都不会再发生\N{\r原文字幕}becomes unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:26.46,2:02:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到有人制造更大的炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}Until somebody builds a bigger bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:49.65,2:02:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说会打来\N{\r原文字幕}I thought they would call.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:51.28,2:02:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天只是五号\N{\r原文字幕}It's only the 5th.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:55.11,2:02:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在日本是六号\N{\r原文字幕}In Japan, it's the 6th.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:10.05,2:03:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏绿蒂\N{\r原文字幕}Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:13.59,2:03:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打给格罗夫斯\N{\r原文字幕}Try Groves.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:16.18,2:03:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有消息吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Anything?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:19.76,2:03:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夏绿蒂？\N{\r原文字幕}Charlotte?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:20.76,2:03:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜鲁门在电台广播\N{\r原文字幕}Truman's on the radio.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:23.43,2:03:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,16小时前\N{\r原文字幕}Sixteen hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:26.31,2:03:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一架美国飞机在广岛投下一颗炸弹\N{\r原文字幕}an American airplane dropped one bomb on Hiroshima...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:33.07,2:03:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摧毁该城市对敌方的用途\N{\r原文字幕}...and destroyed its usefulness to the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.41,2:03:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,炸弹的威力超过2万吨黄色炸药\N{\r原文字幕}The bomb had more power than 20,000 tons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:46.37,2:03:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是一颗原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}It is an atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:51.09,2:03:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它驾驭了宇宙的基本力量\N{\r原文字幕}It is a harnessing of the basic power of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:57.97,2:03:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格罗夫斯在一线\N{\r原文字幕}Groves on one.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:59.05,2:04:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们准备尽快彻底摧毁日本的…\N{\r原文字幕}We are now prepared to destroy, more rapidly and completely, the Japanese--
Dialogue: 0,2:04:05.27,2:04:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少将？\N{\r原文字幕}General?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:06.35,2:04:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为你和所有人感到骄傲\N{\r原文字幕}I'm very proud of you and all of your people.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:09.23,2:04:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切都顺利？\N{\r原文字幕}It went all right?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:10.81,2:04:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它很显然造成巨大的爆炸\N{\r原文字幕}Apparently, it went with a tremendous bang.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:14.40,2:04:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\N{\r原文字幕}Well,
Dialogue: 0,2:04:15.53,2:04:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的每个人都觉得很不错\N{\r原文字幕}everyone here is feeling reasonably good about it.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:19.82,2:04:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一条漫长的路\N{\r原文字幕}It's been a long road.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:21.66,2:04:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这辈子做过最明智的决定\N{\r原文字幕}I think one of the wisest things I ever did
Dialogue: 0,2:04:23.87,2:04:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是挑选洛斯阿拉莫斯的负责人\N{\r原文字幕}was when I selected the director of Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:29.79,2:04:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们花了…\N{\r原文字幕}We have spent
Dialogue: 0,2:04:31.29,2:04:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,二十多亿美元…\N{\r原文字幕}more than two billion dollars
Dialogue: 0,2:04:34.00,2:04:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投注在史上最伟大的科学豪赌…\N{\r原文字幕}on the greatest scientific gamble in history,
Dialogue: 0,2:04:38.13,2:04:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们赌赢了\N{\r原文字幕}and we have won.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:44.72,2:04:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥比…奥比…\N{\r原文字幕}Oppie! Oppie! Oppie! Oppie!
Dialogue: 0,2:06:08.35,2:06:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全世界…\N{\r原文字幕}The world...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:11.39,2:06:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将永远记得这一天\N{\r原文字幕}will remember this day.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:31.91,2:06:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在还太早…\N{\r原文字幕}It's too soon to--
Dialogue: 0,2:06:34.21,2:06:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无法判断轰炸的结果是什么\N{\r原文字幕}It's too soon to determine what the results of the bombing are.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:41.13,2:06:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我打赌日本人并不喜欢\N{\r原文字幕}But I'll bet the Japanese didn't like it.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:03.65,2:07:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感到无比骄傲\N{\r原文字幕}I'm so proud.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:06.36,2:07:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对你们的成就深感骄傲\N{\r原文字幕}So proud of what you have accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:16.08,2:07:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只希望能及时用来对付德国人\N{\r原文字幕}I just wish we had it in time to use against the Germans.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:08.45,2:09:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士？\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:10.86,2:09:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士？\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:13.33,2:09:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很棒的照片\N{\r原文字幕}Nice picture.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:15.04,2:09:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜鲁门总统可以接见你了\N{\r原文字幕}President Truman will see you now.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:31.05,2:09:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士 幸会了\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.It's an honor.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:33.89,2:09:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统先生\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.President.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:34.89,2:09:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请坐\N{\r原文字幕}Please.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:35.85,2:09:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:37.56,2:09:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国务卿伯恩斯\N{\r原文字幕}Secretary Byrnes.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:41.39,2:09:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为全世界最有名的人是什么感觉？\N{\r原文字幕}How's it feel to be the most famous man in the world?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:45.44,2:09:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮助拯救很多美国人的性命\N{\r原文字幕}You helped save a lot of American lives.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:48.69,2:09:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在广岛投放的原子弹…\N{\r原文字幕}What we did at Hiroshima was a--
Dialogue: 0,2:09:51.40,2:09:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有长崎\N{\r原文字幕}And Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:53.78,2:09:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了\N{\r原文字幕}Well, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:56.03,2:09:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的发明让我们把国军兄弟带回家\N{\r原文字幕}Your invention let us bring our boys home.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:59.08,2:10:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是我的发明\N{\r原文字幕}Well, it was hardly...my invention.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:02.50,2:10:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你登上《时代杂志》封面\N{\r原文字幕}It was you on the cover of Time.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:07.59,2:10:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉姆说你担心美国与苏联的军备竞赛\N{\r原文字幕}Jim tells me you're concerned about an arms race with the Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:11.47,2:10:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, yes, uh...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:14.01,2:10:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:15.43,2:10:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们的机会确保…\N{\r原文字幕}It's that, uh, now is our chance to secure...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:20.73,2:10:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国际原子能的合作\N{\r原文字幕}international cooperation on......atomic energy
Dialogue: 0,2:10:23.60,2:10:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很担心…\N{\r原文字幕}a-a-and I'm concerned--
Dialogue: 0,2:10:25.90,2:10:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道苏联何时会有原子弹吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you know when the Soviets are gonna have the bomb?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:28.98,2:10:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定能够…\N{\r原文字幕}I don't think I could give a precise--
Dialogue: 0,2:10:30.78,2:10:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永远都不会\N{\r原文字幕}Never.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:32.86,2:10:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永远都不会\N{\r原文字幕}Never.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:34.49,2:10:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统先生 俄国有优秀的物理学家…\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.President, the Russians have good physicists
Dialogue: 0,2:10:38.03,2:10:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及丰富的资源\N{\r原文字幕}a-a-and abundant resources.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:39.41,2:10:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丰富？\N{\r原文字幕}Abundant?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:40.70,2:10:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:42.37,2:10:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不这么认为\N{\r原文字幕}I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:44.42,2:10:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会投入所有的资源…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, they'll put everything they have in...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:51.76,2:10:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说你要离开洛斯阿拉莫斯\N{\r原文字幕}I hear you're leaving Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:56.68,2:10:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们该怎么处理那地方？\N{\r原文字幕}What should we do with it?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:58.18,2:11:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,归还给印第安人\N{\r原文字幕}Give it back to the Indians.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:08.98,2:11:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Um, Dr.Oppenheimer,
Dialogue: 0,2:11:11.19,2:11:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你关于苏联的说法是真的…\N{\r原文字幕}if what you say about the Soviets is true,
Dialogue: 0,2:11:14.32,2:11:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就必须扩建洛斯阿拉莫斯实验室\N{\r原文字幕}we have to build up Los Alamos,
Dialogue: 0,2:11:17.16,2:11:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是关闭它\N{\r原文字幕}not shut it down.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:22.29,2:11:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统先生…\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.President...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:29.17,2:11:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得我的双手沾满了鲜血\N{\r原文字幕}I feel that I have blood on my hands.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:52.57,2:11:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为广岛或是长崎的任何人…\N{\r原文字幕}You think anyone in Hiroshima or Nagasaki
Dialogue: 0,2:11:57.86,2:12:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在乎谁制造了原子弹？\N{\r原文字幕}gives a shit who built the bomb?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:04.45,2:12:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只在乎是谁投放的\N{\r原文字幕}They care who dropped it.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:07.33,2:12:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是我\N{\r原文字幕}I did.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:11.29,2:12:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,广岛的核爆与你无关\N{\r原文字幕}Hiroshima isn't about you.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:20.18,2:12:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:33.02,2:12:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别让那个爱哭鬼再回来\N{\r原文字幕}Don't let that crybaby back in here.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:40.95,2:12:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特发现他的忧虑毫无作用\N{\r原文字幕}Robert saw that hand-wringing got him nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:44.91,2:12:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我见到他的时候…\N{\r原文字幕}By the time I met him, he'd fully embraced
Dialogue: 0,2:12:46.25,2:12:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他完全接受“原子弹之父”的响亮名气\N{\r原文字幕}his "father of the bomb" reputation.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:50.08,2:12:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且用来影响政府政策\N{\r原文字幕}And he used his profile to influence policy.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:01.68,2:13:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,博士 在战后的几年内…\N{\r原文字幕}Doctor, in the years following the war,
Dialogue: 0,2:13:03.18,2:13:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否对美国原子能政策造成重大影响？\N{\r原文字幕}would you say that you exerted a great influence on the atomic policies of the USA?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:07.39,2:13:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不至于到重大影响\N{\r原文字幕}I think "great" would be an overstatement.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:10.02,2:13:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗？看看同位素的事件…\N{\r原文字幕}Really? If we look at the issue of isotopes,
Dialogue: 0,2:13:11.94,2:13:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你难道没有逼迫反对出口的人噤声？\N{\r原文字幕}were you not personally responsible for destroying all opposition to their export?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:15.65,2:13:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一瓶啤酒都能用来制造核武 是真的\N{\r原文字幕}You could use a bottle of beer... ...when making atomic weapons. In fact, you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:20.49,2:13:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是发言人 科学界的意见一致\N{\r原文字幕}I was the spokesman, but the opinion among scientists was unanimous.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:24.58,2:13:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当麦卡锡主义崛起 他知道会被殃及\N{\r原文字幕}All along with McCarthy on the rise, he knew he was vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:28.45,2:13:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他弟弟被全国大学列入黑名单\N{\r原文字幕}His brother was blacklisted by every university in the country.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:33.63,2:13:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洛马尼茨后来替铁路公司铺铁轨\N{\r原文字幕}Lomanitz wound up working the railroad, laying track.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:38.51,2:13:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薛瓦利埃则流亡海外\N{\r原文字幕}And Chevalier went into exile.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:43.14,2:13:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这没阻止罗伯特逼迫总顾问委员会\N{\r原文字幕}But none of that stopped Robert from pushing the GAC
Dialogue: 0,2:13:46.51,2:13:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,建议军备控制而不是制造氢弹\N{\r原文字幕}to recommend arms control instead of the H-bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:51.31,2:13:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当杜鲁门拒绝这项建议 他深受打击\N{\r原文字幕}He was devastated when Truman rejected their recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:56.69,2:13:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我太想念理查德了\N{\r原文字幕}I miss Richard more than I can bear.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:59.11,2:14:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 露丝\N{\r原文字幕}I know, Ruth, I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:00.57,2:14:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很高兴他没活着看到这种发展\N{\r原文字幕}Part of me's glad he didn't live to see where this is all going.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:06.95,2:14:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寿星来了\N{\r原文字幕}Here comes the birthday boy.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:08.54,2:14:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洋洋得意  -玩得开心\N{\r原文字幕}To gloat. Have fun.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:11.92,2:14:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 我儿子和他未婚妻很想见到\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, uh, my son and his fiancée are desperate to meet
Dialogue: 0,2:14:14.46,2:14:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子弹之父\N{\r原文字幕}the father of the atomic bomb, and so...
Dialogue: 0,2:14:16.42,2:14:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝你愉快\N{\r原文字幕}Well...good day.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:25.18,2:14:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,心情不好？\N{\r原文字幕}Is this a bad time?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:27.51,2:14:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说呢 路易斯？\N{\r原文字幕}What do you think, Lewis?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:29.22,2:14:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这对你一定是很大的打击\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I think it must have been a blow for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:31.43,2:14:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对全世界也是\N{\r原文字幕}For the world.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:34.10,2:14:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全世界？富赫斯对全世界有何重要？\N{\r原文字幕}The world? What does Fuchs mean to the rest of the world?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:38.52,2:14:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,富赫斯？\N{\r原文字幕}Fuchs?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:40.24,2:14:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克劳斯富赫斯？\N{\r原文字幕}Klaus Fuchs?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:43.28,2:14:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是的 你还没听说\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, dear.You haven't heard.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:48.70,2:14:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英国科学家克劳斯富赫斯\N{\r原文字幕}Klaus Fuchs, the British scientist
Dialogue: 0,2:14:50.79,2:14:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你让他参与内爆式炸弹研究\N{\r原文字幕}that you put onto the implosion team at Los Alamos,
Dialogue: 0,2:14:54.75,2:14:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原来他是…\N{\r原文字幕} turns out he was
Dialogue: 0,2:14:56.25,2:14:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他一直都是苏联派去的间谍\N{\r原文字幕}spying for the Soviets the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:59.34,2:15:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很遗憾\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.14,2:15:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,富赫斯的身分被揭露之后…\N{\r原文字幕}After the truth about Fuchs came out,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.01,2:15:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,联邦调查局加强对他的监视\N{\r原文字幕}the FBI stepped up surveillance on him.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:11.22,2:15:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他知道电话被窃听\N{\r原文字幕}He knew his phone was tapped,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:13.77,2:15:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去那里都被跟踪\N{\r原文字幕}he was followed everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:16.35,2:15:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的垃圾也被翻遍\N{\r原文字幕}his trash picked through.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:21.73,2:15:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他却仍然仗义直言\N{\r原文字幕}But never stopped speaking his mind.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:23.90,2:15:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他具有坚定信念\N{\r原文字幕}-A man of conviction.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:26.03,2:15:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他以为他的名气能保护他\N{\r原文字幕}And maybe he thought fame could actually protect him.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:30.83,2:15:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾森豪上任后 他又看到一次机会\N{\r原文字幕}When Eisenhower took office, he saw one more chance.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:35.33,2:15:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,决定把握机会\N{\r原文字幕}He took it.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:36.33,2:15:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国和俄国\N{\r原文字幕}America and Russia
Dialogue: 0,2:15:38.63,2:15:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以比喻成\N{\r原文字幕}may be likened to
Dialogue: 0,2:15:40.88,2:15:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瓶子里的两只蠍子\N{\r原文字幕}two scorpions in a bottle,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:43.05,2:15:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都有能力杀死对方\N{\r原文字幕}each capable of killing the other,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:46.47,2:15:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但只能冒着自己的生命危险\N{\r原文字幕}but only at the risk of his own life.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:49.97,2:15:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这项政策有许多面向…\N{\r原文字幕}Now, there are various aspects of this policy--
Dialogue: 0,2:15:52.02,2:15:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有很多科学家责怪我 但…\N{\r原文字幕}Lot of scientists blame me,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:55.06,2:15:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我该怎么保护他？\N{\r原文字幕}but how was I supposed to protect him?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:57.10,2:15:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…为了保密不肯谈判\N{\r原文字幕}...are too secret for discussion,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:59.02,2:16:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开诚布公是唯一的解决方法\N{\r原文字幕}candor is the only remedy.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:01.11,2:16:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,华府官员必须开始向美国人民说实话\N{\r原文字幕}Officials in Washington need to start leveling with the American people.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:06.07,2:16:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是压垮他的最后一根稻草\N{\r原文字幕}That was the last straw for Robert's enemies.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:08.87,2:16:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那让他失去他的安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}So he had to lose his security clearance?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:11.08,2:16:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也让他名誉扫地\N{\r原文字幕}And with it, his credibility.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:13.75,2:16:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政府怎么能这么对他？\N{\r原文字幕}But how could they do it?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:16.04,2:16:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是战争英雄 也交代了他的过去\N{\r原文字幕}He was a war hero.He'd already told everyone about his past.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:19.25,2:16:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波登又翻他的旧帐\N{\r原文字幕}Borden dredged it all up.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:21.38,2:16:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波登怎么会拿到奥本海默的安全档案\N{\r原文字幕}How could Borden get access to Oppenheimer's FBI file?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:24.71,2:16:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼柯斯给他的？\N{\r原文字幕}Could it have been Nichols?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:26.13,2:16:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 他不会那么做\N{\r原文字幕}No, I can't imagine he'd do that.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:28.43,2:16:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这掀起了一场腥风血雨\N{\r原文字幕}But whoever did unleashed a firestorm
Dialogue: 0,2:16:30.51,2:16:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从白宫一直延烧到原子委员会\N{\r原文字幕}that burned a path from the White House back to my desk at the AEC.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:35.56,2:16:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也看到他们吧？\N{\r原文字幕}You see him in there, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:37.69,2:16:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我努力一辈子达到今天的地位\N{\r原文字幕}I've worked my whole life to get here,
Dialogue: 0,2:16:41.02,2:16:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为美国政府内阁成员\N{\r原文字幕}Cabinet of the United States of America,
Dialogue: 0,2:16:43.36,2:16:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在他们要在全国人民面前\N{\r原文字幕}and now, in front of the entire country,
Dialogue: 0,2:16:45.19,2:16:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狠狠地把我打回原形\N{\r原文字幕}they're gonna put me back in my place.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:48.57,2:16:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个低微的鞋类销售员\N{\r原文字幕}A lowly shoe salesman.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:51.20,2:16:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,路易斯 我们可以赢\N{\r原文字幕}Lewis, we can win this thing.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:53.24,2:16:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能让参议院知道你恪守职责\N{\r原文字幕}I-I think we can get the Senate to grasp that you did your duty,
Dialogue: 0,2:16:56.41,2:16:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然非常煎熬\N{\r原文字幕}painful though it was.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:58.12,2:16:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔的证词靠得住吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Now, will Hill's testimony back us up?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:59.83,2:17:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不会是问题  -我不认识他\N{\r原文字幕}Hill will be fine. I don't really know him,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:01.75,2:17:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他是西拉德在芝加哥的手下\N{\r原文字幕}but he was one of Szilard's boys in Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:04.05,2:17:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们一直不原谅罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}and they never forgave Robert
Dialogue: 0,2:17:05.59,2:17:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有支持反对轰炸日本的请愿书\N{\r原文字幕}for not supporting the petition against bombing Japan.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:09.22,2:17:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是轰炸后31天拍摄的\N{\r原文字幕}This was taken 31 days after the bombing.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:13.68,2:17:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,方圆1.6公里的每个人…\N{\r原文字幕}Virtually everyone in the street for nearly a mile around
Dialogue: 0,2:17:18.73,2:17:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都立刻遭到严重灼烧\N{\r原文字幕}was instantly and seriously burned.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:23.02,2:17:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日本人提到只要穿条纹衣服…\N{\r原文字幕}The Japanese spoke of people who wore striped clothing
Dialogue: 0,2:17:27.69,2:17:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身上都留下条纹状的灼伤\N{\r原文字幕}upon whom the skin was burned in stripes.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:31.70,2:17:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多人以为自己很幸运…\N{\r原文字幕}There were many who thought themselves lucky,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:34.45,2:17:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从废墟中爬出来只受到轻伤\N{\r原文字幕}who climbed out of the ruins of their homes, only slightly injured.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:40.00,2:17:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们仍难逃一死\N{\r原文字幕}But they died anyway.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:42.50,2:17:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在几天或几周后\N{\r原文字幕}They died days or weeks later from the radium-like rays
Dialogue: 0,2:17:45.67,2:17:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为暴露在爆炸瞬间散发的…\N{\r原文字幕}emitted in great numbers at the moment
Dialogue: 0,2:17:48.92,2:17:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,镭放射线而死\N{\r原文字幕}of the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:52.43,2:17:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在报纸上看到这种屁话？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you read this crap in the papers?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:54.35,2:17:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一位英国物理学家说原爆\N{\r原文字幕}A British physicist is saying the atomic bombings were
Dialogue: 0,2:17:56.97,2:17:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是二次大战的尾声\N{\r原文字幕}not the last act of World War II,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:59.31,2:18:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是与俄国冷战的序幕\N{\r原文字幕}but the first act of this cold war with Russia.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:02.77,2:18:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪位物理学家？\N{\r原文字幕}Which physicist?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:03.90,2:18:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该认识他\N{\r原文字幕}I think you knew him.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:05.31,2:18:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕特里克·布莱克特\N{\r原文字幕}Patrick Blackett.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:09.61,2:18:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也许没说错\N{\r原文字幕}He may not be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:10.90,2:18:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史汀生现在告诉我…\N{\r原文字幕}Stimson is now telling me
Dialogue: 0,2:18:12.57,2:18:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们轰炸已经被打败的敌人\N{\r原文字幕}we bombed an enemy that was essentially defeated.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:15.74,2:18:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 你有这么大的影响力\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, you've all the influence now.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:19.20,2:18:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托了\N{\r原文字幕}Please.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:20.91,2:18:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请他们继续我对氢弹的研究\N{\r原文字幕}Urge them to continue my research on the Super.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:23.21,2:18:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能也不会这么做\N{\r原文字幕}I neither can nor will, Edward.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:25.29,2:18:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:26.67,2:18:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不该这么使用我们的资源\N{\r原文字幕}It's not the right use of our resources.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:28.84,2:18:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真的这么相信？\N{\r原文字幕}Is that what you really believe?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:31.17,2:18:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,J·罗伯特·奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}J.Robert Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:33.13,2:18:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谜一般的原子弹之父\N{\r原文字幕}Sphinx-like guru of the atom.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:36.55,2:18:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人知道你相信什么\N{\r原文字幕}Nobody knows what you believe.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:39.35,2:18:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自己知道吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:41.64,2:18:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请最后一次欢迎计划主任奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}One final time, our program director, Dr.J.Robert Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:47.40,2:18:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望在未来的岁月…\N{\r原文字幕}I hope that, in years to come,
Dialogue: 0,2:18:49.73,2:18:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位会骄傲地回顾这里的研究工作\N{\r原文字幕}you will look back on your work here with pride.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:53.07,2:18:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但今天这份骄傲伴随着深切的忧虑\N{\r原文字幕}But today that pride must be tempered with a profound concern.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:59.12,2:19:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,核武若被加入这个好战世界的军火库\N{\r原文字幕}If atomic weapons are to be added to the arsenals of a warring world,
Dialogue: 0,2:19:04.33,2:19:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一天世人将诅咒洛斯阿拉莫斯这名字\N{\r原文字幕}then the day will come when people will curse the name of Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:12.92,2:19:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 少将\N{\r原文字幕}Sorry, Admiral.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:14.51,2:19:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我出去买了这个\N{\r原文字幕}Stopped off to get this.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:17.72,2:19:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,似乎对你有利\N{\r原文字幕}It seems pretty favorable.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:19.26,2:19:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,文章提到奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}There's Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:20.52,2:19:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,标题是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What's the caption?
Dialogue: 0,2:19:22.39,2:19:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯杠上罗伯特·奥本海默…\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, "J.Robert Oppenheimer, Strauss fought...
Dialogue: 0,2:19:26.48,2:19:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国赢了\N{\r原文字幕}and the US won."
Dialogue: 0,2:19:29.07,2:19:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样也行\N{\r原文字幕}That'll work.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:30.48,2:19:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是你前几天说的话\N{\r原文字幕}Those were your words from the other day.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:32.44,2:19:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须掌握先机\N{\r原文字幕}We needed to pivot.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:34.32,2:19:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么知道《时代杂志》会写什么？\N{\r原文字幕}But how would you know what Time magazine's gonna write?
Dialogue: 0,2:19:37.16,2:19:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利鲁斯是个朋友\N{\r原文字幕}Henry Luce is a friend.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:46.58,2:19:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你坐在这里让我下指导棋\N{\r原文字幕}You sat here and let me tell you how it's done,
Dialogue: 0,2:19:49.63,2:19:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却比我早下几步棋\N{\r原文字幕}but you've been far ahead all along.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:51.84,2:19:56.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,华府的生存法则就是了解游戏规则\N{\r原文字幕}Survival in Washington is about knowing how to get things done.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:57.68,2:19:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}Right.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:00.72,2:20:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是怎么说波登的？\N{\r原文字幕}What was it you said about Borden?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:02.81,2:20:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想要借刀杀人\N{\r原文字幕}"Why get caught holding the knife yourself?"
Dialogue: 0,2:20:06.98,2:20:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我开始觉得你是借波登的刀杀人\N{\r原文字幕}I'm beginning to think Borden was holding the knife for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:12.78,2:20:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最后要看波登对泰勒有多大的影响\N{\r原文字幕}It's gonna come down to how much influence Borden's been able to exert on Teller.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:17.86,2:20:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的话很可笑吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did I say something funny?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:19.32,2:20:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都一直说是波登\N{\r原文字幕}Just "Borden, Borden, Borden"
Dialogue: 0,2:20:20.53,2:20:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其实大家都知道是史特劳斯搞的鬼\N{\r原文字幕}when we all know that it's Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:24.54,2:20:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,路易斯把我带到普林斯顿 琪蒂\N{\r原文字幕}Lewis brought me to Princeton, Kitty.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:26.66,2:20:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后你在国会面前羞辱了他\N{\r原文字幕}And then you humiliated him in front of Congress.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:29.29,2:20:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是比三明治更有用\N{\r原文字幕}But more useful than a sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:35.05,2:20:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,够狠吧？  -休会十分钟\N{\r原文字幕}How'd I do?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:37.30,2:20:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许太狠了 罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Maybe a little too well, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:39.72,2:20:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是六年前的事\N{\r原文字幕}That was six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:40.93,2:20:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真正会记仇的小人…\N{\r原文字幕}You know the truly vindictive,
Dialogue: 0,2:20:42.81,2:20:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟圣人一样有耐心\N{\r原文字幕}patient as saints.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:44.43,2:20:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯清楚表明他的中立立场\N{\r原文字幕}Strauss has been perfectly clear that he is neutral.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:48.10,2:20:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,醒醒吧 是史特劳斯在搞鬼\N{\r原文字幕}Wake up! It is Strauss!
Dialogue: 0,2:20:50.73,2:20:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直都是他 你心知肚明\N{\r原文字幕}It's always been Strauss, and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:53.73,2:20:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何不反抗他？\N{\r原文字幕}Why won't you fight him?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:56.24,2:20:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老天爷\N{\r原文字幕}Christ's sake.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:58.65,2:20:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是尼柯斯…\N{\r原文字幕}It wasn't Nichols,
Dialogue: 0,2:21:00.62,2:21:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,胡佛或是杜鲁门的手下 而是你\N{\r原文字幕}or Hoover, or one of Truman's guys. It was you.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:03.95,2:21:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把档案交给波登 让他盯上奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}You gave the file to Borden. You set him on Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:06.91,2:21:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说服他去…  -波登…\N{\r原文字幕}You convinced him to-- Borden
Dialogue: 0,2:21:09.50,2:21:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不需要被说服\N{\r原文字幕}didn't take any convincing.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:11.92,2:21:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢慢来 用整份档案\N{\r原文字幕}Take your time, use the entire file.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:13.75,2:21:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写下你的结论 寄给联邦调查局\N{\r原文字幕}Write up your conclusions, send them to the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:16.13,2:21:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,内容非常广泛 但…\N{\r原文字幕}The material is obviously extensive, but
Dialogue: 0,2:21:19.38,2:21:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有新的资料\N{\r原文字幕}there's nothing new here.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:20.68,2:21:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会有新的结论\N{\r原文字幕}Your conclusions will be.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:22.93,2:21:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也会因此付出代价\N{\r原文字幕}And they'll have to be answered.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:25.43,2:21:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,胡佛把这些结论交给麦卡锡？\N{\r原文字幕}Hoover passes them to McCarthy?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:26.89,2:21:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个跳梁小丑不是奥本海默的对手\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer's too slippery for that self-promoting clown.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:30.23,2:21:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和胡佛商量好了 他会压住麦卡锡…\N{\r原文字幕}I've talked it over with Hoover, he'll hold McCarthy at bay
Dialogue: 0,2:21:33.06,2:21:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让你用原子能委员会对付他\N{\r原文字幕}while you do this with the AEC.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:35.23,2:21:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一场审判？  -不是\N{\r原文字幕}A trial. No.No trial.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:36.82,2:21:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不开庭 不能让奥本海默公开发言\N{\r原文字幕}You can't give Oppenheimer a platform.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:40.32,2:21:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更不能让他当烈士\N{\r原文字幕}You can't martyr him.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:42.32,2:21:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须有系统地摧毁他的信誉\N{\r原文字幕}We need a systematic destruction of Oppenheimer's credibility
Dialogue: 0,2:21:45.58,2:21:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他再也不能谈论国家安全的事务\N{\r原文字幕}so he can never again speak on matters of national security.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:49.75,2:21:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那要怎么做？\N{\r原文字幕}Then what?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:52.38,2:21:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弄个小房间 不对媒体公开\N{\r原文字幕}A shabby little room, far from the limelight.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:01.55,2:22:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个简单的官僚程序\N{\r原文字幕}A simple, bureaucratic procedure.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:03.68,2:22:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要重新申请安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}His Q clearance is up for renewal.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:05.97,2:22:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你的指控寄给联邦调查局\N{\r原文字幕}You send your accusations to the FBI...
Dialogue: 0,2:22:10.89,2:22:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,胡佛再寄给原子能委员会\N{\r原文字幕}Hoover sends them to the AEC,
Dialogue: 0,2:22:12.85,2:22:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不得不采取行动\N{\r原文字幕}you're forced to act.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:15.02,2:22:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写一份起诉书…\N{\r原文字幕}You write up an indictment.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:16.48,2:22:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉奥本海默他的安全许可没被批准\N{\r原文字幕}You tell Oppenheimer his security clearance is not being renewed.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:20.95,2:22:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是给他上诉的机会\N{\r原文字幕}But offer him the chance to appeal.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:22.45,2:22:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也看到 罗伯特 这还没签名\N{\r原文字幕}As you can see, Robert, it's not yet signed.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:24.99,2:22:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能留着吗？\N{\r原文字幕}May I keep this?
Dialogue: 0,2:22:26.20,2:22:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:27.28,2:22:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你若决定上诉 他们就得把副本寄给你\N{\r原文字幕}If you do decide to appeal, they'll have to send you a copy.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:31.37,2:22:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当他提出上诉 相信我 他一定会\N{\r原文字幕}When he appeals, and trust me, he will,
Dialogue: 0,2:22:34.83,2:22:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就任命一个委员会\N{\r原文字幕}I appoint a board.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:36.84,2:22:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们当然会有律师\N{\r原文字幕}They will, of course, have counsel.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:39.55,2:22:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,检察官？  -实质上是的\N{\r原文字幕}Prosecutor?  -In all but name.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:41.38,2:22:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who?
Dialogue: 0,2:22:42.38,2:22:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗杰·罗博\N{\r原文字幕}Roger Robb.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:43.38,2:22:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他够狠\N{\r原文字幕}Ouch.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:44.47,2:22:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会有审阅奥本海默档案的安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}Robb will have security clearance to examine Oppenheimer's file.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:47.76,2:22:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格雷的委员会也会有\N{\r原文字幕}As will the Gray board.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:49.18,2:22:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被告律师不会有\N{\r原文字幕}Defense counsel will not.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:52.27,2:22:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一场秘密听证会\N{\r原文字幕}A closed hearing.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:53.23,2:22:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们对我做出所谓的诋毁性指控…\N{\r原文字幕}"The so-called and derogatory information in your indictment of me..."
Dialogue: 0,2:22:57.36,2:23:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有旁听席 没有记者席\N{\r原文字幕}No audience.No reporters.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:00.11,2:23:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有举证责任\N{\r原文字幕}No burden of proof.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:01.57,2:23:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有举证责任？\N{\r原文字幕}No burden of proof?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:04.61,2:23:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不是定他罪\N{\r原文字幕}We're not convicting.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:07.03,2:23:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是否决他的安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}We're just denying.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:14.33,2:23:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是怎么说的？\N{\r原文字幕}What is it you said?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:17.25,2:23:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只是游戏规则\N{\r原文字幕}"This is just how the game is played."
Dialogue: 0,2:23:21.17,2:23:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我太天真了\N{\r原文字幕}Well, forgive my naivete.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:23.59,2:23:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,追逐名利的外行人\N{\r原文字幕}Amateurs seek the sun...
Dialogue: 0,2:23:26.51,2:23:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会被生吞活剥\N{\r原文字幕}get eaten.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:28.64,2:23:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真正的掌权者不会现身\N{\r原文字幕}Power stays in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:31.85,2:23:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你现在已经现身了\N{\r原文字幕}But, sir, you're out of the shadows now.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:35.31,2:23:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以这一招必须成功\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, that's why this has to work.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:36.81,2:23:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\N{\r原文字幕}Well...
Dialogue: 0,2:23:39.69,2:23:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒今天早上作证\N{\r原文字幕}Teller's testifying this morning.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:41.65,2:23:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那会有帮助 然后…\N{\r原文字幕}That'll help. And then...
Dialogue: 0,2:23:44.15,2:23:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔下午出席作证\N{\r原文字幕}Hill is in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:45.61,2:23:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔也会帮助我们\N{\r原文字幕}Hill is gonna help us too.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:50.37,2:23:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也看到 罗伯特 这还没签名\N{\r原文字幕}As you can see, Robert, it's not yet signed.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:53.54,2:23:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能留着吗？\N{\r原文字幕}May I keep this?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:54.54,2:23:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能\N{\r原文字幕}-No.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:57.71,2:23:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你若决定上诉…\N{\r原文字幕}If you do decide to appeal,
Dialogue: 0,2:23:59.79,2:24:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们就得把副本寄给你\N{\r原文字幕}then they'll have to send you a copy.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:06.09,2:24:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用我的车和司机 我坚持\N{\r原文字幕}Take my car and driver.I insist.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:13.14,2:24:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须谘询我的律师 路易斯\N{\r原文字幕}I'll have to consult my lawyers, Lewis.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:15.06,2:24:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了 但别拖太久\N{\r原文字幕}Of course.But don't take too long.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:17.98,2:24:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我压不住尼柯斯\N{\r原文字幕}I can't keep Nichols at bay.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:26.20,2:24:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很抱歉走到这个地步\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry it's come to this, Robert.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:28.53,2:24:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得是错的\N{\r原文字幕}I think it's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:42.96,2:24:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼柯斯希望我抗辩 好让一切留下记录\N{\r原文字幕}Nichols wants me to fight so he can get it all on the record.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:46.51,2:24:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯要我退让\N{\r原文字幕}Strauss wants me to walk away.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:48.34,2:24:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯知道你不能退让\N{\r原文字幕}Strauss knows that you can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:51.10,2:24:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那等于是承认这些指控\N{\r原文字幕}You'd be accepting the charges.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:53.76,2:24:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会丢掉工作\N{\r原文字幕}You'll lose your job.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:55.35,2:24:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也会名誉扫地\N{\r原文字幕}You will lose your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:56.77,2:24:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会失去我们的房子\N{\r原文字幕}We'll lose our house.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:58.31,2:24:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 我们必须反抗\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, we have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:03.07,2:25:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身为原子能委员会律师 我不能代表你\N{\r原文字幕}As AEC counsel, I can't represent you.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:05.73,2:25:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会打给洛伊德盖里森\N{\r原文字幕}I'll call Lloyd Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:07.49,2:25:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很厉害\N{\r原文字幕}He's good.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:08.53,2:25:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最顶尖的 但…\N{\r原文字幕}-The best, but...
Dialogue: 0,2:25:10.66,2:25:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得警告你…\N{\r原文字幕}I have to warn you,
Dialogue: 0,2:25:13.53,2:25:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这会很不公平\N{\r原文字幕}this won't be a fair fight.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:15.54,2:25:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在1943年和鲍里斯帕什访谈时\N{\r原文字幕}During your interview with Boris Pash in 1943,
Dialogue: 0,2:25:17.41,2:25:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有提到微缩胶片？\N{\r原文字幕}did you refer to microfilm?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:19.87,2:25:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有  -标记11 第1页 第3段\N{\r原文字幕}No.  -Tab 11, page one, paragraph three.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:23.09,2:25:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没说“领事馆有位缩微胶片专家”？\N{\r原文字幕}You never said, "Man of the consulate expert in the use of microfilm."
Dialogue: 0,2:25:26.55,2:25:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起  -没有\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry.  -No.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:27.72,2:25:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道罗博先生引用哪份文件\N{\r原文字幕}I would like to know what document Mr.Robb is quoting from
Dialogue: 0,2:25:30.01,2:25:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们也想拿到副本\N{\r原文字幕}and if we might be furnished with a copy.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:31.93,2:25:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是机密文件 盖里森先生\N{\r原文字幕}The document is classified, Mr.Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:33.89,2:25:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该回到第一手资料\N{\r原文字幕}I think we should get back to firsthand information.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:36.14,2:25:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是第一手资料\N{\r原文字幕}This is firsthand.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:37.52,2:25:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么说 罗杰？\N{\r原文字幕}-How so, Roger?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:40.77,2:25:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是访谈的录音\N{\r原文字幕}There was a recording of the interview.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:47.44,2:25:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的当事人有可能做出伪证…\N{\r原文字幕}You let my client sit here and potentially perjure himself
Dialogue: 0,2:25:49.95,2:25:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你却一直拥有录音档案？\N{\r原文字幕}and all this time, you had a recording?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:52.53,2:25:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人叫你的当事人窜改他之前的回答\N{\r原文字幕}Nobody told your client to misrepresent his former answers.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:55.24,2:25:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,窜改？那是12年前的事\N{\r原文字幕}Misrepres--It was 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:57.58,2:25:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能听这段录音吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Can we hear this recording?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:58.91,2:26:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没有安全许可 盖里森先生\N{\r原文字幕}You don't have the clearance, Mr.Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:00.29,2:26:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你却把它列入记录\N{\r原文字幕}But you're reading it into the record.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:02.21,2:26:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托\N{\r原文字幕}-Please, please.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:03.38,2:26:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场听证会是想诱导犯罪或追求真相？\N{\r原文字幕}Is this proceeding interested in entrapment or in truth?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:07.25,2:26:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是追求真相\N{\r原文字幕}If it's truth,
Dialogue: 0,2:26:08.42,2:26:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,公开证据呢？证人名单呢？\N{\r原文字幕}where's the disclosure?  Where's the witness list?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:11.18,2:26:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盖里森先生 你很清楚这不是审判\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Garrison, this isn't a trial, as you're well aware.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:14.05,2:26:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,证据法则并不适用 这攸关国家安全\N{\r原文字幕}Evidentiary rules do not apply.We are dealing with national security.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:18.22,2:26:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 但恕我直言\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, sir, with all due respect,
Dialogue: 0,2:26:19.39,2:26:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国家安全并不能阻止检方…\N{\r原文字幕}I fail to see how national security prevents the prosecution
Dialogue: 0,2:26:23.52,2:26:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提供证人名单-也许应该暂时休会\N{\r原文字幕}from providing us a list of witnesses. Perhaps we are in need of a brief recess.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:26.07,2:26:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各位 我向你们保证\N{\r原文字幕}Gentlemen, you have my words.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:28.19,2:26:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果这些来自记录副本 我就会接受\N{\r原文字幕}If you say they're from a transcript, then I'll accept it.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:30.99,2:26:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我解释过我编了牛头不对马嘴的故事\N{\r原文字幕}I've already explained I made up a cock-and-bull story.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:33.86,2:26:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么要编出这么复杂的故事？\N{\r原文字幕}But why would anyone make up such an elaborate story?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:37.03,2:26:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我是个白痴\N{\r原文字幕}Because I was an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:39.50,2:26:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要说谎？\N{\r原文字幕}Why lie?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:40.91,2:26:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很显然是不想透露中间人是谁\N{\r原文字幕}Well, clearly with the intention of not revealing who the intermediary was.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:44.92,2:26:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的朋友 共产党员哈肯薛瓦利埃\N{\r原文字幕}Your friend, Haakon Chevalier, the communist?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:47.63,2:26:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还是你的朋友吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is he still your friend?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:49.76,2:26:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:54.13,2:26:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉比博士 谢谢你前来\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Rabi, thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:56.26,2:26:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道检方还传唤了谁吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you know who else the prosecution has called?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:58.26,2:27:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很显然是泰勒\N{\r原文字幕}Teller, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:01.31,2:27:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们问过劳伦斯\N{\r原文字幕}They've asked Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:02.60,2:27:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他怎么说？\N{\r原文字幕}-What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:03.77,2:27:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不打算帮助他们 但是…\N{\r原文字幕}He wasn't going to help them, but...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:06.23,2:27:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是什么？\N{\r原文字幕}-But?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:07.61,2:27:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯跟他说你和露丝托尔曼搞外遇\N{\r原文字幕}Strauss told him that you and Ruth Tolman have been having an affair for years.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:12.19,2:27:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和他们夫妻住在一起的那些年\N{\r原文字幕}The whole time you lived with them in Pasadena.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:14.78,2:27:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他让劳伦斯相信理查德因为伤心而死\N{\r原文字幕}He convinced Lawrence that Richard died of a broken heart.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:18.16,2:27:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那太荒谬了\N{\r原文字幕}That's absurd.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:19.24,2:27:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪一部分？  -伤心而死\N{\r原文字幕}-What part? The broken heart.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:22.04,2:27:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查德从来没有发现\N{\r原文字幕}Richard never found out.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:24.37,2:27:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劳伦斯会作证吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is Lawrence gonna testify?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:26.13,2:27:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:27.79,2:27:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉比博士…\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Rabi,
Dialogue: 0,2:27:29.42,2:27:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你目前担任什么政府职位\N{\r原文字幕}what governmental positions do you currently hold?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:32.67,2:27:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子能委员会总顾问委员会主席\N{\r原文字幕}I am the chairman of the General Advisory Committee to the AEC,
Dialogue: 0,2:27:36.47,2:27:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接替奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}succeeding Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:38.51,2:27:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认识奥本海默博士多久？\N{\r原文字幕}And how long have you known Dr.Oppenheimer?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:41.31,2:27:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自从1928年\N{\r原文字幕}Since 1928.I...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:43.02,2:27:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我非常了解他\N{\r原文字幕}I know him quite well.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:45.52,2:27:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,足以评断他的忠诚度和品格吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Well enough to speak to the bearing of his loyalty and character?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:49.82,2:27:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士是一个品德高尚的人\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer is a man of upstanding character.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:53.90,2:27:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且对美国、他的朋友…\N{\r原文字幕}And he is loyal to the United States, to his friends,
Dialogue: 0,2:27:57.78,2:28:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及工作单位忠心不二\N{\r原文字幕}to the institutions of which he is part.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:01.83,2:28:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吃吧\N{\r原文字幕}Eat.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:22.06,2:28:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么回事？\N{\r原文字幕}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:23.43,2:28:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没什么好担心的\N{\r原文字幕}-Nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:28.06,2:28:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄国试爆原子弹后 劳伦斯博士\N{\r原文字幕}After the Russian A-bomb test, did Dr.Lawrence
Dialogue: 0,2:28:30.98,2:28:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否问过你氢弹的事？\N{\r原文字幕}come to see you about the hydrogen bomb?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:32.27,2:28:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你最好去问他\N{\r原文字幕}You'd be better off asking him.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:34.07,2:28:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有这个打算\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I fully intend to.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:36.32,2:28:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会说奥本海默博士坚决反对氢弹吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Would you say that Dr.Oppenheimer was unalterably opposed to the H-bomb?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:40.37,2:28:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 他觉得核融合计划\N{\r原文字幕}No, he thought that a fusion program
Dialogue: 0,2:28:43.41,2:28:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会影响进度良好的核分裂计划\N{\r原文字幕}would come at the expense of our awfully good fission program.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:46.29,2:28:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但事后证明并非如此\N{\r原文字幕}But that proved not to be the case.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:48.46,2:28:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果两者都能兼顾\N{\r原文字幕}In the event, both could be done.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:50.79,2:28:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,假设本委员会并不认为\N{\r原文字幕}Suppose that this board did not feel satisfied that,
Dialogue: 0,2:28:53.05,2:28:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士的证词完全属实\N{\r原文字幕}in his testimony here, Dr.Oppenheimer had been wholly truthful.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:57.22,2:28:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为是否该给予他安全许可？\N{\r原文字幕}What would you say whether or not he should be cleared?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:59.84,2:29:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何执意指控做出如此伟大贡献的人？\N{\r原文字幕}Why go through all this against a man who has accomplished what Dr.Oppenheimer has?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:03.81,2:29:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看他的记录\N{\r原文字幕}Look at his record.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:05.60,2:29:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有一系列的核弹\N{\r原文字幕}We have an A-bomb and a whole series of it.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:07.85,2:29:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也有一系列的氢弹\N{\r原文字幕}We have a whole series of Super bombs.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:09.65,2:29:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们还想要什么？\N{\r原文字幕}What more do you want?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:11.48,2:29:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美人鱼？\N{\r原文字幕}Mermaids?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:13.11,2:29:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认识史特劳斯部长很多年\N{\r原文字幕}But I've known Secretary Strauss for many years,
Dialogue: 0,2:29:16.40,2:29:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得有必要肯定他对…\N{\r原文字幕}and I feel it a necessity to express the warm support
Dialogue: 0,2:29:20.03,2:29:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学和科学家的热烈支持\N{\r原文字幕}for science and scientists Lewis has shown.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:22.62,2:29:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先暂时休会 除非有要事\N{\r原文字幕}We'll break now, unless there's any immediate business.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:25.33,2:29:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参议员 我想再次要求…\N{\r原文字幕}Senator, I'd like to once again request
Dialogue: 0,2:29:28.46,2:29:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,检方向我们提供证人名单\N{\r原文字幕}that we're furnished with a list of witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:31.25,2:29:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想提醒候选人我们不一定会事先取得\N{\r原文字幕}And I will remind the nominee that we don't always have that information in advance.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:35.84,2:29:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道希尔博士午饭后会出席\N{\r原文字幕}We do know that Dr.Hill will be here after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:39.34,2:29:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生 下一位证人劳伦斯博士…\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Chairman, our next scheduled witness, Dr.Lawrence,
Dialogue: 0,2:29:41.68,2:29:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很不幸得了结肠炎\N{\r原文字幕}has apparently come down with colitis.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:47.68,2:29:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以会请威廉波登出席作证\N{\r原文字幕}So we'll proceed with William Borden instead.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:51.06,2:29:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波登先生 欢迎\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Borden, welcome.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:52.56,2:29:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请坐\N{\r原文字幕}Please take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:55.15,2:29:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,波登先生\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Borden,
Dialogue: 0,2:29:57.53,2:30:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在调查奥本海默博士的期间\N{\r原文字幕}during your investigation into Dr.Oppenheimer,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:00.11,2:30:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否得到某些结论？\N{\r原文字幕}did you reach certain conclusions?  -I did.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:02.45,2:30:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -你是否…\N{\r原文字幕}And did there come a time
Dialogue: 0,2:30:04.28,2:30:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,写信将结论告知联邦调查局局长\N{\r原文字幕}when you expressed those conclusions in a letter to Mr.J.Edgar Hoover of the
Dialogue: 0,2:30:07.79,2:30:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埃德加胡佛先生？\N{\r原文字幕}Federal Bureau of Investigation?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:09.75,2:30:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -你在写信之前\N{\r原文字幕}That is correct.  -Prior to the writing of the letter,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:11.46,2:30:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有没有和任何\N{\r原文字幕}did you discuss the writing
Dialogue: 0,2:30:13.04,2:30:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,原子能委员会相关人士讨论信件内容？\N{\r原文字幕}of the letter with anybody attached to the Atomic Energy Commission?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:15.67,2:30:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\r原文字幕}I did not.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:16.67,2:30:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 你有副本吗？\N{\r原文字幕}-Do you have a copy of the letter?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:17.92,2:30:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有的\N{\r原文字幕}I have one in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:19.05,2:30:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你读出信件内容\N{\r原文字幕}Would you please be so kind as to read it, sir?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:22.47,2:30:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“胡佛先生钧鉴 此信的目的是…”\N{\r原文字幕}"Dear Mr.Hoover, the purpose of this letter is to state--"
Dialogue: 0,2:30:25.43,2:30:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起 能不能…\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry, I'm sorry, if I could have a--
Dialogue: 0,2:30:27.81,2:30:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何拖延时间？他只会读出这封信\N{\r原文字幕}What is the purpose of the delay? He's simply gonna read the letter.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:31.89,2:30:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主席先生 这是我第一次看到这封信\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Chairman, this is the first I've seen of this letter,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:34.61,2:30:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到的声明中…\N{\r原文字幕}and I see statements here,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:36.11,2:30:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少有一项指控不应该被列入记录\N{\r原文字幕}at least one, of a kind that I don't think anyone would like to see go into the record.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:40.07,2:30:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些都是从未提出的指控\N{\r原文字幕}These are accusations that have not previously been made.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:42.82,2:30:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更不是尼柯斯起诉书的一部分\N{\r原文字幕}That are not part of the indictment from Nichols.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:44.78,2:30:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为不该在这里提出这种指控\N{\r原文字幕}Accusations of a kind that I don't think belong here.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:47.20,2:30:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,证人主动写了这封信\N{\r原文字幕}The witness wrote this letter on his own initiative,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:49.37,2:30:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,列出已经提交给委员会的证据\N{\r原文字幕}laying out evidence that has already been before the board.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:51.91,2:30:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的结论是有效的证词\N{\r原文字幕}His conclusions are valid testimony,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:53.50,2:30:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像奥本海默朋友提出的正面结论\N{\r原文字幕}just like the positive conclusions of friends of Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:56.84,2:30:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须公平看待\N{\r原文字幕}It cuts both ways.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:58.42,2:31:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你拿到这封信有多久？\N{\r原文字幕}How long has counsel been in possession of this letter?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:00.63,2:31:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不应该接受你的诘问 盖里森先生\N{\r原文字幕}I don't think I should be subject to cross-examination by you, Mr.Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:04.64,2:31:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本委员会成员都看过这封信\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Garrison, given that we on the board have all read the letter,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:07.80,2:31:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,列入记录不是更好吗？\N{\r原文字幕}wouldn't it be better to have it in the record?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:10.64,2:31:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's proceed.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:13.69,2:31:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“胡佛先生钧鉴…\N{\r原文字幕}"Dear Mr.Hoover,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:15.52,2:31:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此信的目的是陈述我的意见\N{\r原文字幕}the purpose of this letter is to state my opinion
Dialogue: 0,2:31:18.61,2:31:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据多年来对机密证据的研究\N{\r原文字幕}based upon years of study of the available classified evidence,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:22.86,2:31:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为可能性很高\N{\r原文字幕}that more probably than not
Dialogue: 0,2:31:24.95,2:31:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特·奥本海默是苏联间谍\N{\r原文字幕}J.Robert Oppenheimer is an agent of the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:29.83,2:31:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以下的结论均有依据\N{\r原文字幕}The following conclusions are justified.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:32.41,2:31:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其一 1929年至1942年\N{\r原文字幕}One, between 1929 and 1942, more probably than not,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:36.96,2:31:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特·奥本海默是坚定的共产主义者\N{\r原文字幕}J.Robert Oppenheimer was a sufficiently hardened communist,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:40.59,2:31:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自愿向苏联提供情报\N{\r原文字幕}that he volunteered information to the Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:43.22,2:31:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其二 他很有可能…\N{\r原文字幕}Two, more probably than not,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:45.43,2:31:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直都是一名苏联间谍\N{\r原文字幕}he has since been functioning as an espionage agent.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:49.81,2:31:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其三 他很有可能…\N{\r原文字幕}Three, more probably than not,
Dialogue: 0,2:31:52.56,2:31:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在苏联的指示下\N{\r原文字幕}he has since acted under a Soviet directive
Dialogue: 0,2:31:55.02,2:31:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,左右美国军事政策…\N{\r原文字幕}in influencing United States military policy..."
Dialogue: 0,2:31:57.94,2:31:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 罗伯特  -原子能情报…\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry, Robert.  -..."atomic energy, intelligence..."
Dialogue: 0,2:32:00.11,2:32:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及外交政策“  -有人会愿意说出…\N{\r原文字幕}Is anyone ever going to tell the truth about
Dialogue: 0,2:32:03.61,2:32:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场秘密听证会的真相吗？\N{\r原文字幕}what's happening here?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:05.24,2:32:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在请大卫希尔博士出席作证\N{\r原文字幕}We will now hear from Dr.David Hill.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:18.42,2:32:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Hill,
Dialogue: 0,2:32:19.79,2:32:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想发表声明吗？\N{\r原文字幕}would you care to make a statement?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:23.46,2:32:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:24.80,2:32:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被要求针对路易斯史特劳斯作证\N{\r原文字幕}I've been asked to testify about Lewis Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:28.68,2:32:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他曾经担任政府高阶职位多年\N{\r原文字幕}A man who has given years of service in high positions of government
Dialogue: 0,2:32:33.89,2:32:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并以勤奋工作和聪明才智著称\N{\r原文字幕}and who is known to be earnest, hardworking and intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:39.81,2:32:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我将表达自己的观点\N{\r原文字幕}The views I have to express are my own,
Dialogue: 0,2:32:42.44,2:32:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我相信我的证词将表明\N{\r原文字幕}but I believe that much I have to say will help to indicate
Dialogue: 0,2:32:46.95,2:32:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国大多数的科学家\N{\r原文字幕}why most of the scientists in this country
Dialogue: 0,2:32:48.86,2:32:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望史特劳斯先生完全退出政坛\N{\r原文字幕}would prefer to see Mr.Strauss completely out of government.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:55.66,2:32:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你指的是某些科学家对于\N{\r原文字幕}You're referring to the hostility of certain scientists
Dialogue: 0,2:32:59.92,2:33:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯先生的敌意 因为他在…\N{\r原文字幕}directed toward Mr.Strauss because of his commitment to security,
Dialogue: 0,2:33:03.63,2:33:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默事件中致力于维护国家安全？\N{\r原文字幕}as demonstrated in the Oppenheimer affair?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:09.30,2:33:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不是\N{\r原文字幕}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:10.55,2:33:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是因为他针对奥本海默博士…\N{\r原文字幕}Because of the personal vindictiveness
Dialogue: 0,2:33:12.93,2:33:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表现的个人报复心态\N{\r原文字幕}he demonstrated against Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:17.27,2:33:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肃静\N{\r原文字幕}Order.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:19.23,2:33:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肃静\N{\r原文字幕}Order.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:20.44,2:33:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全国大多数的科学家都认为\N{\r原文字幕}It appears to most scientists around this country
Dialogue: 0,2:33:25.36,2:33:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士之所以饱受抨击和磨难…\N{\r原文字幕}that Robert Oppenheimer is now being pilloried
Dialogue: 0,2:33:29.36,2:33:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是因为他表达诚实的意见\N{\r原文字幕}and put through an ordeal because he expressed his honest opinions.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:33.41,2:33:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布希博士 我以为我是为国家服务\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Bush, I thought I was performing a service to my country when hearing this case.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:37.37,2:33:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全国没有一个委员会\N{\r原文字幕}No board in this country should sit in judgment of a man
Dialogue: 0,2:33:40.21,2:33:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,应该批判一个表达强烈意见的人\N{\r原文字幕}because he expressed strong opinions.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:44.21,2:33:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想进行审判 应该审判我\N{\r原文字幕}If you wanna try that case, you should try me.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:47.51,2:33:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请各位原谅我情绪激动\N{\r原文字幕}Excuse me, gentlemen, if I become stirred.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:51.39,2:33:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我感到义愤填膺\N{\r原文字幕}But I am.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:52.76,2:33:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔博士 史特劳斯先生并未提出指控\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Hill, we've already heard that Mr.Strauss did not bring the charges,
Dialogue: 0,2:33:56.89,2:33:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是参与针对奥本海默博士的听证会\N{\r原文字幕}or participate in the hearings against Dr.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:59.94,2:34:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默事件…\N{\r原文字幕}The Oppenheimer matter
Dialogue: 0,2:34:02.56,2:34:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主要是出于路易斯史特劳斯的恶意\N{\r原文字幕}was initiated and carried through largely through the animus of Lewis Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:08.74,2:34:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默曾经嘲笑史特劳斯\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer made mincemeat out of Strauss's position
Dialogue: 0,2:34:11.70,2:34:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于向挪威出口同位素的立场\N{\r原文字幕}on the shipment of isotopes to Norway,
Dialogue: 0,2:34:13.91,2:34:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯从未原谅他的这种公开羞辱\N{\r原文字幕}and Strauss never forgave him this public humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:18.04,2:34:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们之间另一个恩怨则是来自…\N{\r原文字幕}Another controversy between them centered around their differences in judgment
Dialogue: 0,2:34:21.46,2:34:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们对于氢弹对国家安全的歧见\N{\r原文字幕}on how the H-bomb would contribute to national security.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:25.00,2:34:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯利用人事安全系统\N{\r原文字幕}Strauss turned to the personnel security system
Dialogue: 0,2:34:26.96,2:34:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,企图削减奥本海默的影响力\N{\r原文字幕}in order to destroy Oppenheimer's effectiveness.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:30.72,2:34:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯找到少数野心家\N{\r原文字幕}And Strauss was able to find a few ambitious men
Dialogue: 0,2:34:33.72,2:34:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不但与奥本海默的立场相左\N{\r原文字幕}who also disagreed with Oppenheimer's positions
Dialogue: 0,2:34:36.51,2:34:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且嫉妒他在政坛的威望\N{\r原文字幕}and envied him his prestige in government circles.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:39.93,2:34:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从以前到现在都认为\N{\r原文字幕}I've always assumed, and still assume,
Dialogue: 0,2:34:42.19,2:34:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他完全忠于美国\N{\r原文字幕}that he's loyal to the United States.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:44.73,2:34:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对此坚信不移 除非有确切反证\N{\r原文字幕}I believe this. And I shall believe it until I see very conclusive proof to the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:49.23,2:34:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否认为奥本海默博士构成国安风险？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you, or do you not, believe that Dr.Oppenheimer is a security risk?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:56.95,2:35:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾看过奥本海默博士在许多情况下\N{\r原文字幕}In a great number of cases, I have seen Dr.Oppenheimer act in a way which was, to me,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:00.41,2:35:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说很难理解的行为\N{\r原文字幕}exceedingly hard to understand.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:04.25,2:35:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不同意他对很多议题的观点\N{\r原文字幕}I thoroughly disagreed with him in numerous issues,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:06.33,2:35:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说 他的行为既复杂又令人费解\N{\r原文字幕}and his actions, frankly, appeared to me confused and complicated.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:09.80,2:35:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因此我认为…\N{\r原文字幕}To this extent, I feel,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:11.59,2:35:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个国家的利益应该交给\N{\r原文字幕}I want to see the vital interests of this country
Dialogue: 0,2:35:14.68,2:35:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我更能理解…\N{\r原文字幕}in hands which I understand better,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:16.93,2:35:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也更能信任的人\N{\r原文字幕}and therefore trust more.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:19.56,2:35:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你 博士-谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you, Doctor.  -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:25.10,2:35:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:28.86,2:35:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还跟他握手？\N{\r原文字幕}You shook his fucking hand?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:32.24,2:35:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会向他吐口水\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, I would have spit in his face.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:34.07,2:35:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,委员会应该会很不爽\N{\r原文字幕}Not sure the board would have appreciated that.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:36.24,2:35:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还不够有气度吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is it not gentlemanly enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:37.91,2:35:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得你们都太有气度了\N{\r原文字幕}I think you're all being too goddamn gentlemanly.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:40.74,2:35:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格雷一定看出罗博的意图\N{\r原文字幕}Gray must see what Robb is doing.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:42.79,2:35:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为何不阻止他？\N{\r原文字幕}Why doesn't he just shut him down?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:44.79,2:35:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还跟泰勒握手\N{\r原文字幕}And you shaking Teller's hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:47.33,2:35:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能再当一个烈士\N{\r原文字幕}You need to stop playing the martyr.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:51.13,2:35:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据目前的原子能委员会法规\N{\r原文字幕}Under the current AEC guidelines,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:53.55,2:35:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会批准奥本海默的安全许可吗？\N{\r原文字幕}would you clear Dr.Oppenheimer today?
Dialogue: 0,2:36:02.10,2:36:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据我对原子能法案的理解…\N{\r原文字幕}Under my interpretation of the Atomic Energy Act,
Dialogue: 0,2:36:06.73,2:36:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那在我1942年雇用奥本海默时尚未存在\N{\r原文字幕}which did not exist when I hired Dr.Oppenheimer in 1942,
Dialogue: 0,2:36:12.65,2:36:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…我不会批准他的安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}I would not clear him today
Dialogue: 0,2:36:16.28,2:36:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我是委员会成员\N{\r原文字幕}if I were on the commission.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:18.37,2:36:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好 谢谢你 中将\N{\r原文字幕}Good, thank you, General, that is all.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:19.78,2:36:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我也不会批准任何科学家\N{\r原文字幕}But I don't think I'd clear any of those guys.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:22.45,2:36:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诘问完毕\N{\r原文字幕}That's all.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:26.54,2:36:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士并不负责挑选…\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer had no responsibility
Dialogue: 0,2:36:28.71,2:36:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克劳斯富赫斯或给予他安全许可吧？\N{\r原文字幕}in the selection or the clearance of Klaus Fuchs, did he?
Dialogue: 0,2:36:31.29,2:36:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 一点也没错\N{\r原文字幕}No.None at all.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:32.75,2:36:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你今天也不会在听证会上暗示\N{\r原文字幕}And you wouldn't want to leave this board with any suggestion today
Dialogue: 0,2:36:35.51,2:36:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在质疑他对美国的忠诚度\N{\r原文字幕}that you're here questioning his basic loyalty to the United States
Dialogue: 0,2:36:39.09,2:36:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及他在洛斯阿拉莫斯的行为？\N{\r原文字幕}and the operation of Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:40.80,2:36:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝对不会\N{\r原文字幕}By no means.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:41.97,2:36:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不希望让任何人有这种误解\N{\r原文字幕}I hope I didn't lead anyone to believe otherwise for an instant.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:46.14,2:36:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你 中将\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you, General.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:05.12,2:37:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不该让他们久等\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.We shouldn't keep them waiting.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:07.29,2:37:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她会来作证\N{\r原文字幕}She'll be here.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:08.79,2:37:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真的希望她来？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you even want her here?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:10.67,2:37:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,傻瓜和少年才会自以为了解别人的关系\N{\r原文字幕}Only a fool or an adolescent presumes to know someone else's relationship,
Dialogue: 0,2:37:14.67,2:37:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你两者都不是 洛伊德\N{\r原文字幕}and you're neither, Lloyd.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:19.38,2:37:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和琪蒂…\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty and I,
Dialogue: 0,2:37:21.01,2:37:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都是成年人\N{\r原文字幕}we're grown-ups.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:23.22,2:37:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同生死共患难\N{\r原文字幕}We've walked through fire together.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:25.89,2:37:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不会有事\N{\r原文字幕}She'll do fine.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:28.27,2:37:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对共产主义的立场是支持反对或中立？\N{\r原文字幕}Would you describe your views on communism as pro, anti, neutral?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:32.31,2:37:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常强烈反对 我很久没接触共产党\N{\r原文字幕}Very strongly against. I've had nothing to do with communism
Dialogue: 0,2:37:36.15,2:37:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1936年以后就没有\N{\r原文字幕}since 1936, since...
Dialogue: 0,2:37:39.24,2:37:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我认识罗伯特之前\N{\r原文字幕}since before I met Robert.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:42.82,2:37:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诘问完毕\N{\r原文字幕}That's all.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:45.54,2:37:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,记录显示奥本海默在秘密听证会\N{\r原文字幕}The record demonstrates that Oppenheimer
Dialogue: 0,2:37:47.87,2:37:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并没有受到公正和无私的审问\N{\r原文字幕}was not interrogated by impartial and disinterested counsel for the Gray board.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:51.21,2:37:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是受到一位使用\N{\r原文字幕}He was interrogated by a prosecutor
Dialogue: 0,2:37:53.04,2:37:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狡诈法律诡计的检察官审问\N{\r原文字幕}who used all the tricks of a rather ingenious legal background.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:56.05,2:38:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这是在指控秘密听证会容许这种行为\N{\r原文字幕}You are charging now that the Gray board permitted a prosecution.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:01.01,2:38:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我参与那场听证会\N{\r原文字幕}If I were on the Gray board,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:03.22,2:38:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定会向那位检察官\N{\r原文字幕}I would have protested against the tactics of the man who served, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:05.26,2:38:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,针对他使用的诡计提出抗议\N{\r原文字幕}as the prosecuting counsel.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:08.14,2:38:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,任命他的不是听证会委员\N{\r原文字幕}A man appointed, not by the board,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:11.27,2:38:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是路易斯史特劳斯\N{\r原文字幕}but by Lewis Strauss.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:15.32,2:38:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那位检察官是谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who was this?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:17.90,2:38:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉？\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:19.65,2:38:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那位检察官是谁？\N{\r原文字幕}Who was this?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:21.24,2:38:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗杰罗博\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, Roger Robb.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:22.95,2:38:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默夫人\N{\r原文字幕}Mrs.Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:28.87,2:38:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有共产党员证吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you have a Communist Party membership card?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:32.71,2:38:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定\N{\r原文字幕}I'm-- I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:35.04,2:38:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不确定？\N{\r原文字幕}Not sure?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:38.96,2:38:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是这样的…\N{\r原文字幕}Well--
Dialogue: 0,2:38:43.72,2:38:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么样？\N{\r原文字幕}Well?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:53.40,2:38:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我假设加入共产党…\N{\r原文字幕}I mean, presumably, the act of joining the Party
Dialogue: 0,2:38:56.40,2:38:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要先汇钱才能收到党证 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}required sending some money and receiving a card, no?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:03.20,2:39:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:09.87,2:39:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉\N{\r原文字幕}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:11.91,2:39:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:15.29,2:39:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是很久以前的事 罗博先生\N{\r原文字幕}It's just it was all so very long ago, Mr.Robb, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:18.75,2:39:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不是  -太久了我都忘了\N{\r原文字幕}Not really.  -Long enough to have forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:20.38,2:39:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有没有退回或撕掉？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you return the card or rip it up?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:21.84,2:39:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我早就忘记的党证？\N{\r原文字幕}The card whose existence I've forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:23.59,2:39:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的共产党党证\N{\r原文字幕}Your Communist Party membership card.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:24.88,2:39:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我完全不知道\N{\r原文字幕}-Haven't the slightest idea.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:29.68,2:39:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苏联共产党和共产党有明确的区别吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Can a distinction be made between Soviet communism and communism?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:34.02,2:39:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我仍是党员时绝对认为这两者不同\N{\r原文字幕}In the days when I was a member, I thought they were definitely two things.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:37.48,2:39:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我当时认为美国共产党\N{\r原文字幕}I thought that the Communist Party of the United States
Dialogue: 0,2:39:40.32,2:39:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关心美国国内问题\N{\r原文字幕}was concerned with our domestic problems.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:42.40,2:39:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在不再这么认为\N{\r原文字幕}I now no longer believe this.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:43.99,2:39:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共产主义已经串联并遍佑全世界\N{\r原文字幕}I believe the thing's linked together and spread all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,2:39:46.53,2:39:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在16年前退党之后就这么认为\N{\r原文字幕}and I have believed this since I left the Party, 16 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:50.58,2:39:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是…  -17年前 我说错了\N{\r原文字幕}But-- -17 years ago.My mistake.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:53.50,2:39:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你说…  -抱歉 18年前\N{\r原文字幕}But you sai-- -Sorry, 18.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:56.33,2:39:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,18年前\N{\r原文字幕}18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:58.92,2:39:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道你先生\N{\r原文字幕}Are you familiar with the fact your husband
Dialogue: 0,2:39:59.92,2:40:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到1942年仍为西班牙内战捐款吗？\N{\r原文字幕}was making contributions to the Spanish Civil War as late as 1942?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:04.59,2:40:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道罗伯特偶尔会捐钱\N{\r原文字幕}I knew that Robert gave money from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:06.47,2:40:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道他是向共产党管道捐款吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Did you know this money was going into Communist Party channels?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:09.14,2:40:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说“通过”吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Don't you mean "through"?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:10.68,2:40:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么？  -你应该是说\N{\r原文字幕}-Pardon? I think you mean
Dialogue: 0,2:40:11.89,2:40:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“通过共产党管道” 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}"through Communist Party channels," don't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:14.39,2:40:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -是吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Yes! Yes?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:15.52,2:40:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Yes! -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:17.52,2:40:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是否代表一直到1942年\N{\r原文字幕}Then would it be fair to say that this meant that by 1942,
Dialogue: 0,2:40:20.69,2:40:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你先生仍然和共产党藕断丝连？\N{\r原文字幕}your husband had not stopped having anything to do with the Communist Party?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:24.90,2:40:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不必回答是或否 怎么回答都行\N{\r原文字幕}You don't have to answer that yes or no. You can answer that any way you wish.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:27.70,2:40:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}I know that, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:29.53,2:40:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的问题有毛病\N{\r原文字幕}It's your question.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:31.49,2:40:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的措辞并不正确\N{\r原文字幕}It's not properly phrased.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:32.87,2:40:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你知道我想问什么？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you understand what I'm getting at?  -I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:34.08,2:40:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道  -那你为何不回答？\N{\r原文字幕}Then why don't you answer it that way?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:35.50,2:40:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我不喜欢你的措辞\N{\r原文字幕}'Cause I don't like your phrase.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:37.62,2:40:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“和共产党藕断丝连”\N{\r原文字幕}"Having anything to do with the Communist Party."
Dialogue: 0,2:40:39.58,2:40:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特从来就没和共产党有任何关系\N{\r原文字幕}Because Robert never had anything to do with the Communist Party as such.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:42.84,2:40:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道他捐钱给西班牙难民\N{\r原文字幕}I know he gave money to Spanish refugees.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:45.30,2:40:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也知道他对共产主义思想感兴趣…\N{\r原文字幕}I know he took an intellectual interest in communist ideas--
Dialogue: 0,2:40:48.43,2:40:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否有两种共产主义者？\N{\r原文字幕}Are there two types of communists?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:50.35,2:40:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知识分子或是一般的共产党？\N{\r原文字幕}Intellectual communists and your plain, old, regular commie?
Dialogue: 0,2:40:54.31,2:40:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我回答不了那问题\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I couldn't answer that one.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:57.10,2:40:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也回答不了\N{\r原文字幕}I couldn't either.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:05.44,2:41:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\r原文字幕}Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:06.78,2:41:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特 你赢不了他们\N{\r原文字幕}Robert, you can't win this thing.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:08.20,2:41:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是有预设结果的不公平审判\N{\r原文字幕}It's a kangaroo court with a predetermined outcome.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:10.62,2:41:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何还要继续下去？\N{\r原文字幕}Why put yourself through more of it?
Dialogue: 0,2:41:12.99,2:41:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我自有原因\N{\r原文字幕}I have my reasons.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:16.04,2:41:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:17.41,2:41:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚安\N{\r原文字幕}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:23.17,2:41:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说的有道理\N{\r原文字幕}He has a point.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:25.76,2:41:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定你了解 阿尔伯特\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not sure you understand, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:27.72,2:41:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吗？\N{\r原文字幕}No?
Dialogue: 0,2:41:29.47,2:41:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我离开德国后再也没回去\N{\r原文字幕}I left my country never to return.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:32.93,2:41:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对国家做出伟大贡献\N{\r原文字幕}You served your country well.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:35.18,2:41:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果这个国家是这么回报你…\N{\r原文字幕}If this is the reward she offers you, then...
Dialogue: 0,2:41:38.98,2:41:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许你应该背弃它\N{\r原文字幕}perhaps you should turn your back on her.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:42.27,2:41:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我很爱这个国家\N{\r原文字幕}Damn it, I happen to love this country.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:45.11,2:41:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就叫他们去死吧\N{\r原文字幕}Then tell them to go to hell.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:47.61,2:41:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有趣的是 这不再是确认听证会\N{\r原文字幕}Interestingly enough, this is no longer a confirmation hearing,
Dialogue: 0,2:41:51.57,2:41:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是一场审判\N{\r原文字幕}it's now a trial
Dialogue: 0,2:41:53.58,2:41:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关于另一场审判！\N{\r原文字幕}about a trial!
Dialogue: 0,2:41:56.70,2:41:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说是你发起秘密听证会不是好事\N{\r原文字幕}It's not good he's telling everyone you initiated the hearings.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:59.16,2:42:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他什么都不能证明\N{\r原文字幕}He can't prove a goddamn thing.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:01.33,2:42:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更不能证明是我把档案交给波登\N{\r原文字幕}He certainly can't prove that I gave the file to Borden.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:04.75,2:42:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这并不是法庭\N{\r原文字幕}We're not in court, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:06.21,2:42:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有举证责任\N{\r原文字幕}There's no burden of proof.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:07.96,2:42:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错 他们不想定我罪…\N{\r原文字幕}Right.They're not convicting...
Dialogue: 0,2:42:10.88,2:42:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只想否决我的任命\N{\r原文字幕}just denying.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:13.09,2:42:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔为何来抹黑我？他有何目的？\N{\r原文字幕}But why would Hill come here to tear me down? What's his angle?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:15.51,2:42:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做对的事需要理由吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do people need a reason to do the right thing?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:18.39,2:42:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他认为是对的-我说过…\N{\r原文字幕}As he sees it.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:20.27,2:42:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默第一次和爱因斯坦见面\N{\r原文字幕}I told you, Oppenheimer poisoned the scientists against me,
Dialogue: 0,2:42:22.77,2:42:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就策动科学家反对我\N{\r原文字幕}right from that first meeting.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:24.36,2:42:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道那天他说了什么\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know what Oppenheimer said to him that day,
Dialogue: 0,2:42:27.90,2:42:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但爱因斯坦看都不看我一眼\N{\r原文字幕}but Einstein wouldn't even meet my eye.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:32.03,2:42:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默很会操弄其他科学家\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer knows how to manipulate his own.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:34.66,2:42:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在洛斯阿拉莫斯误导天真的科学家\N{\r原文字幕}And at Los Alamos, he preyed on the naivete of scientists
Dialogue: 0,2:42:38.41,2:42:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们以为能够掌控他们的研究成果\N{\r原文字幕}who thought they'd get a say in how we used their work.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:40.91,2:42:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他从来不觉得自己有那么天真\N{\r原文字幕}Don't ever think he was that naive himself.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:43.71,2:42:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,博士\N{\r原文字幕}Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:45.21,2:42:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在研究氢弹的过程中\N{\r原文字幕}During your work on the hydrogen bomb,
Dialogue: 0,2:42:47.17,2:42:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曾否因为道德疑虑退却？\N{\r原文字幕}were you deterred by any moral qualms?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:50.67,2:42:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:52.18,2:42:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你仍继续研究 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}But you still got on with your work, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:53.97,2:42:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 这是探索性研究 不是武器研制\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, because this was work of exploration.It was not the preparation of a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:58.35,2:43:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以比较像是学术研究\N{\r原文字幕}You mean it was more of an academic excursion?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:00.39,2:43:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 能否制造氢弹不是学术研究\N{\r原文字幕}No, it is not an academic thing whether you can build a hydrogen bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:03.73,2:43:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是攸关生死的问题\N{\r原文字幕}It's a matter of life and death.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:05.36,2:43:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在1942年积极推动…\N{\r原文字幕}By 1942, you were actively pushing
Dialogue: 0,2:43:06.81,2:43:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,氢弹的研制 不是吗？\N{\r原文字幕}the development of the hydrogen bomb, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:08.40,2:43:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,推动并不正确 我只是支持和研究\N{\r原文字幕}Pushing's not the right word.Supporting it and working on it, yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:11.65,2:43:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的道德疑虑在何时强烈到…\N{\r原文字幕}So when did these moral qualms become so strong
Dialogue: 0,2:43:14.07,2:43:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让你积极反对氢弹的研制？\N{\r原文字幕}that you actively opposed the development of the hydrogen bomb?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:17.37,2:43:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当有人建议政府政策应转向…\N{\r原文字幕}When it was suggested that it be the policy of the United States
Dialogue: 0,2:43:20.08,2:43:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不惜任何代价制造氢弹\N{\r原文字幕}to make these things at all cost,
Dialogue: 0,2:43:21.70,2:43:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却无视它和核弹这类武器\N{\r原文字幕}without regard to the balance between these weapons
Dialogue: 0,2:43:24.25,2:43:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与军备之间的平衡\N{\r原文字幕}and atomic weapons as part of our arsenal.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:28.13,2:43:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这与道德疑虑何干？\N{\r原文字幕}What do moral qualms have to do with that?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:31.59,2:43:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这与道德疑虑何干？  -没错\N{\r原文字幕}What do moral qualms have to do with it? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:33.63,2:43:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默想独占核武\N{\r原文字幕}Oppenheimer wanted to own the atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:35.80,2:43:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为能够毁天灭地的人\N{\r原文字幕}He wanted to be the man who moved the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:37.85,2:43:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他谈到要完全消弭核武的威胁\N{\r原文字幕}He talks about putting the nuclear genie back in the bottle.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:42.35,2:43:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我非常了解罗伯特·奥本海默\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I'm here to tell you that I know J.Robert Oppenheimer,
Dialogue: 0,2:43:46.06,2:43:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他能重新来过 还是会做同样的事\N{\r原文字幕}and if he could do it all over, he'd do it all the same.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:49.40,2:43:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道他从来没对广岛感到后悔吗？\N{\r原文字幕}You know he's never once said that he regrets Hiroshima?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:53.03,2:43:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会再做一遍 为什么？\N{\r原文字幕}He'd do it all over.Why?
Dialogue: 0,2:43:55.95,2:43:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为那让他成为史上最重要的人\N{\r原文字幕}Because it made him the most important man who ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:59.83,2:44:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经任意使用原子弹…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, we've freely used the atomic bomb--
Dialogue: 0,2:44:03.66,2:44:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实是你协助军方挑选…\N{\r原文字幕}In fact, Doctor, you assisted in selecting the target
Dialogue: 0,2:44:05.79,2:44:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向日本投放原子弹的城市 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}to drop the atomic bomb on Japan, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:08.50,2:44:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -那你就知道\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.  -Then you knew, did you not,
Dialogue: 0,2:44:09.96,2:44:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将原子弹投放在你挑选的城市\N{\r原文字幕}that by dropping that atomic bomb on the target you selected,
Dialogue: 0,2:44:12.46,2:44:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会导致成千上万平民伤亡 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}that thousands of civilians would be killed or injured, is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:15.88,2:44:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 但没有预期的多\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, not as many as turned out--
Dialogue: 0,2:44:18.72,2:44:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伤亡人数到底是多少？\N{\r原文字幕}Oh.Well, how many were killed or injured?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:20.56,2:44:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,7万  -7万是指广岛…\N{\r原文字幕}70,000. 70,000 at both Hiroshima and--
Dialogue: 0,2:44:22.89,2:44:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,各有11万\N{\r原文字幕}110,000 at both.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:24.60,2:44:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在轰炸的当天？\N{\r原文字幕}On the day of each bombing?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:28.06,2:44:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  -之后的几周和几年呢？\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.  -And in the weeks and years that followed?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:30.19,2:44:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,估计大约在5万和10万之间\N{\r原文字幕}It has been put at somewhere between 50,000 and 100,000.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:33.40,2:44:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少有22万人死亡？  -是的\N{\r原文字幕}220,000 dead, at least.  -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:35.61,2:44:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你感到内疚吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Any moral scruples about that?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:39.16,2:44:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常内疚\N{\r原文字幕}Terrible ones.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:40.16,2:44:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你却作证说轰炸广岛非常成功\N{\r原文字幕}Yet you testified in here that the bombing of Hiroshima was very successful.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:44.16,2:44:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,技术上的成功\N{\r原文字幕}Technically successful.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:45.71,2:44:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,技术上来说非常成功\N{\r原文字幕}-Oh! Technically, it was very successful.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:47.17,2:44:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且也帮助终结了战争\N{\r原文字幕}And it is also alleged to have helped end the war.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:49.63,2:44:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会支持在广岛投放氢弹吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Would you have been supportive of the dropping of a hydrogen bomb on Hiroshima?
Dialogue: 0,2:44:52.88,2:44:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那完全没道理\N{\r原文字幕}That would make no sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:54.51,2:44:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？  -目标太小了\N{\r原文字幕}-Why? The target is too small.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:57.13,2:44:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,假设日本有一个目标…\N{\r原文字幕}Well, supposing there had been a target in Japan big enough
Dialogue: 0,2:44:59.39,2:45:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大到可以投放热核武 你会反对吗？\N{\r原文字幕}for a thermonuclear weapon, would you have been opposed to the dropping of it?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:02.51,2:45:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是我曾面对的问题…\N{\r原文字幕}This was not a problem with which I was confronted--
Dialogue: 0,2:45:04.60,2:45:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在要逼你面对\N{\r原文字幕}I'm confronting you with it now, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:06.14,2:45:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这都是他的盘算\N{\r原文字幕}It was all part of his plan.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:07.81,2:45:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想为自己塑造出深感内疚…\N{\r原文字幕}He wanted the glorious, insincere guilt of the self-important
Dialogue: 0,2:45:11.69,2:45:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自以为是圣人的形象\N{\r原文字幕}to wear like a fucking crown.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:13.86,2:45:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才会说 “不能走上这条不归路”\N{\r原文字幕}Say, "No, we cannot go down this road,"
Dialogue: 0,2:45:16.74,2:45:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然他知道这是必要的\N{\r原文字幕}even as he knew we'd have to.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:19.49,2:45:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会因为良心不安反对在日本\N{\r原文字幕}Would you have been opposed to the dropping... ...of a thermonuclear weapon on Japan
Dialogue: 0,2:45:23.03,2:45:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投下氢弹吗？  -我相信我会\N{\r原文字幕}because of moral scruples? Yes, I believe I would, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:25.12,2:45:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你曾因为良心不安反对在广岛\N{\r原文字幕}Did you oppose the dropping of an atomic bomb on Hiroshima
Dialogue: 0,2:45:27.37,2:45:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投下原子弹吗？\N{\r原文字幕}because of moral scruples?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:29.00,2:45:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们提出我们的论点…\N{\r原文字幕}We set forth our arg--
Dialogue: 0,2:45:30.46,2:45:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你 我说的是你\N{\r原文字幕}-No, you. I'm asking you. You!
Dialogue: 0,2:45:31.67,2:45:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我提出…  -我说的是你！\N{\r原文字幕}-I set-- I set forth
Dialogue: 0,2:45:33.67,2:45:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人反对投放原子弹 但我并不支持\N{\r原文字幕}our arguments against dropping it, but I did not endorse them.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:36.92,2:45:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说三年来夜以继日制造出原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}You mean after working night and day for three years building the bomb,
Dialogue: 0,2:45:40.13,2:45:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你却反对使用它\N{\r原文字幕}you then argued against the use of it.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:42.18,2:45:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,战争部长问我科学家的意见是什么\N{\r原文字幕}I was asked by the secretary of war what the views of scientists were.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:45.97,2:45:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我给了他赞成与反对的意见\N{\r原文字幕}I gave him the views against and the views for.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:48.77,2:45:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你支持在日本投放原子弹\N{\r原文字幕}You supported the dropping of the atom bomb on Japan.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:50.77,2:45:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“支持” 是什么意思？\N{\r原文字幕}What do you mean, "support"?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:51.94,2:45:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说的 “支持” 是什么意思？\N{\r原文字幕}-You supported it.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:53.36,2:45:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮忙挑选目标 不是吗？\N{\r原文字幕}You helped pick the target, didn't you?  -I did my job.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:55.11,2:45:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我的工作 我并不负责做出决策\N{\r原文字幕}I was not in a policy-making position at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:58.49,2:46:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时我被要求做的事我都会去做\N{\r原文字幕}I would have done anything I was asked to do.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:00.45,2:46:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你也会制造氢弹 不是吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Then you would have built the H-bomb too, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:02.95,2:46:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能  -我不是那么问你！\N{\r原文字幕}I couldn't.  -I didn't ask you that, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:05.62,2:46:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在苏联试爆核弹后撰写的…\N{\r原文字幕}And the GAC report, which you co-authored after the Soviet atomic test,
Dialogue: 0,2:46:07.95,2:46:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总顾问委员会报告中说不该制造氢弹！\N{\r原文字幕}said a Super bomb should never be built.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:12.71,2:46:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们 我的意思是…\N{\r原文字幕}What we meant-- What I meant was--
Dialogue: 0,2:46:14.25,2:46:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到底是谁？  -我的意思是…\N{\r原文字幕}What you? Who? Who?  -What I meant--
Dialogue: 0,2:46:17.88,2:46:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道苏联不会不择手段增加武力吗？\N{\r原文字幕}And wouldn't the Russians do anything to increase their strength?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:21.51,2:46:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们制造氢弹 他们也必须跟进\N{\r原文字幕}If we did it, they would have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:23.59,2:46:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只会助长他们的企图心\N{\r原文字幕}Our efforts would only fuel their efforts,
Dialogue: 0,2:46:25.60,2:46:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像原子弹一样\N{\r原文字幕}just as it had with the atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:27.81,2:46:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“就像原子弹一样” 一点都没错！\N{\r原文字幕}"Just as it had with the atomic bomb," exactly!
Dialogue: 0,2:46:31.60,2:46:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1945年不会内疚 1949年却深感内疚\N{\r原文字幕}No moral scruples in 1945, plenty in 1949.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:40.07,2:46:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.Oppenheimer...
Dialogue: 0,2:46:43.57,2:46:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你反对氢弹的强烈道德感…\N{\r原文字幕}when did your strong moral convictions develop
Dialogue: 0,2:46:46.33,2:46:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是从何时开始有的？\N{\r原文字幕}with respect to the hydrogen bomb?
Dialogue: 0,2:46:56.00,2:46:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我清楚知道…\N{\r原文字幕}When it became clear to me...
Dialogue: 0,2:46:59.13,2:47:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类会使用拥有的任何武器\N{\r原文字幕}that we would tend to use any weapon we had.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:05.30,2:47:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特·奥本海默成为烈士\N{\r原文字幕}J.Robert Oppenheimer the Martyr.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:07.60,2:47:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我让他成为他想成为的人\N{\r原文字幕}I gave him exactly what he wanted.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:10.85,2:47:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为研发原子弹留名青史\N{\r原文字幕}To be remembered for Trinity,
Dialogue: 0,2:47:12.48,2:47:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是因为广岛\N{\r原文字幕}not Hiroshima.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:15.19,2:47:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是因为长崎\N{\r原文字幕}Not Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:20.15,2:47:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他应该感谢我\N{\r原文字幕}He should be thanking me.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:22.90,2:47:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他并不感谢你\N{\r原文字幕}Well, he's not.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:27.66,2:47:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还有足够的同意票\N{\r原文字幕}Do we still have enough votes,
Dialogue: 0,2:47:29.41,2:47:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是我政治生涯的巅峰\N{\r原文字幕}or is the crowning moment of my career
Dialogue: 0,2:47:31.20,2:47:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即将成为我一生中最大的羞辱？\N{\r原文字幕}about to become the most public humiliation of my life?
Dialogue: 0,2:47:35.25,2:47:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参议院即将投票\N{\r原文字幕}Full Senate's about to vote.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:37.75,2:47:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会勉强过关\N{\r原文字幕}You'll scrape through.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:38.92,2:47:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了 召开记者会吧\N{\r原文字幕}Great, then gather the fucking press.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:40.80,2:47:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特·奥本海默博士\N{\r原文字幕}Dr.J.Robert Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:42.59,2:47:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本委员会听取了你的证词\N{\r原文字幕}This board, having heard testimony from you
Dialogue: 0,2:47:45.59,2:47:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你目前和前任同事的证词\N{\r原文字幕}and many of your current and former colleagues,
Dialogue: 0,2:47:48.89,2:47:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一致认为你是一名忠诚的公民\N{\r原文字幕}has come to the unanimous conclusion that you are a loyal citizen.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:55.27,2:48:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是有监于你持续与共产党之间的关系\N{\r原文字幕}However, in the light of your continuing associations
Dialogue: 0,2:48:00.57,2:48:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且藐视这个国家的安全机构\N{\r原文字幕}and disregard for the security apparatus of this country,
Dialogue: 0,2:48:04.24,2:48:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加上你对于氢弹计划令人不安的行为\N{\r原文字幕}together with your somewhat disturbing conduct on the hydrogen bomb program,
Dialogue: 0,2:48:10.24,2:48:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及你对本委员会的回应不够坦承\N{\r原文字幕}and the regrettable lack of candor in certain of your responses to this board,
Dialogue: 0,2:48:14.37,2:48:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们以二比一的票数…\N{\r原文字幕}we have voted two-to-one
Dialogue: 0,2:48:17.33,2:48:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否决恢复你的安全许可\N{\r原文字幕}to deny the renewal of your security clearance.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:20.46,2:48:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,书面报告 加上艾凡斯对此决定的异议\N{\r原文字幕}A full written opinion, with a dissent from Mr.Evans,
Dialogue: 0,2:48:23.92,2:48:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将完整地提交给原子能委员会\N{\r原文字幕}will be issued to the AEC in the coming days.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:27.09,2:48:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,散会\N{\r原文字幕}That is all.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:32.35,2:48:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高登…  -罗杰\N{\r原文字幕}Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:39.02,2:48:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:41.11,2:48:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Robert.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:49.37,2:48:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要去收床单\N{\r原文字幕}Don't, uh...Don't take in the sheets.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:54.95,2:48:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生\N{\r原文字幕}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:56.58,2:48:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两分钟\N{\r原文字幕}-Two minutes...
Dialogue: 0,2:48:59.04,2:49:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们会有机会发问\N{\r原文字幕}You'll get your shot.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:00.29,2:49:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们等了很久\N{\r原文字幕}We waited a long time
Dialogue: 0,2:49:01.63,2:49:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出来吧  -先生！\N{\r原文字幕}Come on out! - Sir!
Dialogue: 0,2:49:03.92,2:49:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,已成定局了吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is it official?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:07.34,2:49:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有几张没想到的反对票\N{\r原文字幕}Well, there were a couple of unexpected holdouts.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:16.31,2:49:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我被否决了 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}I'm denied.Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:19.15,2:49:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕是的  -好吧\N{\r原文字幕}I'm afraid so, sir.All right.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:28.61,2:49:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁投反对票？\N{\r原文字幕}Who were the holdouts?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:30.82,2:49:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有三个人\N{\r原文字幕}Um...There were three,
Dialogue: 0,2:49:32.74,2:49:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来自麻省的初任参议员带头\N{\r原文字幕}led by the junior senator from Massachusetts.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:35.66,2:49:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个想出名的年轻人\N{\r原文字幕}Young guy trying to make a name for himself,
Dialogue: 0,2:49:37.41,2:49:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不喜欢你对奥本海默做的事\N{\r原文字幕}didn't like what you did to Oppenheimer.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:39.75,2:49:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫什么名字？\N{\r原文字幕}What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:42.42,2:49:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甘迺迪  约翰·甘迺迪\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, Kennedy.John F.Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:48.51,2:49:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,琪蒂？\N{\r原文字幕}Kitty?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:56.02,2:49:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你认为你让他们公开抹黑你…\N{\r原文字幕}Did you think that if you let them tar and feather you,
Dialogue: 0,2:49:59.77,2:50:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世人就会原谅你？\N{\r原文字幕}that the world would forgive you?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:05.48,2:50:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不会的\N{\r原文字幕}It won't.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:09.24,2:50:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等着瞧吧\N{\r原文字幕}We'll see.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:20.54,2:50:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死\N{\r原文字幕}Goddamn it.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:24.96,2:50:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你明明说我会过关\N{\r原文字幕}You told me I'd be okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:27.09,2:50:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没掌握所有的事实 对吧？\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, well, I didn't have all the facts, did I?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:29.34,2:50:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这才是事实\N{\r原文字幕}Here's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:30.51,2:50:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾森豪总统去年亲自为我别上自由勋章\N{\r原文字幕}President Eisenhower pinned the Medal of Freedom on my chest last year,
Dialogue: 0,2:50:34.60,2:50:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我一直都以国家利益为优先\N{\r原文字幕}'cause I've always done what's right for this country.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:36.89,2:50:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不想让我进入内阁？\N{\r原文字幕}They don't want me in the Cabinet room?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:39.35,2:50:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 无所谓\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, that's--That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:41.73,2:50:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他们应该邀请奥本海默入阁\N{\r原文字幕}Maybe they should just invite Oppenheimer instead.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:44.06,2:50:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他们会\N{\r原文字幕}Maybe they will.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:46.11,2:50:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说过 他让每个科学家跟我作对\N{\r原文字幕}I told you, he turned the scientists against me one by one,
Dialogue: 0,2:50:50.28,2:50:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先是爱因斯坦 我跟你说过\N{\r原文字幕}starting with Einstein. I told you about Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:52.36,2:50:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看到他在池塘旁边\N{\r原文字幕}I saw him by the pond.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:53.82,2:50:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说过 但你要知道\N{\r原文字幕}You did, but you know, sir,
Dialogue: 0,2:50:55.45,2:50:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既然没人知道他们那天聊了什么…\N{\r原文字幕}since nobody really knows what they said to each other that day,
Dialogue: 0,2:50:59.20,2:51:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他们完全没聊到你？\N{\r原文字幕}is it possible they didn't talk about you at all?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:03.33,2:51:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他们聊的是…\N{\r原文字幕}Is it possible they spoke about something
Dialogue: 0,2:51:06.34,2:51:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更重要的事？\N{\r原文字幕}more important?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:07.71,2:51:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,史特劳斯先生！\N{\r原文字幕}Mr.Strauss!
Dialogue: 0,2:51:22.64,2:51:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢谢谢谢谢谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:23.81,2:51:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Albert.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:28.44,2:51:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当下的焦点人物\N{\r原文字幕}The man of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:34.16,2:51:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为我办过一场欢迎会\N{\r原文字幕}You once held a reception for me.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:37.45,2:51:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在伯克利 你颁给我一个奖项\N{\r原文字幕}In Berkeley.You gave me an award, mmm?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:39.99,2:51:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:41.91,2:51:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们都以为我已经搞不懂我发明的理论\N{\r原文字幕}You all thought that I had lost the ability to understand what I'd started.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:48.42,2:51:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个奖项不是颁给我 而是颁给你们\N{\r原文字幕}So, the award really wasn't for me. It was for all of you, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,2:51:54.97,2:51:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在轮到你…\N{\r原文字幕}Now it's your turn
Dialogue: 0,2:51:57.18,2:52:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须面对你的成就造成的后果\N{\r原文字幕}to deal with the consequences of your achievement.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:02.77,2:52:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有一天 当他们决定不再惩罚你\N{\r原文字幕}And one day, when they've punished you enough...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:08.40,2:52:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就会请你吃鲑鱼和马铃薯沙拉\N{\r原文字幕}they'll serve you salmon and potato salad.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:16.49,2:52:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发表演讲…\N{\r原文字幕}Make speeches...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:19.24,2:52:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,颁给你一枚勋章\N{\r原文字幕}...give you a medal.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:22.79,2:52:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 弗兰克\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:24.41,2:52:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你很幸福 我替你高兴\N{\r原文字幕}You're happy, I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:32.84,2:52:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拍拍你的背 原谅你做的事\N{\r原文字幕}Pat you on the back, tell you all is forgiven.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:37.38,2:52:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是要记住…\N{\r原文字幕}Just remember...
Dialogue: 0,2:52:40.47,2:52:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是为了你\N{\r原文字幕}it won't be for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:47.31,2:52:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是为了他们的形象\N{\r原文字幕}It'll be for them.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:02.33,2:53:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔伯特\N{\r原文字幕}Albert.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:05.62,2:53:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我带着那些计算结果来找你\N{\r原文字幕}When I came to you with those calculations,
Dialogue: 0,2:53:08.83,2:53:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们以为会引发连锁反应\N{\r原文字幕}we thought we might start a chain reaction
Dialogue: 0,2:53:10.92,2:53:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毁灭整个世界\N{\r原文字幕}that would destroy the entire world?
Dialogue: 0,2:53:15.71,2:53:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记得很清楚\N{\r原文字幕}Mmm.I remember it well.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:17.84,2:53:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了？\N{\r原文字幕}What of it?
Dialogue: 0,2:53:22.64,2:53:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信我们做到了\N{\r原文字幕}I believe we did.
